E164Address.name: E164Address
E164Address.description: E164 address format defined as 15 ASCII characters.

AtmConnSchedMode.name: AtmConnSchedMode
AtmConnSchedMode.description: The value of this object identifies the scheduling mode for an ATM connection (i.e., VCC or VPC). The possible values are default, roundrobin, guaranteed, and smoothed.

AtmOrigPathSchedMode.name: AtmOrigPathSchedMode
AtmOrigPathSchedMode.description: The value of this object identifies the scheduling mode for an originating path. The possible values are flat, shaped and shaped-roundrobin.

AAL5CountingMode.name: AAL5CountingMode
AAL5CountingMode.description: The value of this object identifies the AAL5 counting mode for a connection (i.e., VCC or VPC). Possible values for this object are default, cell-counting and packet-counting.

boardTable.name: boardTable
boardTable.description: A table of ATM switch board information.

boardEntry.name: boardEntry
boardEntry.description: A table entry containing ATM switch board information.

boardIndex.name: boardIndex
boardIndex.description: The index of this board within the ATM switch.

boardVersion.name: boardVersion
boardVersion.description: The ATM switch board version number in hex. The version number 0x1 is revision A, 0x2 is revision B etc. Version number 0x0 represents an unknown type.

boardModel.name: boardModel
boardModel.description: The ATM switch board model number.

boardSerialNumber.name: boardSerialNumber
boardSerialNumber.description: The ATM switch board serial number.

numberOfModules.name: numberOfModules
numberOfModules.description: The number of network modules on this ATM switch board.

vpiLookupErrors.name: vpiLookupErrors
vpiLookupErrors.description: The number of VPI lookup errors.

vciLookupErrors.name: vciLookupErrors
vciLookupErrors.description: The number of VCI lookup errors.

boardControlPort.name: boardControlPort
boardControlPort.description: This object identifies the index for the control port on this switch board.

boardHDCOMPAsicVersion.name: boardHDCOMPAsicVersion
boardHDCOMPAsicVersion.description: This object identifies the version number of the HDCOMP ASIC on this switch board.

boardMcastSpaceIndex.name: boardMcastSpaceIndex
boardMcastSpaceIndex.description: This object is the index into mcastSpaceTable that gives the number of multicast connections currently supported on this board. Changing this value has the effect of changing the number of multicast connections supported. Change will be effective after reboot only.

numberOfBoards.name: numberOfBoards
numberOfBoards.description: The number of switch boards on this ATM switch.

procUtilLastUpdate.name: procUtilLastUpdate
procUtilLastUpdate.description: The time the procUtilValue was last updated

procUtilValue.name: procUtilValue
procUtilValue.description: The percentage of the processor power that has been used over the last monitoring interval

procUtilMonInterval.name: procUtilMonInterval
procUtilMonInterval.description: The amount of time between calculations of the procUtilValue. This value is expressed in units of 10 msec, (100 per sec). This value may take the value of 1 to 60 seconds

procUtilMinLoad.name: procUtilMinLoad
procUtilMinLoad.description: The MIN percentage of the processor power that has been. This value can be reset by setting the field procUtilHistoryReset.

procUtilMinLoadLastUpdate.name: procUtilMinLoadLastUpdate
procUtilMinLoadLastUpdate.description: The time the procUtilMinLoad was last updated

procUtilMaxLoad.name: procUtilMaxLoad
procUtilMaxLoad.description: The MAX percentage of the processor power that has been. This value can be reset by setting the field procUtilHistoryReset.

procUtilMaxLoadLastUpdate.name: procUtilMaxLoadLastUpdate
procUtilMaxLoadLastUpdate.description: The time the procUtilMaxLoad was last updated

procUtilHistoryReset.name: procUtilHistoryReset
procUtilHistoryReset.description: This is in effect a WRITE_ONLY field. Setting this field resets the procUtilMinLoad, procUtilMinLoadLastUpdate, procUtilMaxLoad, and procUtilMaxLoadLastUpdate. This field can be set to anything by the NMS. When this field is read, it will always report NULL.

procUtilsNumMallocPart.name: procUtilsNumMallocPart
procUtilsNumMallocPart.description: The number of malloc partitions used on this SCP.

procUtilsSystemPartitionID.name: procUtilsSystemPartitionID
procUtilsSystemPartitionID.description: The partition ID os the system MALLOC pool. Use this value as an ID into the mallocUtilTable to view the system malloc pool statistics

boardStatsEntry.name: boardStatsEntry
boardStatsEntry.description: A table entry containing ATM switch fabric statistics information.

boardStatsBoard.name: boardStatsBoard
boardStatsBoard.description: The index of this fabric within the ATM switch.

boardStatsIndex.name: boardStatsIndex
boardStatsIndex.description: The index of this statistics within the ATM switch fabric.

boardStatsName.name: boardStatsName
boardStatsName.description: The name of this statistics within the ATM switch fabric.

boardStatsValue.name: boardStatsValue
boardStatsValue.description: The value of this statistics within the ATM switch fabric.

portCardTable.name: portCardTable
portCardTable.description: A table of ATM switch port card information.

portCardEntry.name: portCardEntry
portCardEntry.description: A table entry containing ATM switch port card information.

portCardIndex.name: portCardIndex
portCardIndex.description: The unique index of this port card within the ATM switch.

portCardName.name: portCardName
portCardName.description: The name of this port card.

portCardFlavor.name: portCardFlavor
portCardFlavor.description: The flavor of this port card.

portCardAssemblyRevision.name: portCardAssemblyRevision

portCardHardwareConf.name: portCardHardwareConf

portCardState.name: portCardState

boardTrafficManagementPerPriorityTable.name: boardTrafficManagementPerPriorityTable
boardTrafficManagementPerPriorityTable.description: A table of ATM switch fabric traffic management features that can be controlled per fabric and per priority.

boardTrafficManagementPerPriorityEntry.name: boardTrafficManagementPerPriorityEntry

btmPerPriorityPriority.description: The index of the traffic priority.

btmPerPriorityPriorityName.name: btmPerPriorityPriorityName
btmPerPriorityPriorityName.description: The name of the traffic priority (e.g. CBR or UBR).

btmPerPriorityValue.name: btmPerPriorityValue
btmPerPriorityValue.description: The value of the specified feature for the specified priority.

moduleTable.name: moduleTable
moduleTable.description: A table of network module information.

moduleEntry.name: moduleEntry
moduleEntry.description: A table entry containing network module information.

moduleBoard.name: moduleBoard
moduleBoard.description: The index of this board within the ATM switch.

moduleNumber.name: moduleNumber
moduleNumber.description: The number of this network module within the ATM switch.

moduleName.name: moduleName
moduleName.description: The type name of this network module within the ATM switch.

moduleSpeed.name: moduleSpeed
moduleSpeed.description: The speed of this network module within the ATM switch.

moduleNumberOfPorts.name: moduleNumberOfPorts
moduleNumberOfPorts.description: The number of ports on this network module.

moduleUptime.name: moduleUptime
moduleUptime.description: The length of time this network module has been up, in hundredths of a second.

moduleHwMajorRev.name: moduleHwMajorRev
moduleHwMajorRev.description: The hardware major revision number of the network module. For generationD network modules this revision number is an ascii character value.

moduleHwMinorRev.name: moduleHwMinorRev
moduleHwMinorRev.description: The hardware minor revision number of the network module.

moduleVersion.name: moduleVersion
moduleVersion.description: The hardware version of this network module.

moduleTimingSupport.name: moduleTimingSupport
moduleTimingSupport.description: Does this network module support distributed timing?

moduleProductNumber.name: moduleProductNumber
moduleProductNumber.description: The product number of this network module.

moduleState.name: moduleState
moduleState.description: The desired state of this network module. If set to reset(1), the netmod is reset. Normally, when the netmod is active, it is inService(2). To put a netmod out of service, this entry must be set to outOfService(3).

moduleSerialNumber.name: moduleSerialNumber
moduleSerialNumber.description: The string representing the serial number for this network module.

moduleTestAdminStatus.name: moduleTestAdminStatus
moduleTestAdminStatus.description: This variable indicates the hardware test configuration of the network module. It can be set to startTest(2), which starts the hardware tests on the network module. abortTest(3) aborts the test, if the network module is under test. The network module returns to normal(0) after the test ends or is aborted.

moduleTestOperStatus.name: moduleTestOperStatus
moduleTestOperStatus.description: The status of the hardware tests on the network module. normal (1) indicates that the network module has never undergone hardware tests. The network module is underTest (2), after the test is started on it, and goes to testSuccessful (3) or testFailed (4), after the tests end. If the tests are aborted, the network module goes to testAborted (5) state. Those network modules that do not support hardware tests like Series-C and LC modules, are in testUnsupported (6) state.

moduleTestStatusText.name: moduleTestStatusText
moduleTestStatusText.description: A message describing the status of the current test

moduleAttachState.name: moduleAttachState
moduleAttachState.description: The actual state of this network module. The netmod state is directed by the moduleState variable. This variable gives the actual state at a given time (which may lag behind the moduleState by several seconds).

moduleCLEI.name: moduleCLEI
moduleCLEI.description: The Common Language Equipment identifications (CLEI) of this network module.

appModuleTable.name: appModuleTable
appModuleTable.description: A table consisting of hardware components that have on-board CPUs. Currently, the FR/ATM, FUNI and IMA network modules appear in this table.

appModuleEntry.name: appModuleEntry
appModuleEntry.description: A table entry containing application module information.

appModuleIndex.name: appModuleIndex
appModuleIndex.description: The index of the application module in this switch.

appModuleName.name: appModuleName
appModuleName.description: The name of this application module.

appModuleOperState.name: appModuleOperState
appModuleOperState.description: The operational state of this network module's hardware.

appModuleStatusText.name: appModuleStatusText
appModuleStatusText.description: A text string describing the current state of the hardware.

appModuleApplicationType.name: appModuleApplicationType
appModuleApplicationType.description: This variable indicates the application(s) running on this application module.

appModuleSoftwareVersion.name: appModuleSoftwareVersion
appModuleSoftwareVersion.description: Version of the software running on this application module.

appModuleBootSoftwareVersion.name: appModuleBootSoftwareVersion
appModuleBootSoftwareVersion.description: Version of the BOOT PROM software on this application module.

appModuleOosLed.name: appModuleOosLed
appModuleOosLed.description: The color of the OOS LED on the application module. This LED is off (1) when the network module is up and running and red (2) when the network module is down (administratively placed out of service or operationally down temporarily). For example, when the network module's hardware initialization is in progress, the LED will be red until the hardware initialization is complete.

appModulePanicAction.name: appModulePanicAction
appModulePanicAction.description: This variable indicates the action to be taken if the on-board CPU fails. This module will be reset if this variable is set to reset(1) and will be suspended if this variable is set to suspend(2).

outputBufferTable.name: outputBufferTable
outputBufferTable.description: A table of output buffer information.

outputBufferEntry.name: outputBufferEntry
outputBufferEntry.description: A table entry containing output buffer information.

obufBoard.name: obufBoard
obufBoard.description: The index of this output buffer's switch board.

obufNumber.name: obufNumber
obufNumber.description: The number of the network module for this output buffer.

obufType.name: obufType
obufType.description: The Priority of this output buffer- 0 is lowest priority

obufOperStatus.name: obufOperStatus
obufOperStatus.description: The operational status of this output buffer.

obufBufferSize.name: obufBufferSize
obufBufferSize.description: The logical size of this output buffer, in cells.

obufQueueLength.name: obufQueueLength
obufQueueLength.description: The number of cells in this output buffer.

obufOverflows.name: obufOverflows
obufOverflows.description: The number of cells dropped because this output buffer was full.

obufPriorityName.name: obufPriorityName
obufPriorityName.description: The priority name (eg. CBR, VBR) for this buffer.

hwPortTable.name: hwPortTable
hwPortTable.description: A table of hardware port information.

hwPortEntry.name: hwPortEntry
hwPortEntry.description: A table entry containing hardware port information.

hwPortBoard.name: hwPortBoard
hwPortBoard.description: The switch board index of this port.

hwPortModule.name: hwPortModule
hwPortModule.description: The network module number of this port.

hwPortNumber.name: hwPortNumber
hwPortNumber.description: The number of this port within its network module.

hwPortVersion.name: hwPortVersion
hwPortVersion.description: The generation of this network module. In general, generation A indicates the most original FORE Systems netmods. Generation-B are intermediate DS3/E3/TAXI. Generation-C are shared-memory based netmods.

hwPortModel.name: hwPortModel
hwPortModel.description: The type of physical connection of this port. The model-ASX(7) indicates this is the control port of the switch. NOTE: as of 2/8/95 the elements model-6port-TAXI-100(6) and model-DS3-PDH(16) should no longer be used. Use the basic types model-TAXI-100(1) and model-DS3(3) to indicate these.

hwPortOperStatus.name: hwPortOperStatus
hwPortOperStatus.description: The operational status of this port. If a port was administered up (by hwPortAdminStatus), but the carrier or the framing bits were lost, the hwPortOperStatus indicates that the port is down(3). Otherwise, the hwPortOperStatus is up(2).

hwPortBufferSize.name: hwPortBufferSize
hwPortBufferSize.description: The logical size of this port's output buffer, in cells.

hwPortQueueLength.name: hwPortQueueLength
hwPortQueueLength.description: The number of cells in this port's output buffer.

hwPortOverflows.name: hwPortOverflows
hwPortOverflows.description: The number of seconds in which cells were dropped because this port's output buffer was full.

hwPortErrors.name: hwPortErrors
hwPortErrors.description: The number of seconds in which errored cells were dropped by this port.

hwPortCarrier.name: hwPortCarrier
hwPortCarrier.description: The presence or absence of carrier at this port.

hwPortGlobalIndex.name: hwPortGlobalIndex
hwPortGlobalIndex.description: The global index of this port within the ATM switch as a whole. It corresponds to the port number used in the software group of this MIB.

hwPortName.name: hwPortName
hwPortName.description: A textual description of the port indicating the Board Network module and Port (BNP) identifiers. The module is indicated by a letter (A-D), while the board and the port are indicated by numbers.

hwPortAdminStatus.name: hwPortAdminStatus
hwPortAdminStatus.description: The administrative state of the physical layer of this port. When a port is configured up(1), the physical layer is configured to process all physical layer events including the transmission and reception of data (cells). When a port is configured down(2), the physical layer should be shut down and should ignore all physical layer events (e.g. cell reception, carrier loss, loss of framing, parity errors, etc.). The operational status of a port is reflected in the hwPortOperStatus object.

hwPortTAXILoopback.name: hwPortTAXILoopback
hwPortTAXILoopback.description: This variable represents the loopback status of a TAXI port. For non-TAXI ports (e.g. DS3/E3 or SONET) the loopback configuration should be set in their specific tables.

hwPortLEDModel.name: hwPortLEDModel
hwPortLEDModel.description: The LED model to use for setting the colors of the LEDs on each port. LAN models typically blink the LEDs when data is transmitted or received on the port. WAN models typically keep the LEDs green unless an error condition exists on the port. With SONET netmods the LED models use the following algorithms: LAN (3 states): if (LOS || LOF || AIS_L || LOP_P || UNEQ_P || PLM_P || LCD) { rxLED = RED } else if (RDI_L) { rxLED = YELLOW } else { rxLED = AUTO } txLED = AUTO WAN (3 states): if (LOS || LOF || AIS_L || LOP_P || UNEQ_P || PLM_P || LCD) { rxLED = RED } else if (RDI_L) { rxLED = YELLOW } else { rxLED = GREEN } txLED = GREEN With LAN and WAN models: RED means fault in receive direction, YELLOW means fault in transmit direction (RDI_L defect), AUTO/GREEN means no fault. Only the receive LED color is changed. These models show only three states and do not reflect the status of the AIS_P and RDI_P defects.

hwPortTxLED.name: hwPortTxLED
hwPortTxLED.description: Indicates the color of the transmit LED for this port. Auto means that the LED is under hardware control. Typically hardware control means that the LED is normally dark with green blinks to indicate data traffic.

hwPortRxLED.name: hwPortRxLED
hwPortRxLED.description: Indicates the color of the receive LED for this port. Auto means that the LED is under hardware control. Typically hardware control means that the LED is normally dark with green blinks to indicate data traffic.

hwPortIfIndex.name: hwPortIfIndex
hwPortIfIndex.description: This entry indicates the IfIndex used to identify this port. It corresponds to the ifIndex used in the rfc2233 rfc1573 ifTables

hwPortRxSyncLED.name: hwPortRxSyncLED
hwPortRxSyncLED.description: The synchronization LED which only applies to the receivers. When green, it indicates that the port is providing the 8 khz clock reference to the switch. This is a new entry which makes sense to those netmod ( currently only FRAM netmod support this LED) which can provide a 8 khz clock reference to the switch. At the netmod scope, only one such LED should be green if the switch is importing a port timing clock.

hwPortCounterResetTime.name: hwPortCounterResetTime
hwPortCounterResetTime.description: Indicates when this port's physical interface counters were reset. The TimeStamp is equal to moduleUptime when the reset occurred. If this ports counters were never reset, hwPortCounterResetTime will be zero. This variable is updated whenever hwPortCounterReset or switchCounterReset is written.

hwPortCounterReset.name: hwPortCounterReset
hwPortCounterReset.description: Writing a value of resetRequest will result in a reset of all physical interface counters on this port. VCC indexed counters are excluded. A response value of resetTrue indicates a resetRequest has succeeded and is currently in effect. A response value of resetFalse indicates a reset is not currently in effect.

hwPortSpeed.name: hwPortSpeed
hwPortSpeed.description: The speed of this physical port in the ATM switch.

netmodAlarmsTable.name: netmodAlarmsTable
netmodAlarmsTable.description: A table of network module alarms information categorized on a per slot basis.

netmodAlarmsEntry.name: netmodAlarmsEntry
netmodAlarmsEntry.description: A table entry containing network module alarm information.

netmodSlot.name: netmodSlot
netmodSlot.description: This number represents the unique number of this netmod within the ATM switch. This number starts at 0.

netmodSlotPriority.name: netmodSlotPriority
netmodSlotPriority.description: The priority assigned to this slot. Possible values are High (corresponding to netmodRemovedHighPrio), Low (corresponding to netmodRemovedLowPrio) and None (default)

netmodStatus.name: netmodStatus
netmodStatus.description: The presence/absence of a netmod in this slot is determined by this variable.

netmodName.name: netmodName
netmodName.description: The name of this netmod. Example: 1A, 3D for ASX4000 and A, B for pre-ASX4000 switches.

hdcompTable.name: hdcompTable
hdcompTable.description: A table for information about HDCOMPs.

hdcompEntry.name: hdcompEntry
hdcompEntry.description: A table for information about HDCOMPs.

hdcompIndex.name: hdcompIndex
hdcompIndex.description: Index of the HDCOMP on the switch.

hdcompDescr.name: hdcompDescr
hdcompDescr.description: Description of the HDCOMP location on the switch.

hdcompAsicVersion.name: hdcompAsicVersion
hdcompAsicVersion.description: Version number of the HDCOMP ASIC on the switch.

hdcompVpiLookupErrors.name: hdcompVpiLookupErrors
hdcompVpiLookupErrors.description: The number of VPI lookup errors.

hdcompVciLookupErrors.name: hdcompVciLookupErrors
hdcompVciLookupErrors.description: The number of VCI lookup errors.

swAlarmTable.name: swAlarmTable
swAlarmTable.description: A table of switch alarm definitions and configuration.

swAlarmEntry.name: swAlarmEntry
swAlarmEntry.description: A table entry containing switch alarm definitions.

swAlarmStatus.name: swAlarmStatus
swAlarmStatus.description: The status of this alarm entry. An alarm becomes active if the underlying condition is detected. For power supplies, the input failed alarm condition is asserted if the input voltage is not within the nominal range for the supply. This does not necessarily mean that an ouput failure will result. A power supply output failure condition is asserted if any power supply is failing or if it is physically removed. Power supply output alarms are only applicable to switches with multiple power supplies. Fan bank and temperature sensor failures are applicable only to switches with the appropriate sensing capabilities. Link and spans failures are applicable to all switches.

swAlarmMinorCategory.name: swAlarmMinorCategory
swAlarmMinorCategory.description: This object indicates whether a minor alarm is triggered when this event occurs.

swAlarmMajorCategory.name: swAlarmMajorCategory
swAlarmMajorCategory.description: This object indicates whether a major alarm is triggered when this event occurs.

swAlarmReset.name: swAlarmReset
swAlarmReset.description: The manager may set this to the value 0 or 1 to cancel a current alarm. This is useful for silencing alarms triggered via edge detection. If this variable is readable, then the alarm is resettable.

swAlarmCriticalCategory.name: swAlarmCriticalCategory
swAlarmCriticalCategory.description: This object indicates whether a critical alarm is triggered when this event occurs. This is supported only on certain platforms.

swAlarmACOState.name: swAlarmACOState
swAlarmACOState.description: This object indicates the Alarm Cutoff Status(ACO) of this alarm entry. To silence an active alarm relay condition this value can be set to on(1), by pushing the front panel ACO button. The ACO is turned off when the alarm status(SwAlarmStatus) becomes inactive.

swAlarmMajorRelayState.name: swAlarmMajorRelayState
swAlarmMajorRelayState.description: This object indicates the current state of the major alarm relay. If one or more of the alarms (swAlarmType) that are defined major (swAlarmMajorCategory) are currently active (swAlarmStatus), and the alarm cutoff(swAlarmACOState) is off then this object will be on(1).

swAlarmMinorRelayState.name: swAlarmMinorRelayState
swAlarmMinorRelayState.description: This object indicates the current state of the minor alarm relay. If one or more of the alarms (swAlarmType) that are defined minor (swAlarmMinorCategory) are currently active (swAlarmStatus), and the alarm cutoff(swAlarmACOState) is off then this object will be on(1).

swAlarmCriticalRelayState.name: swAlarmCriticalRelayState
swAlarmCriticalRelayState.description: This object indicates the current state of the critical alarm relay. If one or more of the alarms (swAlarmType) that are defined critical (swAlarmCriticalCategory) are currently active (swAlarmStatus), and the alarm cutoff(swAlarmACOState) is off then this object will be on(1).

swAlarmRelayTable.name: swAlarmRelayTable
swAlarmRelayTable.description: This table contains the alarm relay definitions for the switch alarms

swAlarmRelayEntry.name: swAlarmRelayEntry
swAlarmRelayEntry.description: This entry contains the alarm relay definitions for the switch alarms.

swAlarmRelayIndex.name: swAlarmRelayIndex
swAlarmRelayIndex.description: This is the index of the alarm relay on the switch.

swAlarmRelayFunction.name: swAlarmRelayFunction
swAlarmRelayFunction.description: This is the alarm function associated with an alarm relay on the switch. An alarm relay may either be unused, assigned to one of critical, major and minor alarm.

swAlarmRelayState.name: swAlarmRelayState
swAlarmRelayState.description: This is the current state of the alarm relay. The state 'on' means that the alarm relay is activated; the state 'off' means that it is deactivated.

swAlarmRelayOperMode.name: swAlarmRelayOperMode
swAlarmRelayOperMode.description: This variable represents the operational mode of the relay. The operational mode 'enabled' means that the relay is under software control and the relay state will reflect 'on' or 'off' according to the alarm conditions. 'disabled' will make the alarm relay state always 'off'. 'test' will make it always 'on'.

envMaxNumberOfPowerSupplies.name: envMaxNumberOfPowerSupplies
envMaxNumberOfPowerSupplies.description: The maximum number of power supplies that can be installed on this ATM switch.

envNumberOfPowerSupplies.name: envNumberOfPowerSupplies
envNumberOfPowerSupplies.description: The number of power supply entries in the power supply table. This is the number of power supplies actually present.

envPowerSupplyTable.name: envPowerSupplyTable
envPowerSupplyTable.description: A table of power supply information.

envPowerSupplyEntry.name: envPowerSupplyEntry
envPowerSupplyEntry.description: A table entry containing power supply information.

envPowerSupplyIndex.name: envPowerSupplyIndex
envPowerSupplyIndex.description: The index of this power supply.

envPowerSupplyType.name: envPowerSupplyType
envPowerSupplyType.description: The type of this power supply.

envPowerSupplyInputState.name: envPowerSupplyInputState
envPowerSupplyInputState.description: The state of the input voltage to this power supply.

envPowerSupplyOutputState.name: envPowerSupplyOutputState
envPowerSupplyOutputState.description: The status of the output of this power supply. In case there are several output supplies (like +5V, +12V, -12V) this object indicates the aggregate state of all outputs.

envPowerSupplySerialNumber.name: envPowerSupplySerialNumber
envPowerSupplySerialNumber.description: The serial number of this power supply, if available.

envPowerSupplyVersion.name: envPowerSupplyVersion

envCpuBoardRevision.description: Revision number of this SCP board. A 32-bit number with the most significant 16 bits represent the revison alphabet. For example, 0x20000 represents Rev B, 0xd0000 represents Rev M.

envCpuPromRevision.description: Revision number of the SCP PROM. Currently only available for boards with i960HA and i960HD processors. A 32-bit number. For example, 0x20000 represents Rev 2.0 and 0x20001 represents Rev 2.1

envCpuIDESize.name: envCpuIDESize

It will then indicate `overTemp' until the temperature reaches the current reset threshold (or until the switch fabric is restarted).

ntBoard.name: ntBoard

ntModule.description: The number of this network module within the switch board.

ntPrimaryRecoveredClock.name: ntPrimaryRecoveredClock
ntPrimaryRecoveredClock.description: The port number on this network module that provides the primary 8KHz reference clock from its received signal.

ntSecondaryRecoveredClock.name: ntSecondaryRecoveredClock
ntSecondaryRecoveredClock.description: The port number on this network module that provides the secondary 8KHz reference clock from its received signal.

ntPrimaryExportClock.name: ntPrimaryExportClock
ntPrimaryExportClock.description: The primary 8KHz clock exported by this network module. The exported clock may be used as the network module global clock, which in turn, may be used by all ports that link their transmit clock to the network module global clock. The noClock option is valid only for tp25 (25mb) netmods.

ntSecondaryExportClock.name: ntSecondaryExportClock
ntSecondaryExportClock.description: The secondary 8KHz clock exported by this network module. The exported clock may be used as the network module global clock. The secondary exported clock will be used if the primary exported clock is not available. The noClock option is valid only for tp25 (25mb) netmods.

ntGlobalClock.name: ntGlobalClock
ntGlobalClock.description: The global 8KHz clock that is available to every port on this network module, when the port links its trasnmit clock to the network module global clock.

ntExportClockOperStatus.name: ntExportClockOperStatus
ntExportClockOperStatus.description: The currently active 8KHz clock configuration. The tertiaryClock(3) is determined by the switch control software if both the primary and secondary clocks are not available.

ntPrimaryImportClock.name: ntPrimaryImportClock
ntPrimaryImportClock.description: The primary 8kHz clock imported by this network module. The imported clock may be used as the network module global clock, which in turn, may be used by all ports that link their transmit clock to the network module global clock.

ntSecondaryImportClock.name: ntSecondaryImportClock
ntSecondaryImportClock.description: The secondary 8kHz clock imported by this network module. The imported clock may be used as the network module global clock. The secondary imported clock will be used if the primary imported clock is not available.

ntImportClockOperStatus.name: ntImportClockOperStatus
ntImportClockOperStatus.description: The currently active 8kHz import clock configuration. The tertiaryClock(3) is determined by the switch control software if both the primary and secondary clocks are not available.

btPrimaryClock.description: The source of the primary 8kHz clock for this board. The clock may be used by each network module in the switch as the network module import clock. The clock may also be used by the management station as the primary or secondary source of the Stratum 3E clock.

btSecondaryClock.name: btSecondaryClock
btSecondaryClock.description: The source of the secondary 8kHz clock. The clock may be used by the management station as the primary or secondary source of the Stratum 3E clock.

btPrimaryClockOperStatus.name: btPrimaryClockOperStatus
btPrimaryClockOperStatus.description: The current state of the 8kHz primary clock.

btSecondaryClockOperStatus.name: btSecondaryClockOperStatus
btSecondaryClockOperStatus.description: The current state of the 8kHz secondary clock.

shmemConfTable.name: shmemConfTable
shmemConfTable.description: A table for shared memory network modules configuration. Implementation of this table is mandatory if at least one of the network modules' hardware is based on shared memory. The user should walk this table and select the shared memory configuration that suits his/her needs. The selection is done in the specific network module shared memory configuration entry (netmodShmemTable).

shmemConfEntry.name: shmemConfEntry
shmemConfEntry.description: A table entry containing shared memory network module configuration information.

shmemConfIndex.name: shmemConfIndex
shmemConfIndex.description: The index of this shared memory configuration.

shmemUcastConnections.name: shmemUcastConnections
shmemUcastConnections.description: The maximum number of unicast connections that is supported by this shared memory configuration.

shmemMcastConnections.name: shmemMcastConnections
shmemMcastConnections.description: The maximum number of multicast connections that is supported by this shared memory configuration.

shmemVpiVciLists.name: shmemVpiVciLists
shmemVpiVciLists.description: The memory allocated for VPI/VCI lists (which is used for multicast connections) by this shared memory configuration.

shmemCellsBuffers.name: shmemCellsBuffers
shmemCellsBuffers.description: The number of cells buffers that is supported by this shared memory configuration.

shmemConfName.name: shmemConfName
shmemConfName.description: The name of this shared memory configuration.

shmemMemorySize.name: shmemMemorySize
shmemMemorySize.description: The size of this shared memory configuration in units of 48 bit words (x48).

netmodShmemTable.name: netmodShmemTable
netmodShmemTable.description: A table for shared memory network modules configuration. Implementation of this table is mandatory if the network module hardware is based on shared memory.

netmodShmemEntry.description: A table entry containing shared memory network module configuration information.

nshmemBoard.description: The index of this board within the ATM switch.

nshmemModule.name: nshmemModule
nshmemModule.description: The number of this network module within the switch board.

nshmemConfRow.description: This object identify the row in the shared memory configuration table that was selected for this network module.

nshmemConfSharedMemory.name: nshmemConfSharedMemory
nshmemConfSharedMemory.description: The amount of memory that was configured for this network module given all the user requirements as specified in the selected shared memory configuration row.

nshmemCurrentUcastConnections.name: nshmemCurrentUcastConnections
nshmemCurrentUcastConnections.description: The current number of unicast connections active on this shared memory network module.

nshmemCurrentMcastConnections.name: nshmemCurrentMcastConnections
nshmemCurrentMcastConnections.description: The current number of multicast connections active on this shared memory network module.

nshmemCurrentVpiVciLists.name: nshmemCurrentVpiVciLists
nshmemCurrentVpiVciLists.description: The current number of VPI/VCI lists active on this shared memory network module.

nshmemCurrentCellsBuffers.name: nshmemCurrentCellsBuffers
nshmemCurrentCellsBuffers.description: The current number cells buffers active on this shared memory network module.

nshmemCurrentSharedMemory.name: nshmemCurrentSharedMemory
nshmemCurrentSharedMemory.description: The current value of the used shared memory on this network module.

nshmemConfAal5PacketDrop.name: nshmemConfAal5PacketDrop
nshmemConfAal5PacketDrop.description: The AAL5 packet drop threshold in percentage of cells. The switch software provides a reasonable default, however, the user may wish to change this value according to the type of traffic and size of packets being transmitted on the network.

nshmemAssertXACPT.name: nshmemAssertXACPT
nshmemAssertXACPT.description: This variable establishes the setting fo the XACPT bit in the fs200sm main control register (section 3.1). This bit determines whether the signal XACPT is asserted whenever the shared memory is full. XACPT prevents the switch from sending cells to the network module. This bit takes advantage of any buffers on the switch to reduce cell loss, but it should not be used if guaranteed cell delay is being provided to high priority cells.

nshmemMemorySize.name: nshmemMemorySize
nshmemMemorySize.description: The size of this Series-C network module's shared memory in units of 48 bit words (x48).

pshmemMaxCDVforCBR.description: The maximum transmitting CDV (Cell Delay Variation) in microseconds for CBR (Constant Bit Rate) / rtVBR (Real-Time Variable Bit Rate) traffic.

The dedicated queue size is determined by the configured maximum CDV (Cell Delay Variation) for CBR/rtVBR (Constant Bit Rate / Real-Time Variable Bit Rate) and nrtVBR (Non-Real-Time Variable Bit Rate) as well as the configurable queue size for ABR (Available Bit Rate) and UBR (Unspecified Bit Rate) traffic.

The user should walk this table and select the shared memory configuration that suits his/her needs. The selection is done in the specific network module shared memory configuration entry (netmodShmemTable).

nShmem3ConfAal5PacketDrop.description: The AAL5 packet drop threshold in number of cells. The switch software provides a reasonable default, however, the user may wish to change this value according to the type of traffic and size of packets being transmitted on the network. Must be between 0 and 32767

nShmem3ConfAal5PacketDropforUBR.name: nShmem3ConfAal5PacketDropforUBR
nShmem3ConfAal5PacketDropforUBR.description: The AAL5 packet drop threshold for UBR traffic in percentage of cells. The switch software provides a reasonable default, however, the user may wish to change this value according to the type of traffic and size of packets being transmitted on the network. Must be between 0 and 32767

nShmem3ConfEfciOn.name: nShmem3ConfEfciOn
nShmem3ConfEfciOn.description: The threshold on which the EFCI (Explicit Forward Congestion Indication) is enabled for UBR (Unspecified Bit Rate) and ABR (Available Bit Rate) traffic. Must be a multiple of 32, greater than or equal to EFCI-off threshold, and less than or equal to 32736.

nShmem3ConfEfciOff.name: nShmem3ConfEfciOff
nShmem3ConfEfciOff.description: The threshold on which the EFCI (Explicit Forward Congestion Indication) is disabled for UBR (Unspecified Bit Rate) and ABR (Available Bit Rate) traffic. Must be a multiple of 32, greater than or equal to 32, and less than or equal to EFCI-on threshold.

nShmem3CellMemorySize.name: nShmem3CellMemorySize
nShmem3CellMemorySize.description: The physical size of this shared memory cell RAM configuration.

nShmem3TableMemorySize.name: nShmem3TableMemorySize
nShmem3TableMemorySize.description: The physical size of this shared memory table RAM configuration.

nShmem3ConfCountPackets.name: nShmem3ConfCountPackets
nShmem3ConfCountPackets.description: Setting this variable to enable(1) causes the network module to count the number of AAL5 packets.

nShmem3ConfAltCLP1Threshold.name: nShmem3ConfAltCLP1Threshold
nShmem3ConfAltCLP1Threshold.description: Alternate CLP=1 threshold for nrt-VBR service class. Must be a multiple of 16, greater than or equal to 0, and less than AltCLP01 threshold.

nShmem3ConfAltCLP01Threshold.name: nShmem3ConfAltCLP01Threshold
nShmem3ConfAltCLP01Threshold.description: Alternate CLP=0+1 threshold for nrt-VBR service class. Must be a multiple of 16, greater than AltCLP1 threshold and less than or equal to 4080.

nShmem3ConfVcCLP1ForCBR.name: nShmem3ConfVcCLP1ForCBR

nShmem3ConfVcCLP01ForCBR.name: nShmem3ConfVcCLP01ForCBR

nShmem3ConfVcCLP1ForVBR.name: nShmem3ConfVcCLP1ForVBR
nShmem3ConfVcCLP1ForVBR.description: Per class CLP=1 threshold for nrt-VBR service class. Must be a multiple of 16, greater than or equal to 0, and less than VcCLP01ForVBR threshold.

nShmem3ConfVcCLP01ForVBR.name: nShmem3ConfVcCLP01ForVBR
nShmem3ConfVcCLP01ForVBR.description: Per class CLP=0+1 threshold for nrt-VBR service class. Must be a multiple of 16, greater than VcCLP1ForVBR threshold, and less than or equal to 4080.

nShmem3ConfVcCLP1ForABR.name: nShmem3ConfVcCLP1ForABR
nShmem3ConfVcCLP1ForABR.description: Per class CLP=1 threshold for ABR service class. Must be a multiple of 16, greater than or equal to 0, and less than VcCLP01ForABR threshold.

nShmem3ConfVcCLP01ForABR.name: nShmem3ConfVcCLP01ForABR
nShmem3ConfVcCLP01ForABR.description: Per class CLP=0+1 threshold for ABR service class. Must be a multiple of 16, greater than VcCLP1ForABR threshold, and less than or equal to 4080.

nShmem3ConfVcCLP1ForUBR.name: nShmem3ConfVcCLP1ForUBR

nShmem3ConfVcCLP01ForUBR.name: nShmem3ConfVcCLP01ForUBR
nShmem3ConfVcCLP01ForUBR.description: Per class CLP=0+1 threshold for UBR service class. Must be a multiple of 16, greater than VcCLP1ForUBR threshold, and less than or equal to 4080.

pShmem3Clp01ThreshforCBR.description: The CLP=0+1 discard threshold in cells for CBR (Constant Bit Rate) / rtVBR (Real-Time Variable Bit Rate) traffic.

pShmem3Clp1ThreshforCBR.name: pShmem3Clp1ThreshforCBR
pShmem3Clp1ThreshforCBR.description: The CLP=1 discard threshold in cells for CBR (Constant Bit Rate) / rtVBR (Real-Time Variable Bit Rate) traffic.

pShmem3Clp01ThreshforVBR.name: pShmem3Clp01ThreshforVBR
pShmem3Clp01ThreshforVBR.description: The CLP=0+1 discard threshold in cells for nrtVBR (Variable Bit Rate) traffic.

pShmem3Clp1ThreshforVBR.name: pShmem3Clp1ThreshforVBR
pShmem3Clp1ThreshforVBR.description: The CLP=1 discard threshold in cells for nrtVBR (Variable Bit Rate) traffic.

pShmem3Clp01ThreshforABR.name: pShmem3Clp01ThreshforABR
pShmem3Clp01ThreshforABR.description: The CLP=0+1 discard threshold in cells for ABR (Available Bit Rate) traffic.

pShmem3Clp1ThreshforABR.name: pShmem3Clp1ThreshforABR
pShmem3Clp1ThreshforABR.description: The CLP=1 discard threshold in cells for ABR (Available Bit Rate) traffic.

pShmem3Clp01ThreshforUBR.description: The CLP=0+1 discard threshold in cells for UBR (Unspecified Bit Rate) traffic.

pShmem3Clp1ThreshforUBR.description: The CLP=1 discard threshold in cells for UBR (Unspecified Bit Rate) traffic.

pShmem3RateLimit.name: pShmem3RateLimit
pShmem3RateLimit.description: The number of cells/second to limit this port. This in effect, sets a new logical line rate for this network module. If set to 0, rate-limiting is disabled. (i.e. full bandwidth is returned to the port).

pShmem3ConfSVCSchedulingCBR.name: pShmem3ConfSVCSchedulingCBR
pShmem3ConfSVCSchedulingCBR.description: This variable defines the scheduling discipline that is going to be used to service all CBR SVC connections that are output across this Series-D port. roundrobin: On Series-D netmod, this means that all CBR SVC's will be served only by one of the two round robin queues. smoothed: On Series-D netmod, this means that all CBR SVC's will be served by the rate controller. guaranteed: On Series-D netmod, this means that all CBR SVC's will be served by both the rate controller and the round robin queues.

pShmem3ConfPVCSchedulingCBR.name: pShmem3ConfPVCSchedulingCBR
pShmem3ConfPVCSchedulingCBR.description: This variable defines the scheduling discipline that is going to be used to service all CBR PVC connections that are output across this port. Series-D netmods support all three scheduling modes. perupc: This means that each individual CBR PVC will be scheduled based on the discipline associated with the UPC contract used to open the connection. roundrobin: This means that each individual CBR PVC will served only by the rate controller. smoothed: On Series-D netmod, this means that all CBR PVC's will be served only by the rate controller. guaranteed: This means that all CBR PVC's will be served by both the rate controller and the round robin queues.

pShmem3ConfSVCSchedulingVBR.name: pShmem3ConfSVCSchedulingVBR
pShmem3ConfSVCSchedulingVBR.description: This variable defines the scheduling discipline that is going to be used to service all VBR SVC connections that are output across this Series-D port. roundrobin: On Series-D netmod, this means that all VBR SVC's will be served only by one of the two round robin queues. smoothed: On Series-D netmod, this means that all VBR SVC's will be served by the rate controller. guaranteed: On Series-D netmod, this means that all VBR SVC's will be served by both the rate controller and the round robin queues.

pShmem3ConfPVCSchedulingVBR.name: pShmem3ConfPVCSchedulingVBR
pShmem3ConfPVCSchedulingVBR.description: This variable defines the scheduling discipline that is going to be used to service all VBR PVC connections that are output across this port. Series-D netmods support all three scheduling modes. perupc: This means that each individual VBR PVC will be scheduled based on the discipline associated with the UPC contract used to open the connection. roundrobin: This means that each individual VBR PVC will served only by the rate controller. smoothed: On Series-D netmod, this means that all VBR PVC's will be served only by the rate controller. guaranteed: This means that all VBR PVC's will be served by both the rate controller and the round robin queues.

pShmem3ConfAltCLPConfigCBR.name: pShmem3ConfAltCLPConfigCBR
pShmem3ConfAltCLPConfigCBR.description: This vairable defines the per-port configuration for the use of the VC level Alternate CLP Thresholdold on CBR/rtVBR connections. The states mean the following: allOn: All CBR/rtVBR connections use the alt CLP threshold. allOff: No CBR/rtVBR connections use the alt CLP threshold. svcOn: All CBR/rtVBR SVC's will use the alt CLP threshold. For CBR/rtVBR PVC's, whether the alt CLP threshold is used is determined by the presence or absence of the 'altCLPthresh' flag in the UPC contract. svcOff: No CBR/rtVBR SVC's will use the alt CLP threshold. For CBR/rtVBR PVC's, whether the alt CLP threshold is used is determined by the presence or absence of the 'altCLPthresh' flag in the UPC contract.

pShmem3ConfAltCLPConfigVBR.name: pShmem3ConfAltCLPConfigVBR
pShmem3ConfAltCLPConfigVBR.description: This vairable defines the per-port configuration for the use of the VC level Alternate CLP Thresholdold on nrtVBR connections. The states mean the following: allOn: All nrtVBR connections use the alt CLP threshold. allOff: No nrtVBR connections use the alt CLP threshold. svcOn: All nrtVBR SVC's will use the alt CLP threshold. For nrtVBR PVC's, whether the alt CLP threshold is used is determined by the presence or absence of the 'altCLPthresh' flag in the UPC contract. svcOff: No nrtVBR SVC's will use the alt CLP threshold. For nrtVBR PVC's, whether the alt CLP threshold is used is determined by the presence or absence of the 'altCLPthresh' flag in the UPC contract.

pShmem3ConfAltCLPConfigUBR.name: pShmem3ConfAltCLPConfigUBR
pShmem3ConfAltCLPConfigUBR.description: This vairable defines the per-port configuration for the use of the VC level Alternate CLP Thresholdold on UBR connections. The states mean the following: allOn: All UBR connections use the alt CLP threshold. allOff: No UBR connections use the alt CLP threshold. svcOn: All UBR SVC's will use the alt CLP threshold. For UBR PVC's, whether the alt CLP threshold is used is determined by the presence or absence of the 'altCLPthresh' flag in the UPC contract. svcOff: No UBR SVC's will use the alt CLP threshold. For UBR PVC's, whether the alt CLP threshold is used is determined by the presence or absence of the 'altCLPthresh' flag in the UPC contract.

vpShmem3UnintentionalLostCells.description: The number of cells on this path that were dropped due to output memory shortages or the CLP (Cell Loss Priority) threshold.

vpShmem3CLP0TxCells.name: vpShmem3CLP0TxCells
vpShmem3CLP0TxCells.description: The number of CLP=0 cells on this path that were transmitted.

vpShmem3CLP1TxCells.name: vpShmem3CLP1TxCells
vpShmem3CLP1TxCells.description: The number of CLP=1 cells on this path that were transmitted.

vpShmem3CLP1LostCells.name: vpShmem3CLP1LostCells
vpShmem3CLP1LostCells.description: The number of cells lost on this path due to CLP=1 threshold.

vpShmem3CLP01LostCells.name: vpShmem3CLP01LostCells
vpShmem3CLP01LostCells.description: The number of cells lost on this path due to CLP=0+1 threshold.

vpShmem3CurrentQsize.name: vpShmem3CurrentQsize
vpShmem3CurrentQsize.description: The current size of the queue.

netmodGenericShmemTable.name: netmodGenericShmemTable
netmodGenericShmemTable.description: A table for simple network modules. Implementation of this table is optional.

netmodGenericShmemEntry.name: netmodGenericShmemEntry
netmodGenericShmemEntry.description: A table entry containing simple network module configuration information

nGenericShmemBoard.name: nGenericShmemBoard
nGenericShmemBoard.description: The index of this board within the ATM switch.

nGenericShmemModule.name: nGenericShmemModule
nGenericShmemModule.description: The number of this network module within the switch board.

nGenericShmemSubindex.name: nGenericShmemSubindex
nGenericShmemSubindex.description: The subindex of this generic shmem within the network module.

nGenericShmemCurrentUcastConnections.name: nGenericShmemCurrentUcastConnections
nGenericShmemCurrentUcastConnections.description: The current number of unicast connections active on this network module. If a separate unicast connection space is not supported, this value will be -1.

nGenericShmemCurrentMcastConnections.name: nGenericShmemCurrentMcastConnections
nGenericShmemCurrentMcastConnections.description: The current number of multicast connections active on this network module. If a separate multicast connection space is not supported, this value will be -1.

nGenericShmemCurrentConnections.name: nGenericShmemCurrentConnections
nGenericShmemCurrentConnections.description: The current number of connections (either multicast or unicast) active on this network module.

nGenericShmemMaxUcastConnections.name: nGenericShmemMaxUcastConnections
nGenericShmemMaxUcastConnections.description: The total number of unicast connections that this network module can support. If a separate unicast connection space is not supported, this value will be -1. The largest possible number of ATM connections can be 2^28 - 1 (i.e., 268435455) since VPI and VCI fields in the ATM cell header occupies a total of 28 bits (12 bits of VPI and 16 bits of VCI). Any value greater than 2^28 - 1 for this MIB will indicate that this network module can support an unlimited number of unicast connections.

nGenericShmemMaxMcastConnections.name: nGenericShmemMaxMcastConnections
nGenericShmemMaxMcastConnections.description: The total number of multicast connections that this network module can support. If a separate multicast connection space is not supported, this value will be -1. The largest possible number of ATM connections can be 2^28 - 1 (i.e., 268435455) since VPI and VCI fields in the ATM cell header occupies a total of 28 bits (12 bits of VPI and 16 bits of VCI). Any value greater than 2^28 - 1 for this MIB will indicate that this network module can support an unlimited number of multicast connections.

nGenericShmemMaxConnections.name: nGenericShmemMaxConnections
nGenericShmemMaxConnections.description: The total number of connections (either multicast or unicast) that this network module can support. The largest possible number of ATM connections can be 2^28 - 1 (i.e., 268435455) since VPI and VCI fields in the ATM cell header occupies a total of 28 bits (12 bits of VPI and 16 bits of VCI). Any value greater than 2^28 - 1 for this MIB will indicate that this network module can support an unlimited number of connections.

netmodGenericShmemCustomBCSTable.name: netmodGenericShmemCustomBCSTable
netmodGenericShmemCustomBCSTable.description: A table for shared memory custom BCS mappings

netmodGenericShmemCustomBCSEntry.name: netmodGenericShmemCustomBCSEntry
netmodGenericShmemCustomBCSEntry.description: A table entry containing shared memory custom BCS mappings

nGenericShmemCustomBCSBoard.name: nGenericShmemCustomBCSBoard
nGenericShmemCustomBCSBoard.description: The index of this board within the ATM switch.

nGenericShmemCustomBCSModule.name: nGenericShmemCustomBCSModule
nGenericShmemCustomBCSModule.description: The number of this network module within the switch board.

nGenericShmemCustomBCSSubindex.name: nGenericShmemCustomBCSSubindex
nGenericShmemCustomBCSSubindex.description: The subindex of this generic shmem within the network module.

nGenericShmemCustomBCSWeight.name: nGenericShmemCustomBCSWeight
nGenericShmemCustomBCSWeight.description: The weight assigned to this BCS

dualScpConfTable.name: dualScpConfTable
dualScpConfTable.description: A table for current state of dual SCP configuration.

dualScpConfEntry.name: dualScpConfEntry
dualScpConfEntry.description: A table entry containing current dual SCP configuration.

dualScpSlot.name: dualScpSlot
dualScpSlot.description: The slot number for this SCP.

dualScpState.name: dualScpState
dualScpState.description: Shows whether the switch is operating with a single or dual SCPs. The value other(3) denotes that both SCPs are present but communication is not yet established.

dualScpSyncState.name: dualScpSyncState
dualScpSyncState.description: This variable contains the current state of synchronization.

dualScpPrimary.name: dualScpPrimary
dualScpPrimary.description: Controls which SCP is designated as the primary SCP.

dualScpFailover.name: dualScpFailover
dualScpFailover.description: Disables the dual SCP failover mechanism. When set to disable(2), the backup SCP will not take over if the main SCP goes down.

dualScpManualSyncRequest.name: dualScpManualSyncRequest
dualScpManualSyncRequest.description: This variable can be used to manually synchronize the entire flash or any of the specified files. syncIdle(1) - No synchronization. syncFlash(2) - Synchronize the entire flash. syncCdb(3) - Synchronize the CDB file. syncPassword(4) - Synchronize the password file (depracated). syncLecsConfig(5) - Synchronize the LECS configuration file. syncOS(6) - Synchronize the OS. syncInit(7) - Reformat the entire flash. syncSecurid(8) - Synchronize the securid configuration file. syncSecret(9) - Synchronize the securid node secret file. syncLoader(10) - Synchronize the mini-loader. syncKrb5KeyTab(12)- Synchronize the kerberos v5srvtab file.

dualScpCdbSyncMode.name: dualScpCdbSyncMode
dualScpCdbSyncMode.description: Controls whether CDB synchronization will be manual or automatic.

dualScpManualSwitchOver.name: dualScpManualSwitchOver
dualScpManualSwitchOver.description: Forces the backup SCP to take switch control from the main SCP.

dualScpSwitchOverTime.name: dualScpSwitchOverTime
dualScpSwitchOverTime.description: Show the time when switch over occurred.

dualScpSwitchOverThreshold.name: dualScpSwitchOverThreshold
dualScpSwitchOverThreshold.description: Amount of time the standby SCP will wait after loss of active SCP's heartbeat before it takes control of the switch. The valid range is 2-300 seconds.

dualScpSyncRequestList.name: dualScpSyncRequestList
dualScpSyncRequestList.description: The current list of items that are waiting to be synchronized. This is a bit pattern containing the specified enumurated bits. The bit definitions are: 0x02 -- syncFlash 0x04 -- syncCdb 0x08 -- syncPassword 0x10 -- syncLecsConfig 0x20 -- syncOS 0x40 -- syncInit 0x80 -- syncSecurid 0x100 -- syncSecret 0x200 -- syncLoader 0x800 -- syncKrb5KeyTab

dualScpNumSyncRequests.name: dualScpNumSyncRequests
dualScpNumSyncRequests.description: The number of synchronization requests since this agent was initialized.

dualScpNumSyncFailures.name: dualScpNumSyncFailures
dualScpNumSyncFailures.description: The number of synchronization failures since this agent was initialized.

dualScpResetStandbyScp.name: dualScpResetStandbyScp
dualScpResetStandbyScp.description: Setting this variable to enable(1) resets the backup SCP forcing it to start over.

dualScpAutoRemoveOldFiles.name: dualScpAutoRemoveOldFiles
dualScpAutoRemoveOldFiles.description: Setting this variable to enable(1) instructs the backup SCP to remove old files during file synchronization in order to make room for the files that are being synchronized. This usually removes older copies of OS files. When synchronizing the OS, the current version of the OS will be removed if there isn't sufficient space for the new OS being synchronized.

dualScpRedundancyState.name: dualScpRedundancyState
dualScpRedundancyState.description: This variable contains the current state of Dual SCP Redundancy.

dualScpSVXCPStateSyncPercent.name: dualScpSVXCPStateSyncPercent
dualScpSVXCPStateSyncPercent.description: When SVx/SPVx Preservation is enabled, call state information will be transferred from the Active SCP to the Standby SCP, prior to any SCP control transfer. This MIB variable tracks the completion percentage of the information transfer. Before SCP control transfer occurs, the user can query this variable to find out how much of the information transfer has been done.

dualScpSVXCPStateTransferFailed.name: dualScpSVXCPStateTransferFailed
dualScpSVXCPStateTransferFailed.description: When SVx/SPVx Preservation is enabled, call state information will be transferred from the Active SCP to the Standby SCP. The value returned is 'Failed' for any failure in this transfer, 'OK' otherwise.

dualScpSVXCPdroppedCallCount.name: dualScpSVXCPdroppedCallCount
dualScpSVXCPdroppedCallCount.description: SVx/SPVx Preservation has failed to preserve zero or more calls, whose number is given here.

genericPortGroupConfTable.name: genericPortGroupConfTable
genericPortGroupConfTable.description: A table for simple network modules. Implementation of this table is optional.

genericPortGroupConfEntry.name: genericPortGroupConfEntry
genericPortGroupConfEntry.description: A table entry containing simple network module configuration information

genericPortGroupBoard.name: genericPortGroupBoard
genericPortGroupBoard.description: The index of this board within the ATM switch.

genericPortGroupIndex.name: genericPortGroupIndex
genericPortGroupIndex.description: The number of this port group(module) within a switch board. This is the number that identifies the port group within a switch board.

genericPortGroupSubindex.name: genericPortGroupSubindex
genericPortGroupSubindex.description: The subindex of this port group identifying a port within this port group.

genericPortGroupAal5PacketDrop.name: genericPortGroupAal5PacketDrop
genericPortGroupAal5PacketDrop.description: The AAL5 packet drop threshold in percentage of cells. The switch software provides a reasonable default, however, the user may wish to change this value according to the type of traffic and size of packets being transmitted on the network.

genericPortGroupEfciOn.name: genericPortGroupEfciOn
genericPortGroupEfciOn.description: The threshold at which the EFCI (Explicit Forward Congestion Indication) bit is turned on for ABR (Available Bit Rate) traffic.

genericPortGroupEfciOff.name: genericPortGroupEfciOff
genericPortGroupEfciOff.description: The threshold at which the EFCI (Explicit Forward Congestion Indication) bit is turned off for ABR (Available Bit Rate) traffic.

genericPortGroupPrioName.name: genericPortGroupPrioName
genericPortGroupPrioName.description: The priority name (CBR, VBR, ABR, UBR) for this priority index.

genericOutputPortConfTable.name: genericOutputPortConfTable
genericOutputPortConfTable.description: A table for managing the configurable items for a port in a generic manner. Implementation of this table is optional.

genericOutputPortConfEntry.name: genericOutputPortConfEntry
genericOutputPortConfEntry.description: A table entry containing generic port configuration information

genericOutputPortConfBoard.name: genericOutputPortConfBoard
genericOutputPortConfBoard.description: The index of this board within the ATM switch

genericOutputPortConfModule.name: genericOutputPortConfModule
genericOutputPortConfModule.description: The number of this port group within the switch board.

genericOutputPortConfPort.name: genericOutputPortConfPort
genericOutputPortConfPort.description: The number identifies the port within a switch board and a port group.

genericOutputPortConfPrio.name: genericOutputPortConfPrio
genericOutputPortConfPrio.description: The priority on the output port.

genericOutputPortConfPrioDedicatedQSize.name: genericOutputPortConfPrioDedicatedQSize
genericOutputPortConfPrioDedicatedQSize.description: The dedicated (minimum) queue size, in cells for this pport and priority

genericOutputPortConfPrioClp1Threshold.name: genericOutputPortConfPrioClp1Threshold
genericOutputPortConfPrioClp1Threshold.description: The CLP=1 discard threshold, in cells for this port and priority.

genericOutputPortConfPrioClp01Threshold.name: genericOutputPortConfPrioClp01Threshold
genericOutputPortConfPrioClp01Threshold.description: The CLP=0+1 discard threshold, in cells for this port and priority.

genericOutputPortConfPrioName.name: genericOutputPortConfPrioName
genericOutputPortConfPrioName.description: The priority name (CBR, VBR, ABR, UBR) for this genericOutputPortIndex on this port.

genericOutputPortConfAtmif.name: genericOutputPortConfAtmif
genericOutputPortConfAtmif.description: The AtmIf(BNP) of this shmem within the ATM switch

genericOutputPortStatsTable.name: genericOutputPortStatsTable
genericOutputPortStatsTable.description: A table for managing Statistics information about the current state of a port in a generic manner. Implementation of this table is optional.

genericOutputPortStatsEntry.name: genericOutputPortStatsEntry
genericOutputPortStatsEntry.description: A table entry containing generic port configuration information

genericOutputPortStatsBoard.name: genericOutputPortStatsBoard
genericOutputPortStatsBoard.description: The index of this board within the ATM switch.

genericOutputPortStatsModule.name: genericOutputPortStatsModule
genericOutputPortStatsModule.description: The number of this port group within the switch board.

genericOutputPortStatsPort.name: genericOutputPortStatsPort
genericOutputPortStatsPort.description: The number of this port within the switch board and the port group.

genericOutputPortStatsPrioTransmittedCel.name: genericOutputPortStatsPrioTransmittedCells
genericOutputPortStatsPrioTransmittedCel.description: The number of cells transmitted on this port for this priority

genericOutputPortStatsPrioClp1LostCells.name: genericOutputPortStatsPrioClp1LostCells
genericOutputPortStatsPrioClp1LostCells.description: The number of cells lost on this port for this priority due to CLP=1 threshold.

genericOutputPortStatsPrioClp01LostCells.name: genericOutputPortStatsPrioClp01LostCells
genericOutputPortStatsPrioClp01LostCells.description: The number of cells lost on this port for this priority due to CLP=0+1 threshold.

genericOutputPortStatsPrioName.name: genericOutputPortStatsPrioName
genericOutputPortStatsPrioName.description: The priority name (CBR, VBR, ABR, UBR) for this genericOutputPortIndex on this port.

genericOutputPortStatsAtmif.name: genericOutputPortStatsAtmif
genericOutputPortStatsAtmif.description: The index of Atmif associated with this shmem in the ATM switch.

genericOutputPortStatsPrioEpdPpdLostCell.name: genericOutputPortStatsPrioEpdPpdLostCells
genericOutputPortStatsPrioEpdPpdLostCell.description: The number of cells lost on this port for this priority due to EPD/PPD threshold.

hardwareVersion.name: hardwareVersion
hardwareVersion.description: The version of the ATM switch hardware in hex. The version number 0x1 is revision A, 0x2 is revision B etc. Version number 0x0 represents an unknown type.

softwareVersion.name: softwareVersion
softwareVersion.description: The version of the ATM switch control software in hex. The version number is encoded into 6 hex digits. For example, version 1.2.3 is encoded as 0x010203.

maxPaths.name: maxPaths
maxPaths.description: The maximum number of input VPIs (Virtual Path Identifies).

maxChannels.name: maxChannels
maxChannels.description: The maximum number of input VCIs (Virtual Channel Identifiers).

atmAddress.name: atmAddress
atmAddress.description: The address of this ATM switch.

uptime.name: uptime
uptime.description: The length of time this ATM switch has been up, in hundredths of a second.

switchCDV.name: switchCDV
switchCDV.description: The switch Cell Delay Variation (CDV) specified in microseconds, indicates the time window in which a cell may be received on a connection and be accepted. A cell that is received on a connection outside the CDV window will be tagged or dropped as indicated by the switchPolicingAction object. The switchCDV is the default CDV for all the connections on this switch. Individual connections can be set to explicitly override this value.

switchPolicingAction.name: switchPolicingAction
switchPolicingAction.description: This object indicates the action the switch will take in case of bandwidth violation. The switchPolicingAction is the default policing action for all the connections on this switch. Individual connections can be set to explicitly override this default action.

softwareVersionText.name: softwareVersionText
softwareVersionText.description: The version of the ATM switch control software. This object provides text information about the internal software configuration that was used when the switch control software was built.

switchType.name: switchType
switchType.description: This object identifies the switch type.

switchReservedPMPMinVCI.name: switchReservedPMPMinVCI
switchReservedPMPMinVCI.description: The minimum VCI that is reserved for PMP connections.

switchReservedPMPMaxVCI.name: switchReservedPMPMaxVCI
switchReservedPMPMaxVCI.description: The maximum VCI that is reserved for PMP connections.

switchTimeZone.name: switchTimeZone
switchTimeZone.description: The TimeZone configured for this ATM switch. This variable follows the POSIX standard 1003.1-1988 for the format of the TZ environment variable. In particular, it is general enough to specify the rules for converting from Standard to Daylight Savings time for most timezones of the world. By default, the switch has the rules built in for the following timezones: EST5EDT CST6CDT MST7MDT PST8PDT AKST9AKDT. Locales outside of these timezones will need to supply the appropriate rule for switching between Daylight and Standard time.

switchGMTime.name: switchGMTime
switchGMTime.description: The switch's notion of Greenwich Mean Time. Linked to hrSystemDate. Offset part of time spec, if supplied, is considered an error.

switchProtocolType.name: switchProtocolType
switchProtocolType.description: The transfer protocol that is used when upgrading the switch software, backing up the CDB, etc.

switchCurrentUserid.name: switchCurrentUserid
switchCurrentUserid.description: The value of this object identifies the user currently logged in or attempting to log in on the switch. It would be a NULL string if no one is logged in currently.

switchCurrentLoginFrom.name: switchCurrentLoginFrom
switchCurrentLoginFrom.description: This string gives the IP address of the host from where the current user is logged in or attempting to log in. A NULL string is returned if no one is currently logged in on the switch. If its a serial port login, the string indicates the same

switchPrimaryClock.name: switchPrimaryClock
switchPrimaryClock.description: The port number whose 8KHz clock is used as primary clock by all the netmods on all the boards in this switch.

switchSecondaryClock.name: switchSecondaryClock
switchSecondaryClock.description: The port number whose 8KHz clock is used as secondary clock by all the netmods on all the boards in this switch.

switchClockOperStatus.name: switchClockOperStatus
switchClockOperStatus.description: The currently active 8KHz clock configuration. The crystal?Clock types are not currently used. The default mode is localCrystalClock which means each netmod runs off of its own crystal. If primary, secondary or tcm clocking is configured then the status will be updated by switch software accordingly.

switchTimingMode.name: switchTimingMode
switchTimingMode.description: The timing mode in which the switch is running. switchMode(1) provides for the direct use of any port recovered clock from any timing-capable network module in the switch. tcmMode(3) uses the clock provided by the CEC-Plus' Timing Control Modules (TCM).

switchConnectionPreservation.name: switchConnectionPreservation
switchConnectionPreservation.description: When connection preservation is enabled the switch will not reset the hardware when a fail-over or software-reboot occurs. The software will preserve existing PVC connections and re-create other connections. This prevents cell traffic on PVC connections from being disrupted during the fail-over / software-reboot process. When connection preservation is disabled the switch will reset the hardware when a fail-over or software-reboot occurs. All connections will then be re-created. Cell traffic on all connections will be disrupted during the fail-over / software-reboot process. This is disabled by default on all asx200bx based switches. On all the other platforms, this is enabled by default.

switchATMLayerOAM.name: switchATMLayerOAM
switchATMLayerOAM.description: This object specifies whether the processing of ATM layer OAM cells by this switch is enabled or disabled.

switchHttpServer.name: switchHttpServer
switchHttpServer.description: This specifies whether the embedded HTTP Server (which is used for the element manager) is enabled or disabled.

switchHttpHelpUrl.name: switchHttpHelpUrl
switchHttpHelpUrl.description: This specifies the URL path for the local depository of the WWW help pages for the web-based element manager on the switch. The URL is in the form: <ipaddress>[:port][<pathname>] For example: 1.2.3.4:8000/usr/fore/www This includes the IP address host to contact, and optionally the port on that host, and the directory on that host where the help pages were saved. If an empty string, the switch will use a default location on FORE's external web site.

switchCtrlLinkid.name: switchCtrlLinkid
switchCtrlLinkid.description: The linkid of the ctrl port on this switch.

switchClockCurrentStatus.name: switchClockCurrentStatus
switchClockCurrentStatus.description: The currently active 8KHz clock configuration. The value would indicate primary Clock or secondary Clock or if neither is available a <netmod> crystal Clock is determined by the switch control software. The software chooses the lowest netmod number with timing support

softwareLicenseKey.name: softwareLicenseKey
softwareLicenseKey.description: The software license key of this switch.

switchCounterResetTime.name: switchCounterResetTime
switchCounterResetTime.description: Indicates when all switch (except for virtual connection) counters were reset. The TimeStamp is equal to the sysUpTime when the reset occurred. If switch counters have never been reset, the switchCounterResetTime will be zero. This variable is updated whenever switchCounterReset is written.

switchCounterReset.name: switchCounterReset
switchCounterReset.description: Writing a value of resetRequest will result in a reset of all counters on the switch except for VCC indexed counters. Writing a value of unresetRequest will destroy all counter offsets and restore counter values to what has accumulated over the sysUpTime period. A response value of resetTrue indicates a resetRequest succeeded and is in effect. A response of resetFalse indicates a reset is not currently in effect.

switchPrimaryClockPort.name: switchPrimaryClockPort
switchPrimaryClockPort.description: The name of the hardware port whose 8KHz clock is used as primary clock by all the netmods on all the boards in this switch.

switchSecondaryClockPort.name: switchSecondaryClockPort
switchSecondaryClockPort.description: The name of the hardware port whose 8KHz clock is used as secondary clock by all the netmods on all the boards in this switch.

switchPmpEnable.name: switchPmpEnable
switchPmpEnable.description: Disabling the PMP Feature disallows any point to multipoint connections. The services which require point to multi point connections also need to be disabled. By default the feature is enabled.

switchCallPreservation.name: switchCallPreservation
switchCallPreservation.description: When SVx/SPVx Preservation is enabled, existing switched connections will be preserved during transfers of switch control from the Active SCP to the Standby SCP, whether user-initiated or due to SCP failure. Cell traffic is preserved during the failover/switchover process. When SVx/SPVx Preservation is disabled, and if Connection Preservation also is disabled, control transfers from the Active SCP to the Standby SCP will reset the switch hardware without having preserved the necessary call-state information. Hence, all switched connections will be cleared and will then have to be recreated. Cell traffic on all switched connections will be disrupted. By default, this feature is disabled on all supported dual-scp platforms.

switchCallPresOperStatus.name: switchCallPresOperStatus
switchCallPresOperStatus.description: When SVx/SPVx Preservation is enabled administratively, the feature nevertheless may be disabled operationally (e.g., because of hardware failures, like a missing Standby SCP). When it is operationally disabled, the effect is as though SVx/SPVx Preservation were disabled administratively.

switchDebounceTable.name: switchDebounceTable
switchDebounceTable.description: A table, where each entry consists of debounce information associated with a unique port. This information includes the hysteresis value (a positive number in ms) for that port, i.e, the number of ms for which a physical-level failure persists for that port, after which the connection will be brought down

switchDebounceEntry.name: switchDebounceEntry
switchDebounceEntry.description: A table entry containing physical interface debounce information.

switchDebounceIndex.name: switchDebounceIndex
switchDebounceIndex.description: The index value for this entry - ties in with a unique port

switchDebounceName.name: switchDebounceName
switchDebounceName.description: The persistent name of this interface - (the port name)

switchDebounceHysteresis.name: switchDebounceHysteresis
switchDebounceHysteresis.description: The hysteresis value for this interface. The hysteresis value is the number of ms for which a physical-level failure persists for that interface, after which the connection will be brought down

mcastSpaceTable.name: mcastSpaceTable
mcastSpaceTable.description: A table containing information on number of multicast connections supported on this switch.

mcastSpaceEntry.name: mcastSpaceEntry
mcastSpaceEntry.description: A table entry containing multicast space information

mcastSpaceIndex.name: mcastSpaceIndex
mcastSpaceIndex.description: Index of this multicast space entry. This value is used to set boardMcastIndex value.

mcastSpaceNumConn.name: mcastSpaceNumConn
mcastSpaceNumConn.description: Number of multicast connections that this entry represents. When boardMcastIndex is set to mcastSpaceIndex value, the corresponding board will support mcastSpaceNumConn number of multicast connections.

mcastSpaceName.name: mcastSpaceName
mcastSpaceName.description: Name of this multicast space entry.

switchSbprServerAddressTable.name: switchSbprServerAddressTable
switchSbprServerAddressTable.description: A table, where each entry consists of a static list of 5 bootp address entries.

switchSbprServerAddressEntry.name: switchSbprServerAddressEntry
switchSbprServerAddressEntry.description: A bootp Ip Address server entry.

sbprServerAddressIndex.name: sbprServerAddressIndex
sbprServerAddressIndex.description: A unique value greater then zero used as an index into the bootp address table.

sbprServerAddressIndexName.name: sbprServerAddressIndexName
sbprServerAddressIndexName.description: Name of the Interface index into the bootp address table.

sbprServerMaxHops.name: sbprServerMaxHops
sbprServerMaxHops.description: The maximum number of hops that a BOOTREQUEST message is permitted to traverse before it must be discarded. Received BOOTREQUEST messages that have a hopcount greater than this value are discarded by this relay agent. The default value is 4.

sbprServerMinSeconds.name: sbprServerMinSeconds
sbprServerMinSeconds.description: The minimum number of seconds that a BOOTP client must have been attempting to boot before the relay agent will relay BOOTREQUESTs from that client. The default value is 0.

sbprServerAddress1.name: sbprServerAddress1
sbprServerAddress1.description: The IP address of the BOOTP server.

sbprServerAddress2.name: sbprServerAddress2
sbprServerAddress2.description: The IP address of the BOOTP server.

sbprServerAddress3.name: sbprServerAddress3
sbprServerAddress3.description: The IP address of the BOOTP server.

sbprServerAddress4.name: sbprServerAddress4
sbprServerAddress4.description: The IP address of the BOOTP server.

sbprServerAddress5.name: sbprServerAddress5
sbprServerAddress5.description: The IP address of the BOOTP server.

serviceCategoryTable.name: serviceCategoryTable
serviceCategoryTable.description: A table of ATM service categories supported.

serviceCategoryEntry.name: serviceCategoryEntry
serviceCategoryEntry.description: A table entry containing ATM Service Category information.

serviceCategoryName.name: serviceCategoryName
serviceCategoryName.description: The name of the ATM service category. The following values are supported: serviceCategoryIndex serviceCategoryName ----------------- ---------------------- 1 CBR 2 rtVBR 3 nrtVBR 4 ABR 5 UBR

confTopoHelloInterval.name: confTopoHelloInterval
confTopoHelloInterval.description: This is the time interval in milli seconds between successive Hello Indication messages sent by SPANS

confTopoNsapIndInterval.name: confTopoNsapIndInterval
confTopoNsapIndInterval.description: This is the time interval in milli seconds between successive NSAP Indication messages sent by SPANS

confTopoStaticUpdateInterval.name: confTopoStaticUpdateInterval
confTopoStaticUpdateInterval.description: This is the time interval in milli seconds between successive refreshes of NSAP static routes in the NSAP topology

confTopoMaxHopCount.name: confTopoMaxHopCount
confTopoMaxHopCount.description: This is the upper limit on the number of hops in the source routes computed by the NSAP router

confTopoACRPropMult.name: confTopoACRPropMult
confTopoACRPropMult.description: This is the proportional multiplier expressed as a percentage of Available Cell Rate (ACR). If the percentage change of the ACR of any given link in the NSAP topology exceeds this threshold, then the change is deemed significant

confTopoMinThresh.name: confTopoMinThresh
confTopoMinThresh.description: This is the capacity value in Cells per second of the minimum value that the threshold value for determining the significant change can take. This minimum value is used to ensure that the threshold for determining significant changes to ACR does not become a very small value in cases where product of the ACR and the proportional multiplier is a very small number.

confTopoMinVCAvail.name: confTopoMinVCAvail
confTopoMinVCAvail.description: This is the minimum number of VCs that should be available on a link before the state of the link changes from VCs-not- available to VCs-available. This state is propagated in the link state information. The state changes from VCs-available to VCs-not-available when the number of VCs available becomes zero from a non-zero value.

confTopoSpansAreaID.name: confTopoSpansAreaID
confTopoSpansAreaID.description: This is the ID of the Area in the SPANS routing hierarchy to which this switch belongs. This number goes into the most significant byte of the SPANS ATM address

confTopoSpansBorderSwitch.name: confTopoSpansBorderSwitch
confTopoSpansBorderSwitch.description: This variable indicates wherher this switch is configured to operate as a SPANS-NNI Border Switch or not

confTopoSwitchPrefix.name: confTopoSwitchPrefix
confTopoSwitchPrefix.description: The default NSAP (Network Service Access Point) prefix for this ATM switch. The NSAP prefix will be used in the ILMI address registration message as well as the 'hello-indication' SPANS-NNI message.

confTopoSwitchPrefixMask.name: confTopoSwitchPrefixMask
