confTopoSwitchPrefixMask.description: This mask gives the number of leading bits in the above prefix to be used to aggregate the addresses that belong to the switch in SPANS-PNNI alias FORE-PNNI

confTopoPeerGroupMask.name: confTopoPeerGroupMask
confTopoPeerGroupMask.description: This mask gives the number of the leading bits in the above prefix to be used to aggregate the addresses that belong to the peer group containing this switch in SPANS-PNNI alias FORE-PNNI

confTopoSpansPnniBorderSwitch.name: confTopoSpansPnniBorderSwitch
confTopoSpansPnniBorderSwitch.description: This variable indicates whether this switch is configured to operate as a SPANS-PNNI Border Switch or not

confTopoPGSNReachCost.name: confTopoPGSNReachCost
confTopoPGSNReachCost.description: This is used to indicate cost of link from border node to PGSN

confTopoPGSNReachCostMethod.name: confTopoPGSNReachCostMethod
confTopoPGSNReachCostMethod.description: This variable indicates the method of computing cost of link from border node to PGSN

confTopoFtPnniForeArea.name: confTopoFtPnniForeArea
confTopoFtPnniForeArea.description: This variable is the area ID of the FT-PNNI autonomous system in the global fore hierarchy of PNNI and FT-PNNI peergroups

confTopoFtPnniForeLevel.name: confTopoFtPnniForeLevel
confTopoFtPnniForeLevel.description: This variable is the level of the FT-PNNI autonomous system in the global fore hierarchy of PNNI and FT-PNNI peergroups

confTopoLBUbrLoadBalance.name: confTopoLBUbrLoadBalance
confTopoLBUbrLoadBalance.description: This variable indicates whether this switch is to do Load Balanced UBR routing

numberOfPorts.name: numberOfPorts
numberOfPorts.description: The number of ports on this ATM switch.

portTable.name: portTable
portTable.description: A table of information about the ports on this ATM switch.

portEntry.name: portEntry
portEntry.description: A table entry containing port information.

portNumber.name: portNumber
portNumber.description: The value of this object identifies the port.

portAdminStatus.name: portAdminStatus
portAdminStatus.description: The desired state of this port. The up(3) state indicates that SPANS (Simple Protocol for ATM Network Signalling), FORE's link signalling protocol, is used to determine the operational status of the port. The down(2) state dictates that the operational status of the port should not be determined by SPANS.

portOperStatus.name: portOperStatus
portOperStatus.description: The current operational state of this port, as determined either by administrative action, when the value of portAdminStatus is down(2), or by SPANS (Simple Protocol for ATM Network Signalling), FORE's link signalling protocol, when the value of porAdminStatus is up(3). For FRAM netmod, it is equivalent to the ifOperStatus of the same port

portTime.name: portTime
portTime.description: The length of time this port has been in its current state, in hundredths of a second.

portRemoteAtmAddress.name: portRemoteAtmAddress
portRemoteAtmAddress.description: The ATM address of the entity connected to this port.

portRemoteIpAddress.name: portRemoteIpAddress
portRemoteIpAddress.description: The IP address of the entity connected to this port.

portMaxPathsIn.name: portMaxPathsIn
portMaxPathsIn.description: The maximum number of incoming virtual paths supported by this port.

portNumPathsIn.name: portNumPathsIn
portNumPathsIn.description: The number of incoming virtual paths on this port.

portMaxBandwidthIn.name: portMaxBandwidthIn
portMaxBandwidthIn.description: The maximum incoming bandwidth of this port, in cells per second.

portAllocBandwidthIn.name: portAllocBandwidthIn
portAllocBandwidthIn.description: The allocated incoming bandwidth of this port, in cells per second.

portUsedBandwidthIn.name: portUsedBandwidthIn
portUsedBandwidthIn.description: The incoming bandwidth being used on this port, in cells per second.

portReceivedCells.name: portReceivedCells
portReceivedCells.description: The number of cells received on this port.

portMaxPathsOut.name: portMaxPathsOut
portMaxPathsOut.description: The maximum number of outgoing virtual paths supported by this port.

portNumPathsOut.name: portNumPathsOut
portNumPathsOut.description: The number of outgoing virtual paths on this port.

portMaxBandwidthOut.name: portMaxBandwidthOut
portMaxBandwidthOut.description: The maximum outgoing bandwidth of this port, in cells per second.

portAllocBandwidthOut.name: portAllocBandwidthOut
portAllocBandwidthOut.description: The allocated outgoing bandwidth of this port, in cells per second.

portUsedBandwidthOut.name: portUsedBandwidthOut
portUsedBandwidthOut.description: The outgoing bandwidth being used on this port, in cells per second.

portTransmittedCells.name: portTransmittedCells
portTransmittedCells.description: The number of cells transmitted on this port.

portHwBoard.name: portHwBoard
portHwBoard.description: The hardware board number of this port.

portHwModule.name: portHwModule
portHwModule.description: The hardware module number of this port. For a control port (a software port), the value of this object is the maximun number of hardware modules plus one.

portHwNumber.name: portHwNumber
portHwNumber.description: The hardware port number of this port. For a control port (a software port), the value of this object is 0.

portILMIRemoteIpAddress.name: portILMIRemoteIpAddress
portILMIRemoteIpAddress.description: The IP address of the entity connected to this port that was discovered using ILMI on path 0. If there is no q2931 siganlling path on VPI 0 that uses ILMI, the value of this object is 255.255.255.255.

portCDVT.name: portCDVT
portCDVT.description: The Cell Delay Variation Tolerance associated with this physical port. Connections take their default value for CDVT from the input side port.

portInputPolicingStatus.name: portInputPolicingStatus
portInputPolicingStatus.description: The state of policing on this input port. Enabled(1) forces every connection on this input port to be policed. Disabled(2) turns policing off for every connection on this input port. The functions of this variable have been subsumed by the new GCRAPolicingCBR and GCRAPolicingVBR variables below. Now, writing 'disabled' to this MIB variable has the effect of setting GCRAPolicingCBR=allOff and GCRAPolicingVBR=allOff. On read, this variable reports 'enabled', if either of the GCRAPolicing*BR options are in an 'On' setting. Use of this variable should be avoided, in favor of the two GCRA variables.

portVbrOverbooking.name: portVbrOverbooking
portVbrOverbooking.description: The percentage of overbooking for nrtVBR connections. The default value is 100 (no overbooking).

portVbrBufferOverb.name: portVbrBufferOverb
portVbrBufferOverb.description: The percentage of buffer overbooking for nrtVBR connections. The default value is 100 (no overbooking).

portManagementStatus.name: portManagementStatus
portManagementStatus.description: The visibility of this port in the management station's view. The default value is 1 (managed).

portAISRDIGeneration.name: portAISRDIGeneration
portAISRDIGeneration.description: The port ATM layer AIS and RDI generation status.

portGCRAPolicingCBR.name: portGCRAPolicingCBR
portGCRAPolicingCBR.description: This variable defines the per-port policing configuration for CBR connections. The states mean the following: allOn: ALL CBR connections arriving on this port will be subjected to GCRA policing. allOff: NO CBR connections arriving on this port will be subjected to GCRA policing. svcOn: ALL CRB SVCs arriving on this port will be subjected to GCRA policing svcOff: NO CBR SVCs arriving on this port will be subjected to GCRA policing. CBR PVCs will be GCRA policed based on the state of their UPC contract. default: ALL CBR UNI SVCs/SVPs arriving at this port will be subject to GCRA policing and NO CBR NNI SVCs/SVPs arriving at this port will be subject to GCRA policing. CBR PVCs/PVPs arriving at this port will be policed based on the state of their UPC contract.

portGCRAPolicingVBR.name: portGCRAPolicingVBR
portGCRAPolicingVBR.description: This variable defines the per-port policing configuration for nrtVBR connections. The states mean the following: allOn: ALL nrtVBR connections arriving on this port will be subjected to GCRA policing. allOff: NO nrtVBR connections arriving on this port will be subjected to GCRA policing. svcOn: ALL nrtVBR SVCs arriving on this port will be subjected to GCRA policing svcOff: NO nrtVBR SVCs arriving on this port will be subjected to GCRA policing. nrtVBR PVCs will be GCRA policed based on the state of their UPC contract. default: ALL nrtVBR UNI SVCs/SVPs arriving at this port will be subject to GCRA policing and NO nrtVBR NNI SVCs/SVPs arriving at this port will be subject to GCRA policing. nrtVBR PVCs/PVPs arriving at this port will be policed based on the state of their UPC contract.

portAAL5PacketDiscardCBR.name: portAAL5PacketDiscardCBR
portAAL5PacketDiscardCBR.description: This variable defines the per-port AAL5 packet discard configuration for CBR connections. The states mean the following: allOn: All CBR AAL5 connections have packet discard performed on them. allOff: AAL5 packet discard is not performed on any CBR connections. svcOn: Any CBR SVC that 'requests' packet discard will have it performed. For CBR PVC's, AAL5 packet discard is enabled based on the UPC contract of the connection. svcOff: AAL5 packet discard is not performed on any CBR SVC's.For CBR PVC's, AAL5 packet discard is enabled based on the UPC contract of the connection.

portAAL5PacketDiscardVBR.name: portAAL5PacketDiscardVBR
portAAL5PacketDiscardVBR.description: This variable defines the per-port AAL5 packet discard configuration for nrtVBR connections. The states mean the following: allOn: All nrtVBR AAL5 connections have packet discard performed on them. allOff: AAL5 packet discard is not performed on any nrtVBR connections. svcOn: Any nrtVBR SVC that 'requests' packet discard will have it performed. For nrtVBR PVC's, AAL5 packet discard is enabled based on the UPC contract of the connection. svcOff: AAL5 packet discard is not performed on any nrtVBR SVC's.For nrtVBR PVC's, AAL5 packet discard is enabled based on the UPC contract of the connection.

portAAL5PacketDiscardUBR.name: portAAL5PacketDiscardUBR
portAAL5PacketDiscardUBR.description: This variable defines the per-port AAL5 packet discard configuration for UBR connections. The states mean the following: allOn: All UBR AAL5 connections have packet discard performed on them. allOff: AAL5 packet discard is not performed on any UBR connections. svcOn: Any UBR SVC that 'requests' packet discard will have it performed. For UBR PVC's, AAL5 packet discard is enabled based on the UPC contract of the connection. svcOff: AAL5 packet discard is not performed on any UBR SVC's.For UBR PVC's, AAL5 packet discard is enabled based on the UPC contract of the connection.

portInputCACErrors.name: portInputCACErrors
portInputCACErrors.description: The number of input CAC (Call Admission Control) failures on this port.

portInputVPIErrors.name: portInputVPIErrors
portInputVPIErrors.description: The number of input VPI allocation failures on this port.

portInputVCIErrors.name: portInputVCIErrors
portInputVCIErrors.description: The number of input VCI allocation failures on this port.

portInputSetupErrors.name: portInputSetupErrors
portInputSetupErrors.description: The number of input connection setup failures on this port.

portOutputCACErrors.name: portOutputCACErrors
portOutputCACErrors.description: The number of output CAC (Call Admission Control) failures on this port.

portOutputVPIErrors.name: portOutputVPIErrors
portOutputVPIErrors.description: The number of output VPI allocation failures on this port.

portOutputVCIErrors.name: portOutputVCIErrors
portOutputVCIErrors.description: The number of output VCI allocation failures on this port.

portOutputSetupErrors.name: portOutputSetupErrors
portOutputSetupErrors.description: The number of output connection setup failures on this port.

portPPPolicingCBR.name: portPPPolicingCBR
portPPPolicingCBR.description: This variable defines the per-port AAL5 Partial Packet Policing configuration for CBR connections. The states of this variable mean the following: allOn: All CBR AAL5 connections have partial packet policing performed on them. allOff: AAL5 partial packet policing is not performed on any CBR connections. svcOn: Any CBR SVC that uses AAL5 will have partial packet policing performed on it. For CBR PVC's, partial packet policing will be performed based on the UPC contract of the connection. svcOff: Partial packet policing will not be performed on any CBR SVC's. For CBR PVC's, partial packet policing is enabled based on the UPC contract of the connection.

portPPPolicingVBR.name: portPPPolicingVBR
portPPPolicingVBR.description: This variable defines the per-port AAL5 Partial Packet Policing configuration for nrtVBR connections. The states of this variable mean the following: allOn: All nrtVBR AAL5 connections have partial packet policing performed on them. allOff: AAL5 partial packet policing is not performed on any nrtVBR connections. svcOn: Any nrtVBR SVC that uses AAL5 will have partial packet policing performed on it. For nrtVBR PVC's, partial packet policing will be performed based on the UPC contract of the connection. svcOff: Partial packet policing will not be performed on any nrtVBR SVC's. For nrtVBR PVC's, partial packet policing is enabled based on the UPC contract of the connection.

portUBRTagging.name: portUBRTagging
portUBRTagging.description: This variable defines the per-port configuration for tagging (setting CLP=1) of all cells on UBR connections. The states of this variable mean the following: allOn: All UBR connections will be tagged. allOff: No UBR connections will be subject to tagging. svcOn: All UBR SVC's will be tagged. UBR PVC's will be tagged based on their UPC contract. svcOff: No UBR SVC's will be tagged. UBR PVC's will be tagged based on their UPC contract.

portInputCdv.name: portInputCdv
portInputCdv.description: The current value of Cell Delay Variation attributed to the input side of this port, which can be either a user specified value or the system default, as determined by the setting of portInputCdvMode.

portInputMaxctd.name: portInputMaxctd
portInputMaxctd.description: This variable give the maximum Cell Transfer Delay that is being attributed to the input side of this port. The value can be either user specified or a hardware dependant system default value.

portInputDelayMode.name: portInputDelayMode
portInputDelayMode.description: This variable controls whether the Cell Delay Variation and Maximum Cell Transfer Delay values attributed to the input side of this port are based on a user defined value or the hardware dependant system default values.

portOutputCdv.name: portOutputCdv
portOutputCdv.description: If portOutputDelayMode == userSpecified then this variable contains the constant amount of Cell Delay Variation that is being attributed to this output port. If portOutputDelayMode == systemDefault then an actual value for the Cell Delay Variation experienced by connections traversing this port is being calculated. In this case the value of this variable is meaningless since CDV can only be calculated on a per-connection basis.

portOutputMaxctd.name: portOutputMaxctd
portOutputMaxctd.description: This variable gives the maximum Cell Transfer Delay that is being attributed to the output side of this port. The value can be either user specified or a hardware dependant system default value.

portOutputDelayMode.name: portOutputDelayMode
portOutputDelayMode.description: This variable controls whether the Cell Delay Variation value contributed by the input side of this port is based on a user defined value or the system default value.

portCACStatus.name: portCACStatus
portCACStatus.description: The enforcement state of call admission control. The default is enabled(1).

portCounterResetTime.name: portCounterResetTime
portCounterResetTime.description: Indicates when this port's counters were reset. The TimeStamp is equal to moduleUptime when the reset occurred. If this ports counters were never reset, portCounterResetTime will be zero. This variable is updated whenever portCounterReset or switchCounterReset is written.

portCounterReset.name: portCounterReset
portCounterReset.description: Writing a value of resetRequest will result in a reset of all counters on this port. VCC indexed counters are excluded. A response value of resetTrue indicates a resetRequest has succeeded and is currently in effect. A response value of resetFalse indicates a reset is not currently in effect.

portName.name: portName
portName.description: The name of this port (BNP format or otherwise).

portGCRAPolicingRTVBR.name: portGCRAPolicingRTVBR
portGCRAPolicingRTVBR.description: This variable defines the per-port policing configuration for rtVBR connections. The states mean the following: allOn: ALL rtVBR connections arriving on this port will be subjected to GCRA policing. allOff: NO rtVBR connections arriving on this port will be subjected to GCRA policing. svcOn: ALL rtVBR SVCs arriving on this port will be subjected to GCRA policing svcOff: NO rtVBR SVCs arriving on this port will be subjected to GCRA policing. rtVBR PVCs will be GCRA policed based on the state of their UPC contract. default: ALL rtVBR UNI SVCs/SVPs arriving at this port will be subject to GCRA policing and NO rtVBR NNI SVCs/SVPs arriving at this port will be subject to GCRA policing. rtVBR PVCs/PVPs arriving at this port will be policed based on the state of their UPC contract.

portGCRAPolicingNRTVBR.name: portGCRAPolicingNRTVBR
portGCRAPolicingNRTVBR.description: This variable defines the per-port policing configuration for nrtVBR connections. The states mean the following: allOn: ALL nrtVBR connections arriving on this port will be subjected to GCRA policing. allOff: NO nrtVBR connections arriving on this port will be subjected to GCRA policing. svcOn: ALL nrtVBR SVCs arriving on this port will be subjected to GCRA policing svcOff: NO nrtVBR SVCs arriving on this port will be subjected to GCRA policing. nrtVBR PVCs will be GCRA policed based on the state of their UPC contract. default: ALL nrtVBR UNI SVCs/SVPs arriving at this port will be subject to GCRA policing and NO nrtVBR NNI SVCs/SVPs arriving at this port will be subject to GCRA policing. nrtVBR PVCs/PVPs arriving at this port will be policed based on the state of their UPC contract.

portAAL5PacketDiscardRTVBR.name: portAAL5PacketDiscardRTVBR
portAAL5PacketDiscardRTVBR.description: This variable defines the per-port AAL5 packet discard configuration for rtVBR connections. The states mean the following: allOn: All rtVBR AAL5 connections have packet discard performed on them. allOff: AAL5 packet discard is not performed on any rtVBR connections. svcOn: Any rtVBR SVC that 'requests' packet discard will have it performed. For rtVBR PVC's, AAL5 packet discard is enabled based on the UPC contract of the connection. svcOff: AAL5 packet discard is not performed on any rtVBR SVC's.For rtVBR PVC's, AAL5 packet discard is enabled based on the UPC contract of the connection.

portAAL5PacketDiscardNRTVBR.name: portAAL5PacketDiscardNRTVBR
portAAL5PacketDiscardNRTVBR.description: This variable defines the per-port AAL5 packet discard configuration for nrtVBR connections. The states mean the following: allOn: All nrtVBR AAL5 connections have packet discard performed on them. allOff: AAL5 packet discard is not performed on any nrtVBR connections. svcOn: Any nrtVBR SVC that 'requests' packet discard will have it performed. For nrtVBR PVC's, AAL5 packet discard is enabled based on the UPC contract of the connection. svcOff: AAL5 packet discard is not performed on any nrtVBR SVC's.For nrtVBR PVC's, AAL5 packet discard is enabled based on the UPC contract of the connection.

portPPPolicingNRTVBR.name: portPPPolicingNRTVBR
portPPPolicingNRTVBR.description: This variable defines the per-port AAL5 Partial Packet Policing configuration for nrtVBR connections. The states of this variable mean the following: allOn: All nrtVBR AAL5 connections have partial packet policing performed on them. allOff: AAL5 partial packet policing is not performed on any nrtVBR connections. svcOn: Any nrtVBR SVC that uses AAL5 will have partial packet policing performed on it. For nrtVBR PVC's, partial packet policing will be performed based on the UPC contract of the connection. svcOff: Partial packet policing will not be performed on any nrtVBR SVC's. For nrtVBR PVC's, partial packet policing is enabled based on the UPC contract of the connection.

portPPPolicingRTVBR.name: portPPPolicingRTVBR
portPPPolicingRTVBR.description: This variable defines the per-port AAL5 Partial Packet Policing configuration for rtVBR connections. The states of this variable mean the following: allOn: All rtVBR AAL5 connections have partial packet policing performed on them. allOff: AAL5 partial packet policing is not performed on any rtVBR connections. svcOn: Any rtVBR SVC that uses AAL5 will have partial packet policing performed on it. For rtVBR PVC's, partial packet policing will be performed based on the UPC contract of the connection. svcOff: Partial packet policing will not be performed on any rtVBR SVC's. For rtVBR PVC's, partial packet policing is enabled based on the UPC contract of the connection.

portNrtVbrOverbooking.name: portNrtVbrOverbooking
portNrtVbrOverbooking.description: The percentage of overbooking for nrtVBR connections. The default value is 100 (no overbooking).

portNrtVbrBufferOverb.name: portNrtVbrBufferOverb
portNrtVbrBufferOverb.description: The percentage of buffer overbooking for nrtVBR connections. The default value is 100 (no overbooking).

portRtVbrOverbooking.name: portRtVbrOverbooking
portRtVbrOverbooking.description: The percentage of overbooking for rtVBR connections. The default value is 100 (no overbooking).

portRtVbrBufferOverb.name: portRtVbrBufferOverb
portRtVbrBufferOverb.description: The percentage of buffer overbooking for rtVBR connections. The default value is 100 (no overbooking).

portPathOverbooking.name: portPathOverbooking
portPathOverbooking.description: The percentage of overbooking for inelastic originating paths. The default value is 100 (no overbooking).

atmIfConnSchedTable.name: atmIfConnSchedTable
atmIfConnSchedTable.description: A table of connection scheduling information on this ATM If.

atmIfConnSchedEntry.name: atmIfConnSchedEntry
atmIfConnSchedEntry.description: A table of connection scheduling information on this ATM If.

atmIfConnSchedLink.name: atmIfConnSchedLink
atmIfConnSchedLink.description: The index of this ATM If.

atmIfConnSchedServCat.name: atmIfConnSchedServCat
atmIfConnSchedServCat.description: Index of this service category within serviceCategoryTable.

atmIfConnSchedMode.name: atmIfConnSchedMode
atmIfConnSchedMode.description: The scheduling mode used for connections of type atmIfConnSchedServCat on this ATM if. The default choice of AtmConnSchedMode is not allowed at atmIf level.

atmIfConnSchedOverride.name: atmIfConnSchedOverride
atmIfConnSchedOverride.description: The override option used for connections of type atmIfConnSchedServCat on this ATM if.

ifIndexMapTable.name: ifIndexMapTable
ifIndexMapTable.description: A table containing information about how physical interfaces ifIndexes relate to the b-n-p triplets. Other ifIndices will not have entries in this table.

ifIndexMapEntry.name: ifIndexMapEntry
ifIndexMapEntry.description: A table entry containing ifindex/b-n-p information.

ifIndexMapIndex.name: ifIndexMapIndex
ifIndexMapIndex.description: The ifIndex of this entry. The ifindex must be that of a physical interface.

ifIndexMapBoard.name: ifIndexMapBoard
ifIndexMapBoard.description: The board number that this ifIndex refers to

ifIndexMapNetmod.name: ifIndexMapNetmod
ifIndexMapNetmod.description: The netmod number that this ifIndex refers to

ifIndexMapPort.name: ifIndexMapPort
ifIndexMapPort.description: The port number that this ifIndex refers to

cesExtTable.name: cesExtTable
cesExtTable.description: This indicates the value of the next available index to be used for CES creation

cbrctConfTable.name: cbrctConfTable
cbrctConfTable.description: A table of CBR Cut-through configuration information.

cbrctConfEntry.name: cbrctConfEntry
cbrctConfEntry.description: A table entry containing CBR Cut-through configuration information for each CES connection.

cbrctState.name: cbrctState
cbrctState.description: This variable indicates whether the CBR Cut-through feature is enabled or disabled on the ingress connection. The values mean: enabled CBR Cut-through enabled disabled CBR Cut-through disabled

cbrctIdleDetection.name: cbrctIdleDetection
cbrctIdleDetection.description: This variable identifies the idle detection mechanism used on this connection. The different values are: idlePattern(1) detection is based on idle pattern detection cas(2) detection is based on CAS signalling

cbrctIdleMask.name: cbrctIdleMask
cbrctIdleMask.description: This contains the mask pattern for idle detection.

cbrctNoOfIdlePatterns.name: cbrctNoOfIdlePatterns
cbrctNoOfIdlePatterns.description: This variable contains the number of idle patterns configured for detection.

cbrctIdlePatterns.name: cbrctIdlePatterns
cbrctIdlePatterns.description: This contains the patterns for idle detection. For detection based on both idle and mask patterns it contains the idle octet patterns. For detection based on signalling it contains the octet value of AB signalling bits (eg. 00000010 (02H), the bit 0 is B bit and bit 1 is A bit). Maximum of 4 idle patterns are used. The idle patterns get filled from the least significant byte. The cbrctNoOfIdlePatterns gives the number of idle patterns.

cbrctIdleIntPeriod.name: cbrctIdleIntPeriod
cbrctIdleIntPeriod.description: This contains the integration period for idle detection.

cbrctActiveIntPeriod.name: cbrctActiveIntPeriod
cbrctActiveIntPeriod.description: This contains the integration period for active detection.

asxAtmIfTable.name: asxAtmIfTable
asxAtmIfTable.description: A table of atm interface information.

asxAtmIfEntry.name: asxAtmIfEntry
asxAtmIfEntry.description: A table entry containing atm interface information.

asxAtmIfName.name: asxAtmIfName
asxAtmIfName.description: The persistent name of this atm interface. It is used to index this atm interface. All letters in the asxAtmIfName are always represented in uppercase.

asxAtmIfLinkid.name: asxAtmIfLinkid
asxAtmIfLinkid.description: The linkid of this atm interface.

pathTable.name: pathTable
pathTable.description: A table of information about the virtual paths passing through this ATM switch.

pathEntry.name: pathEntry
pathEntry.description: A table entry containing path information.

pathPort.name: pathPort
pathPort.description: The value of this object identifies the input port of this path and is the same as the portNumber.

pathVPI.name: pathVPI
pathVPI.description: The input VPI (Virtual Path Identifier) of this path.

pathStatus.name: pathStatus
pathStatus.description: The status of this path entry.

pathNumOutputs.name: pathNumOutputs
pathNumOutputs.description: The number of output ports to which this path is routed.

pathMaxChannels.name: pathMaxChannels
pathMaxChannels.description: The maximum number of virtual channels that can be allocated on this path.

pathNumChannels.name: pathNumChannels
pathNumChannels.description: The number of virtual channels currently allocated on this path.

pathMaxBandwidth.name: pathMaxBandwidth
pathMaxBandwidth.description: The maximum bandwidth of this path, in cells per second.

pathAllocBandwidth.name: pathAllocBandwidth
pathAllocBandwidth.description: The allocated bandwidth of this path, in cells per second.

pathUsedBandwidth.name: pathUsedBandwidth
pathUsedBandwidth.description: The bandwidth being used on this path, in cells per second.

pathCells.name: pathCells
pathCells.description: The number of cells transferred over this path.

pathUptime.name: pathUptime
pathUptime.description: The time since this path was created, in hundredths of a second.

pathSigProtocol.name: pathSigProtocol
pathSigProtocol.description: The signaling protocol that created this path.

pathRejectedCells.name: pathRejectedCells
pathRejectedCells.description: The number of cells over this path that were rejected (i.e. dropped) by the policer on the switch fabric. This does not include any cells that may have been tagged with CLP=1 by the policer, only cells that were discarded.

pathMinVCI.name: pathMinVCI
pathMinVCI.description: The minimum VCI that can be allocated on this path.

pathMaxVCI.name: pathMaxVCI
pathMaxVCI.description: The maximum VCI that can be allocated on this path.

pathCACErrors.name: pathCACErrors
pathCACErrors.description: The number of CAC (Call Admission Control) failures on this path.

pathVCIErrors.name: pathVCIErrors
pathVCIErrors.description: The number of VCI allocation failures on this path.

pathSetupErrors.name: pathSetupErrors
pathSetupErrors.description: The number of connection setup failures on this path.

pathRouteTable.name: pathRouteTable
pathRouteTable.description: A table of information about the routing of paths through this ATM switch.

pathRouteEntry.name: pathRouteEntry
pathRouteEntry.description: A table entry containing path route information.

pathrInputPort.name: pathrInputPort
pathrInputPort.description: The value of this object identifies the input port of this path and is the same as the portNumber.

pathrInputVPI.name: pathrInputVPI
pathrInputVPI.description: The input VPI (Virtual Path Identifier) of this path.

pathrOutputPort.name: pathrOutputPort
pathrOutputPort.description: The value of this object identifies the output port of this path and is the same as the portNumber.

pathrOutputVPI.name: pathrOutputVPI
pathrOutputVPI.description: The output VPI (Virtual Path Identifier) of this path.

pathrStatus.name: pathrStatus
pathrStatus.description: The status of this path entry.

pathrMaxBandwidth.name: pathrMaxBandwidth
pathrMaxBandwidth.description: The maximum bandwidth of this path, in cells per second.

pathrAllocBandwidth.name: pathrAllocBandwidth
pathrAllocBandwidth.description: The allocated bandwidth of this path, in cells per second.

pathrCells.name: pathrCells
pathrCells.description: The number of cells transferred over this path.

pathrUptime.name: pathrUptime
pathrUptime.description: The time since this path was created, in hundredths of a second.

pathrSigProtocol.name: pathrSigProtocol
pathrSigProtocol.description: The signaling protocol that created this path.

pathrRejectedCells.name: pathrRejectedCells
pathrRejectedCells.description: The number of cells over this through path that were rejected (i.e. dropped) by the policer on the switch fabric. This does not include any cells that may have been tagged with CLP=1 by the policer, only cells that were discarded.

pathrLoopVPI.name: pathrLoopVPI
pathrLoopVPI.description: If this value is other than -1, cells destined for pathrOutputPort, pathrOutputVPI will be translated by the netmod to pathrLoopVPI before actually being trasmitted. This was instituted to facilitate single port loopback.

pathrUpcContract.name: pathrUpcContract
pathrUpcContract.description: The UPC contract that will be used to police this through path. This is the number of the row in the upcContractTable.

pathrName.name: pathrName
pathrName.description: The value of this object identifies the name that has been assigned for this path.

pathrConnectionType.name: pathrConnectionType
pathrConnectionType.description: This object identifies the type of the path endpoints with respect to a particular network.

pathrServCat.name: pathrServCat
pathrServCat.description: Index of this service category within serviceCategoryTable

outputPathTable.name: outputPathTable
outputPathTable.description: A table of information about the virtual paths originating at this ATM switch.

outputPathEntry.name: outputPathEntry
outputPathEntry.description: A table entry containing output path information.

opathPort.name: opathPort
opathPort.description: The value of this object identifies the output port of this path and is the same as the portNumber.

opathVPI.name: opathVPI
opathVPI.description: The VPI (Virtual Path Identifier) of this path.

opathStatus.name: opathStatus
opathStatus.description: The status of this path entry.

opathMaxChannels.name: opathMaxChannels
opathMaxChannels.description: The maximum number of virtual channels that can be allocated on this path.

opathNumChannels.name: opathNumChannels
opathNumChannels.description: The number of virtual channels currently allocated on this path.

opathMaxBandwidth.name: opathMaxBandwidth
opathMaxBandwidth.description: The maximum bandwidth of this path, in cells per second.

opathAllocBandwidth.name: opathAllocBandwidth
opathAllocBandwidth.description: The allocated bandwidth of this path, in cells per second.

opathUsedBandwidth.name: opathUsedBandwidth
opathUsedBandwidth.description: The bandwidth used on this path, in cells per second.

opathCells.name: opathCells
opathCells.description: The number of cells transmitted on this path.

opathUptime.name: opathUptime
opathUptime.description: The time since this path was created, in hundredths of a second.

opathSigProtocol.name: opathSigProtocol
opathSigProtocol.description: The signaling protocol that created this path.

opathRejectedCells.name: opathRejectedCells
opathRejectedCells.description: The number of cells on this output path that were rejected (i.e. dropped) by the policer on the switch fabric. This does not include any cells that may have been tagged with CLP=1 by the policer, only cells that were discarded.

opathVbrOverbooking.name: opathVbrOverbooking
opathVbrOverbooking.description: The percentage of overbooking for nrtVBR connections. The default value is 100 (no overbooking). A value of -1 indicates that the path is elastic, and therefore the overbooking factors are meaningless.

opathVbrBufferOverb.name: opathVbrBufferOverb
opathVbrBufferOverb.description: The percentage of buffer overbooking for nrtVBR connections. The default value is 100 (no overbooking). A value of -1 indicates that the path is elastic, and therefore the overbooking factors are meaningless.

opathMinVCI.name: opathMinVCI
opathMinVCI.description: The minimum VCI that can be allocated on this path.

opathMaxVCI.name: opathMaxVCI
opathMaxVCI.description: The maximum VCI that can be allocated on this path.

opathCACErrors.name: opathCACErrors
opathCACErrors.description: The number of CAC (Call Admission Control) failures on this path.

opathVCIErrors.name: opathVCIErrors
opathVCIErrors.description: The number of VCI allocation failures on this path.

opathSetupErrors.name: opathSetupErrors
opathSetupErrors.description: The number of connection setup failures on this path.

opathLoopVPI.name: opathLoopVPI
opathLoopVPI.description: If this value is assigned to other than -1, the netmod will modify cell headers received from the fabric that are destined for opathPort, opathVPI to have the vpi value of opathLoopVPI before being transmitted. This extra translation can be used to loop cells back onto the fabric using a single port.

opathSchedMode.name: opathSchedMode
opathSchedMode.description: The value of this object identifies the scheduling mode for this originating path.

opathNrtVbrOverbooking.name: opathNrtVbrOverbooking
opathNrtVbrOverbooking.description: The percentage of overbooking for nrtVBR connections. The default value is 100 (no overbooking). A value of -1 indicates that the path is elastic, and therefore the overbooking factors are meaningless.

opathNrtVbrBufferOverb.name: opathNrtVbrBufferOverb
opathNrtVbrBufferOverb.description: The percentage of buffer overbooking for nrtVBR connections. The default value is 100 (no overbooking). A value of -1 indicates that the path is elastic, and therefore the overbooking factors are meaningless.

opathRtVbrOverbooking.name: opathRtVbrOverbooking
opathRtVbrOverbooking.description: The percentage of overbooking for rtVBR connections. The default value is 100 (no overbooking). A value of -1 indicates that the path is elastic, and therefore the overbooking factors are meaningless.

opathRtVbrBufferOverb.name: opathRtVbrBufferOverb
opathRtVbrBufferOverb.description: The percentage of buffer overbooking for rtVBR connections. The default value is 100 (no overbooking). A value of -1 indicates that the path is elastic, and therefore the overbooking factors are meaningless.

outputPathStatsTable.name: outputPathStatsTable
outputPathStatsTable.description: A table of statistics information about the virtual paths originating at this ATM switch.

outputPathStatsEntry.name: outputPathStatsEntry
outputPathStatsEntry.description: A table entry containing originating channel statistics information.

opathStatsPort.name: opathStatsPort
opathStatsPort.description: The value of this object identifies the output port of this channel and is the same as the opathPort, and portNumber.

opathStatsVPI.name: opathStatsVPI
opathStatsVPI.description: The value of this object identifies the output VPI (Virtual Path Identifier) of this channel and is the same as the opathVPI.

opathStatsLostCells.name: opathStatsLostCells
opathStatsLostCells.description: The number of cells on this output path that were dropped at the output netmod.

opathStatsTransmittedCells.name: opathStatsTransmittedCells
opathStatsTransmittedCells.description: The number of cells on this output path that were transmitted.

opathStatsIntentionalLostCells.name: opathStatsIntentionalLostCells
opathStatsIntentionalLostCells.description: The number of cells on this output path that were dropped intentionally at the output netmod.

opathStatsCLP0Cells.name: opathStatsCLP0Cells
opathStatsCLP0Cells.description: The number of CLP = 0 cells transmitted on this output path.

opathStatsLostPackets.name: opathStatsLostPackets
opathStatsLostPackets.description: The number of packets on this output path that were dropped at the output netmod.

opathStatsTransmittedPackets.name: opathStatsTransmittedPackets
opathStatsTransmittedPackets.description: The number of Packets on this output path that were transmitted.

outputPathChannelSchedTable.name: outputPathChannelSchedTable
outputPathChannelSchedTable.description: A table of connection scheduling information on this output path.

outputPathChannelSchedEntry.name: outputPathChannelSchedEntry
outputPathChannelSchedEntry.description: A table of connection scheduling information on this output path.

opathChannelSchedVPI.name: opathChannelSchedVPI
opathChannelSchedVPI.description: The value of this object identifies the output VPI (Virtual Path Identifier) of this path.

opathChannelSchedServCat.name: opathChannelSchedServCat
opathChannelSchedServCat.description: Index of this service category within serviceCategoryTable

opathChannelSchedSchedMode.name: opathChannelSchedSchedMode
opathChannelSchedSchedMode.description: The scheduling mode used for channels of type opathChannelSchedServCat within this path. The default choice of AtmConnSchedMode is not allowed at path level.

opathChannelSchedSchedOverride.name: opathChannelSchedSchedOverride
opathChannelSchedSchedOverride.description: The override option used for channels of type opathChannelSchedServCat within this path

channelTable.name: channelTable
channelTable.description: A table of information about the virtual channels passing through this ATM switch.

channelEntry.name: channelEntry
channelEntry.description: A table entry containing channel information.

chanPort.name: chanPort
chanPort.description: The value of this object identifies the input port of this channel and is the same as the pathPort and portNumber.

chanVPI.name: chanVPI
chanVPI.description: The value of this object identifies the input VPI (Virtual Path Identifier) of this channel, and is the same as the pathVPI.

chanVCI.name: chanVCI
chanVCI.description: The input VCI (Virtual Channel Identifier) of this channel.

chanStatus.name: chanStatus
chanStatus.description: The status of this channel entry.

chanNumOutputs.name: chanNumOutputs
chanNumOutputs.description: The number of output ports to which this channel is routed.

chanAllocBandwidth.name: chanAllocBandwidth
chanAllocBandwidth.description: The allocated bandwidth of this channel, in cells per second.

chanUsedBandwidth.name: chanUsedBandwidth
chanUsedBandwidth.description: The bandwidth used on this channel, in cells per second.

chanCells.name: chanCells
chanCells.description: The number of cells transferred on this channel.

chanUptime.name: chanUptime
chanUptime.description: The time since this channel was created, in hundredths of a second.

chanSigProtocol.name: chanSigProtocol
chanSigProtocol.description: The signaling protocol that created this channel.

chanRejectedCells.name: chanRejectedCells
chanRejectedCells.description: The number of cells on this channel that were rejected (dropped) by the policer on the switch fabric. This does not include any cells that may have been tagged with CLP=1 by the policer, only cells that were discarded.

chanCDV.name: chanCDV
chanCDV.description: The channel Cell Delay Variation Tolerance (CDV), specified in microseconds, indicates the time window in which a cell may be received on a channel and be accepted. A cell that is received on a channel outside the CDV window will be dropped or tagged, based on the value of chanPolicingAction. The chanCDV value overrides the default value inherited from the link.

chanPolicingAction.name: chanPolicingAction
chanPolicingAction.description: This object indicates the action the switch will take in case of bandwidth violation on this channel.

chanUpcContract.name: chanUpcContract
chanUpcContract.description: The UPC contract that will be used to police this channel. This is the number of the row in the upcContractTable.

chanServCat.name: chanServCat
chanServCat.description: Index of this service category within serviceCategoryTable

chanQosPoliceScheme.name: chanQosPoliceScheme
chanQosPoliceScheme.description: It identifies the policing associated with the UPC contract as defined in the ATM Forum TM 4.0 specifications. However, the policing schemes cbr0 and cbr0tag are specific to FORE switches

chanQosSCR.name: chanQosSCR
chanQosSCR.description: The sustained cell rate (cells/sec). It also holds the PCR0 value for cbr0 & cbr0tag contracts

chanQosCDVT.name: chanQosCDVT
chanQosCDVT.description: The channel Cell Delay Variation Tolerance (CDVT), specified in microseconds, indicates the time window in which a cell may be received on a channel and be accepted. A cell that is received on a channel outside the CDV window will be dropped or tagged, based on the value of chanPolicingAction. The chanCDV value overrides the default value inherited from the link.

chanQosPoliceState.name: chanQosPoliceState
chanQosPoliceState.description: Indicates if this connection is policed for traffic violations. When set to 'on' it overrides the policing status of the atm interface on which this connection is established.

chanQosIsAAL5.name: chanQosIsAAL5
chanQosIsAAL5.description: Indicates if this connection is AAL 5

chanQosPerPacketPolicing.name: chanQosPerPacketPolicing
chanQosPerPacketPolicing.description: Should we perform AAL5 Partial Packet Policing on this UPC contract. This variable only has meaning if the connections is also AAL5.

channelRouteTable.name: channelRouteTable
channelRouteTable.description: A table of information about the routing of channels through this ATM switch.

channelRouteEntry.name: channelRouteEntry
channelRouteEntry.description: A table entry containing channel route information.

chanrInputPort.name: chanrInputPort
chanrInputPort.description: The value of this object identifies the input port of this channel and is the same as the chanPort, pathPort, and portNumber.

chanrInputVPI.name: chanrInputVPI
chanrInputVPI.description: The value of this object identifies the input VPI (Virtual Path Identifier) of this channel, and is the same as the chanVPI, and pathVPI.

chanrInputVCI.name: chanrInputVCI
chanrInputVCI.description: The value of this object identifies the input VCI (Virtual Channel Identifier) of this channel, and is the same as chanVCI.

chanrOutputPort.name: chanrOutputPort
chanrOutputPort.description: The value of this object identifies the output port of this channel and is the same as the opathPort, and portNumber.

chanrOutputVPI.name: chanrOutputVPI
chanrOutputVPI.description: The value of this object identifies the output VPI (Virtual Path Identifier) of this channel and is the same as the opathVPI.

chanrOutputVCI.name: chanrOutputVCI
chanrOutputVCI.description: The output VCI (Virtual Channel Identifier) of this channel.

chanrStatus.name: chanrStatus
chanrStatus.description: The status of this channel entry.

chanrSigProtocol.name: chanrSigProtocol
chanrSigProtocol.description: The signaling protocol that created this channel.

chanrName.name: chanrName
chanrName.description: The value of this object identifies the name that has been assigned for this channel.

chanrConnectionType.name: chanrConnectionType
chanrConnectionType.description: This object identifies the type of the channel endpoints with respect to a particular network.

reverseChannelRouteTable.name: reverseChannelRouteTable
reverseChannelRouteTable.description: A table of information about reverse channel routes through this ATM switch.

reverseChannelRouteEntry.name: reverseChannelRouteEntry
reverseChannelRouteEntry.description: A table entry containing reverse channel route information.

revChanrOutputPort.name: revChanrOutputPort
revChanrOutputPort.description: The value of this object identifies the output port of this channel and is the same as the chanrOutputPort, opathPort and portNumber.

revChanrOutputVPI.name: revChanrOutputVPI
revChanrOutputVPI.description: The value of this object identifies the output VPI (Virtual Path Identifier) of this channel and is the same as the chanrOutputVPI and opathVPI.

revChanrOutputVCI.name: revChanrOutputVCI
revChanrOutputVCI.description: The output VCI (Virtual Channel Identifier) of this channel and is the same as chanrOutputVCI.

revChanrInputPort.name: revChanrInputPort
revChanrInputPort.description: The value of this object identifies the input port of this channel and is the same as the chanPort, chanrInputPort, pathPort, and portNumber.

revChanrInputVPI.name: revChanrInputVPI
revChanrInputVPI.description: The value of this object identifies the input VPI (Virtual Path Identifier) of this channel, and is the same as the chanVPI, chanrInputVPI and pathVPI.

revChanrInputVCI.name: revChanrInputVCI
revChanrInputVCI.description: The value of this object identifies the input VCI (Virtual Channel Identifier) of this channel, and is the same as chanVCI and chanrInputVCI.

revChanrSigProtocol.name: revChanrSigProtocol
revChanrSigProtocol.description: The signaling protocol that created this channel and is the same as chanrSigProtocol.

outputChannelStatsTable.name: outputChannelStatsTable
outputChannelStatsTable.description: A table of statistics information about the virtual channels originating at this ATM switch.

outputChannelStatsEntry.name: outputChannelStatsEntry
outputChannelStatsEntry.description: A table entry containing originating channel statistics information.

ochanStatsPort.name: ochanStatsPort
ochanStatsPort.description: The value of this object identifies the output port of this channel and is the same as the opathPort, and portNumber.

ochanStatsVPI.name: ochanStatsVPI
ochanStatsVPI.description: The value of this object identifies the output VPI (Virtual Path Identifier) of this channel and is the same as the opathVPI.

ochanStatsVCI.name: ochanStatsVCI
ochanStatsVCI.description: The output VCI (Virtual Channel Identifier) of this channel.

ochanStatsLostCells.name: ochanStatsLostCells
ochanStatsLostCells.description: The number of cells on this output channel that were dropped at the output netmod.

ochanStatsTransmittedCells.name: ochanStatsTransmittedCells
ochanStatsTransmittedCells.description: The number of cells on this output channel that were transmitted.

ochanStatsIntentionalLostCells.name: ochanStatsIntentionalLostCells
ochanStatsIntentionalLostCells.description: The number of cells on this output channel that were dropped intentionally.

ochanStatsCLP0Cells.name: ochanStatsCLP0Cells
ochanStatsCLP0Cells.description: The number of CLP = 0 cells transmitted on this output path.

ochanStatsLostPackets.name: ochanStatsLostPackets
ochanStatsLostPackets.description: The number of packets on this output path that were dropped at the output netmod.

ochanStatsTransmittedPackets.name: ochanStatsTransmittedPackets
ochanStatsTransmittedPackets.description: The number of Packets on this output path that were transmitted.

numberOfLinks.name: numberOfLinks
numberOfLinks.description: Current number of links known by this ATM switch.

linkTable.name: linkTable
linkTable.description: A table of links describing this switch's view of the ATM network topology.

linkEntry.name: linkEntry
linkEntry.description: A table entry containing link information.

linkSrc.name: linkSrc
linkSrc.description: The ATM address of the source switch of this link.

linkDest.name: linkDest
linkDest.description: The ATM address of the destination switch of this link.

linkCapacity.name: linkCapacity
linkCapacity.description: The free capacity of this link in kilobits per second.

linkAge.name: linkAge
linkAge.description: The freshness of this link information. The actual value has no units associated with it. It should be used for comparison.

sigPathTable.name: sigPathTable
sigPathTable.description: A table of general information about the signaling path.

sigPathEntry.name: sigPathEntry
sigPathEntry.description: A table entry containing signaling path information, indexed by port and path.

sigPathPort.name: sigPathPort
sigPathPort.description: The value of this object identifies the port of this signalling path, and is the same as the portNumber.

sigPathVPI.name: sigPathVPI
sigPathVPI.description: The VPI (Virtual Path Identifier) of this signaling path.

sigPathVCI.name: sigPathVCI
sigPathVCI.description: The VCI (Virtual Channel Identifier) of the signaling channel within the signaling path.

sigPathClsVCI.name: sigPathClsVCI
sigPathClsVCI.description: The VCI (Virtual Channel Identifier) of the connectionless channel within the signaling path.

sigPathAdminStatus.name: sigPathAdminStatus
sigPathAdminStatus.description: The desired state of this signaling channel. The up(1) state dictates that SPANS (Simple Protocol for ATM Network Siganlling) messages are used for signalling. The down(2) state dictates the SPANS protocol is not used for signalling.

sigPathOperStatus.name: sigPathOperStatus
sigPathOperStatus.description: The current operational state of this signaling channel, as determined either by administrative action, when the value of sigPathAdminStatus is down(2), or by a link monitoring protocol, when the value of sigPathAdminStatus is up(1).

sigPathEntryStatus.name: sigPathEntryStatus
sigPathEntryStatus.description: The status of this signaling path entry.

sigPathAALType.name: sigPathAALType
sigPathAALType.description: The AAL (ATM Adaptation LAyer) type that is used by this signaling path.

sigPathCDV.name: sigPathCDV
sigPathCDV.description: The signalling path Cell Delay Variation (CDV) specified in microseconds, indicates the time window in which a cell may be received on a signalling channel and be accepted. A cell that is received on a channel outside the CDV window will be dropped. The sigPathCDV value overrides the default value of switchCDV.

sigPathPolicingAction.name: sigPathPolicingAction
sigPathPolicingAction.description: This object indicates the action the switch will take in case of bandwidth violation on a signalling channel. The value set here overrides the default value of switchPolicingAction.

sigPathRemoteAtmAddress.name: sigPathRemoteAtmAddress
sigPathRemoteAtmAddress.description: The ATM address of the entity connected to this signalling path.

sigPathRemoteIpAddress.name: sigPathRemoteIpAddress
sigPathRemoteIpAddress.description: The IP address of the entity connected to this signalling path.

sigPathType.name: sigPathType
sigPathType.description: The type of the signalling path connection. uni(1) (User Network Interface) means that there is a host on remote side, while nni(2) (Network Network Interface) means there is another switch, that speaks SPANS, on the remote side.

sigPathClsUpcContract.name: sigPathClsUpcContract
sigPathClsUpcContract.description: The UPC contract that will be used to police the connectionless VC. This is the number of a row in the upcContractTable

sigPathSigReservedBW.name: sigPathSigReservedBW
sigPathSigReservedBW.description: Bandwidth reserved for the SPANS Signaling VC, in cells/sec.

sigPathMinVCI.name: sigPathMinVCI
sigPathMinVCI.description: The minimum configured VCI (Virtual Channel Identifier) that can be used for SVCs (Signalled Virtual Circuits).

sigPathMaxVCI.name: sigPathMaxVCI
sigPathMaxVCI.description: The maximum configured VCI (Virtual Channel Identifier) that can be used for SVCs (Signalled Virtual Circuits).

sigPathOpenTimeout.name: sigPathOpenTimeout
sigPathOpenTimeout.description: The timeout in msec for SPANS open requests.

sigPathCloseTimeout.name: sigPathCloseTimeout
sigPathCloseTimeout.description: The timeout in msec for SPANS close requests.

sigPathOutputSigService.name: sigPathOutputSigService
sigPathOutputSigService.description: Service Queue where the output signalling vc should be inserted into.

sigPathAALOperType.name: sigPathAALOperType
sigPathAALOperType.description: The AAL (ATM Adaptation LAyer) type that is currently being used by this signaling path.

sigPathStatsTable.name: sigPathStatsTable
sigPathStatsTable.description: A table of statistics about the signaling path.

sigPathStatsEntry.name: sigPathStatsEntry
sigPathStatsEntry.description: A table entry containing signaling path statistics, indexed by port and path.

sigPathStatsPort.name: sigPathStatsPort
sigPathStatsPort.description: The value of this object identifies the port of this signalling path, and is the same as sigPathPort.

sigPathStatsVPI.name: sigPathStatsVPI
sigPathStatsVPI.description: The value of this object identifies the VPI (Virtual Path Identifier) of this signaling path statistics entry, and is the same as sigPathVPI.

sigPathVCCs.name: sigPathVCCs
sigPathVCCs.description: The number of Virtual Channel Connections (VCCs) on this signaling path.

sigPathRestarts.name: sigPathRestarts
sigPathRestarts.description: The number of times the switch has lost and regained contact with the remote signaling entity on this path.

sigPathCallsCompletions.name: sigPathCallsCompletions
sigPathCallsCompletions.description: The number of successfully completed calls on this signaling path.

sigPathCallsFailures.name: sigPathCallsFailures
sigPathCallsFailures.description: The number of call failures on this signaling path.

sigPathCallsRejections.name: sigPathCallsRejections
sigPathCallsRejections.description: The number of connections on this signaling path that were rejected by the far end.

sigPathSpansTransmittedMessages.name: sigPathSpansTransmittedMessages
sigPathSpansTransmittedMessages.description: The total number of SPANS messages that have been transmitted over this signalling path.

sigPathSpansReceivedMessages.name: sigPathSpansReceivedMessages
sigPathSpansReceivedMessages.description: The total number of SPANS messages that have been received on this signalling path.

sigPathClsTransmittedMessages.name: sigPathClsTransmittedMessages
sigPathClsTransmittedMessages.description: The total number of connectionless messages that have been transmitted over this signalling path.

sigPathClsReceivedMessages.name: sigPathClsReceivedMessages
sigPathClsReceivedMessages.description: The total number of connectionless messages that have been received on this signalling path.

spvcSrcNumberOfSPVCs.name: spvcSrcNumberOfSPVCs
spvcSrcNumberOfSPVCs.description: The number of SPVCs (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) that are going out of this switch (i.e. this switch is their source).

spvcSrcTable.name: spvcSrcTable
spvcSrcTable.description: This table contains information about SPVCs (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) that their source is this switch.

spvcSrcEntry.name: spvcSrcEntry
spvcSrcEntry.description: A table entry containing source SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) information.

spvcSrcSpvcId.name: spvcSrcSpvcId
spvcSrcSpvcId.description: The value of this object uniquely identify the SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) that this switch is its source.

spvcSrcSwitchAddr.name: spvcSrcSwitchAddr
spvcSrcSwitchAddr.description: The ATM address of the source switch.

spvcSrcDestSpvcId.name: spvcSrcDestSpvcId
spvcSrcDestSpvcId.description: The SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) identifier at the destination switch. This object should match the spvcDestSpvcId at the destination switch.

spvcSrcDestSwitchAddr.name: spvcSrcDestSwitchAddr
spvcSrcDestSwitchAddr.description: The ATM address of the destination switch.

spvcSrcInPort.name: spvcSrcInPort
spvcSrcInPort.description: The value of this object identifies the input port of this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits), and is the same as the chanrInputPort, chanPort, pathPort, and portNumber.

spvcSrcInVPI.name: spvcSrcInVPI
spvcSrcInVPI.description: The value of this object identifies the input VPI (Virtual Path Identifier) of this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits), and is the same as the chanrInputVPI, chanVPI, pathVPI.

spvcSrcInVCI.name: spvcSrcInVCI
spvcSrcInVCI.description: The value of this object identifies the input VCI (Virtual Channel Identifier) of this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits), and is the same as the chanrInputVCI.

spvcSrcAllocBandwidth.name: spvcSrcAllocBandwidth
spvcSrcAllocBandwidth.description: The allocated bandwidth of this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits).

spvcSrcUpTime.name: spvcSrcUpTime
spvcSrcUpTime.description: The time since this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) was created in hundredths of a second.

spvcSrcStatus.name: spvcSrcStatus
spvcSrcStatus.description: The status of this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits).

spvcSrcEntryStatus.name: spvcSrcEntryStatus
spvcSrcEntryStatus.description: The status of this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) entry.

spvcDestNumberOfSPVCs.name: spvcDestNumberOfSPVCs
spvcDestNumberOfSPVCs.description: The number of SPVCs (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) that are coming into this switch (i.e. this switch is their destination).

spvcDestTable.name: spvcDestTable
spvcDestTable.description: This table contains information about SPVCs (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) that their destination is this switch.

spvcDestEntry.name: spvcDestEntry
spvcDestEntry.description: A table entry containing destination SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) information.

spvcDestSpvcId.name: spvcDestSpvcId
spvcDestSpvcId.description: The value of this object uniquely identify the SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) that this switch is its destination. The range of this object is [1..spvcDestNumberOfSPVCs].

spvcDestSwitchAddr.name: spvcDestSwitchAddr
spvcDestSwitchAddr.description: The ATM address of this (the destination) switch.

spvcDestSrcSpvcId.name: spvcDestSrcSpvcId
spvcDestSrcSpvcId.description: The SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) identifier at the source switch. This object should match the spvcSrcSpvcId at the source switch.

spvcDestSrcSwitchAddr.name: spvcDestSrcSwitchAddr
spvcDestSrcSwitchAddr.description: The ATM address of the source switch.

spvcDestOutPort.name: spvcDestOutPort
spvcDestOutPort.description: The value of this object identifies the output port of this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) and is the same as the chanrOutputPort, opathPort, and portNumber.

spvcDestOutVPI.name: spvcDestOutVPI
spvcDestOutVPI.description: The value of this object identifies the output VPI (Virtual Path Identifier) of this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits), and is the same as the chanrOutputVPI, and opathVPI.

spvcDestOutVCI.name: spvcDestOutVCI
spvcDestOutVCI.description: The value of this object identifies the output VCI (Virtual Channel Identifier) of this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits), and is the same as the chanrOutputVCI.

spvcDestAllocBandwidth.name: spvcDestAllocBandwidth
spvcDestAllocBandwidth.description: The allocated bandwidth of this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits).

spvcDestUpTime.name: spvcDestUpTime
spvcDestUpTime.description: The time since this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) was created in hundredths of a second.

spvcDestStatus.name: spvcDestStatus
spvcDestStatus.description: The status of this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits).

spvcDestEntryStatus.name: spvcDestEntryStatus
spvcDestEntryStatus.description: The status of this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) entry.

pnniSpvcSrcNumberOfSPVCs.name: pnniSpvcSrcNumberOfSPVCs
pnniSpvcSrcNumberOfSPVCs.description: The number of SPVCs (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) that have their source at this switch.

pnniSpvcSrcTable.name: pnniSpvcSrcTable
pnniSpvcSrcTable.description: This table contains information about SPVCs (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) that have their source at this switch.

pnniSpvcSrcEntry.name: pnniSpvcSrcEntry
pnniSpvcSrcEntry.description: A table entry containing source SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) information.

pnniSpvcSrcIndex.name: pnniSpvcSrcIndex
pnniSpvcSrcIndex.description: The value of this object uniquely identify the SPVCs (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) that have this switch as their source.

pnniSpvcSrcCallingPort.name: pnniSpvcSrcCallingPort
pnniSpvcSrcCallingPort.description: The value of this object identifies the input port of this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits), and is the same as the chanrInputPort, chanPort, pathPort, and portNumber.

pnniSpvcSrcCallingVPI.name: pnniSpvcSrcCallingVPI
pnniSpvcSrcCallingVPI.description: The VPI to be used at the Calling NI for this SPVC.

pnniSpvcSrcCallingVCI.name: pnniSpvcSrcCallingVCI
pnniSpvcSrcCallingVCI.description: The VCI to be used at the Calling NI SPVC.

pnniSpvcSrcCalledAtmAddr.name: pnniSpvcSrcCalledAtmAddr
pnniSpvcSrcCalledAtmAddr.description: The ATM address of the distant end NI (remote switch) for this SPVC.

pnniSpvcSrcCalledPort.name: pnniSpvcSrcCalledPort
pnniSpvcSrcCalledPort.description: The value of this object identifies the port of this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) at the destination end. It has a value of -1 if the port at the destination switch cannot be determined.

pnniSpvcSrcCalledVPVCSel.name: pnniSpvcSrcCalledVPVCSel
pnniSpvcSrcCalledVPVCSel.description: The Called VPI/VCI value selection qualifier.

pnniSpvcSrcCalledVPI.name: pnniSpvcSrcCalledVPI
pnniSpvcSrcCalledVPI.description: The VPI to be used at the Called NI for this SPVC.

pnniSpvcSrcCalledVCI.name: pnniSpvcSrcCalledVCI
pnniSpvcSrcCalledVCI.description: The VCI to be used at the Called NI for this SPVC.

pnniSpvcSrcCalledAssignedVPI.name: pnniSpvcSrcCalledAssignedVPI
pnniSpvcSrcCalledAssignedVPI.description: The VPI assigned at the Called NI for this SPVC. This value is only meaningful if the SPVC status is up.

pnniSpvcSrcCalledAssignedVCI.name: pnniSpvcSrcCalledAssignedVCI
pnniSpvcSrcCalledAssignedVCI.description: The VCI assigned at the Called NI for this SPVC. This value is only meaningful if the SPVC status is up.

pnniSpvcSrcFwdUpcKey.name: pnniSpvcSrcFwdUpcKey
pnniSpvcSrcFwdUpcKey.description: The forward UPC traffic contract key for this SPVC. This key must be defined in the upcContractTable.

pnniSpvcSrcBckUpcKey.name: pnniSpvcSrcBckUpcKey
pnniSpvcSrcBckUpcKey.description: The forward UPC traffic contract key for this SPVC. This key must be defined in the upcContractTable.

pnniSpvcSrcBearerClass.name: pnniSpvcSrcBearerClass
pnniSpvcSrcBearerClass.description: The requested broadband bearer class for this SPVC.

pnniSpvcSrcTrafficType.name: pnniSpvcSrcTrafficType
pnniSpvcSrcTrafficType.description: The requested broadband bearer traffic type for this SPVC.

pnniSpvcSrcTimingReq.name: pnniSpvcSrcTimingReq
pnniSpvcSrcTimingReq.description: The requested broadband bearer timing requirements for this SPVC.

pnniSpvcSrcSusceptClip.name: pnniSpvcSrcSusceptClip
pnniSpvcSrcSusceptClip.description: The requested broadband bearer susceptability to for this SPVC.

pnniSpvcSrcFwdQoSClass.name: pnniSpvcSrcFwdQoSClass
pnniSpvcSrcFwdQoSClass.description: The requested quality of service for this SPVC in the forward (calling to called) direction.

pnniSpvcSrcBckQoSClass.name: pnniSpvcSrcBckQoSClass
pnniSpvcSrcBckQoSClass.description: The requested quality of service for this SPVC in the backward (called to calling) direction.

pnniSpvcSrcTransitNetSel.name: pnniSpvcSrcTransitNetSel
pnniSpvcSrcTransitNetSel.description: The optional transit network selection for this SPVC.

pnniSpvcSrcLastFailCause.name: pnniSpvcSrcLastFailCause
pnniSpvcSrcLastFailCause.description: The last call setup failure cause code for this SPVC.

pnniSpvcSrcRetryCount.name: pnniSpvcSrcRetryCount
pnniSpvcSrcRetryCount.description: The number of times the call setup has been attempted since the SPVC creation or the last successful call setup.

pnniSpvcSrcLastChangeTime.name: pnniSpvcSrcLastChangeTime
pnniSpvcSrcLastChangeTime.description: The time since this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) has been up/down in hundredths of a second.

pnniSpvcSrcStatus.name: pnniSpvcSrcStatus
pnniSpvcSrcStatus.description: The operational status of this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuit).

pnniSpvcSrcName.name: pnniSpvcSrcName
pnniSpvcSrcName.description: The value of this object identifies the name that has been assigned for this SPVC.

pnniSpvcSrcEntryStatus.name: pnniSpvcSrcEntryStatus
pnniSpvcSrcEntryStatus.description: The status of this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) entry.

pnniSpvcSrcRouteCost.name: pnniSpvcSrcRouteCost
pnniSpvcSrcRouteCost.description: The cumulative route cost for the current route of this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits).

pnniSpvcSrcDtlIndex.name: pnniSpvcSrcDtlIndex
pnniSpvcSrcDtlIndex.description: The Designated Transit List (DTL) index for this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuit). This variable has been deprecated. Any writes to this variable will be treated as writes to pnniSpvcSrcDtlIndex1. This value must be defined in the ftPnniDTLTable. The DTL specifies a preferred call routing for the SVC portion of the SPVC.

pnniSpvcSrcActiveDtlIndex.name: pnniSpvcSrcActiveDtlIndex
pnniSpvcSrcActiveDtlIndex.description: The Active Designated Transit List (DTL) index for this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuit). This value along with pnniSpvcSrcActiveDtlNodeIndex uniquely identifies the DTL that is currently used by the SVC portion of the SPVC.

pnniSpvcSrcRerouteStatus.name: pnniSpvcSrcRerouteStatus
pnniSpvcSrcRerouteStatus.description: The status of the reroute function for this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuit). If set to disabled(2), no rerouting will be attempted for this SPVC.

pnniSpvcSrcCallingDomain.name: pnniSpvcSrcCallingDomain
pnniSpvcSrcCallingDomain.description: The Domain ID to be used at the Calling NI SPVC.

pnniSpvcSrcQosIndex.name: pnniSpvcSrcQosIndex
pnniSpvcSrcQosIndex.description: The index for the QOS Class Expansion Table to be used for this spvc.

pnniSpvcSrcDtlIndex1.name: pnniSpvcSrcDtlIndex1
pnniSpvcSrcDtlIndex1.description: The first Designated Transit List (DTL) index for this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuit). This value must be defined in the ftPnniDTLTable. The DTL specifies a preferred call routing for the SVC portion of the SPVC.

pnniSpvcSrcDtlIndex2.name: pnniSpvcSrcDtlIndex2
pnniSpvcSrcDtlIndex2.description: The second Designated Transit List (DTL) index for this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuit). This value must be defined in the ftPnniDTLTable. The DTL specifies a preferred call routing for the SVC portion of the SPVC.

pnniSpvcSrcDtlIndex3.name: pnniSpvcSrcDtlIndex3
pnniSpvcSrcDtlIndex3.description: The third Designated Transit List (DTL) index for this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuit). This value must be defined in the ftPnniDTLTable. The DTL specifies a preferred call routing for the SVC portion of the SPVC.

pnniSpvcSrcDtlIndex4.name: pnniSpvcSrcDtlIndex4
pnniSpvcSrcDtlIndex4.description: The fourth Designated Transit List (DTL) index for this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuit). This value must be defined in the ftPnniDTLTable. The DTL specifies a preferred call routing for the SVC portion of the SPVC.

pnniSpvcSrcDtlWeight1.name: pnniSpvcSrcDtlWeight1
pnniSpvcSrcDtlWeight1.description: The weight of the first Designated Transit List (DTL) index for this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuit). The weight specifies the priority of this DTL index among the four DTL indices that can be specified for a particular SPVC.

pnniSpvcSrcDtlWeight2.name: pnniSpvcSrcDtlWeight2
pnniSpvcSrcDtlWeight2.description: The weight of the second Designated Transit List (DTL) index for this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuit). The weight specifies the priority of this DTL index among the four DTL indices that can be specified for a particular SPVC.

pnniSpvcSrcDtlWeight3.name: pnniSpvcSrcDtlWeight3
pnniSpvcSrcDtlWeight3.description: The weight of the third Designated Transit List (DTL) index for this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuit). The weight specifies the priority of this DTL index among the four DTL indices that can be specified for a particular SPVC.

pnniSpvcSrcDtlWeight4.name: pnniSpvcSrcDtlWeight4
pnniSpvcSrcDtlWeight4.description: The weight of the fourth Designated Transit List (DTL) index for this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuit). The weight specifies the priority of this DTL index among the four DTL indices that can be specified for a particular SPVC.

pnniSpvcSrcBackoffStatus.name: pnniSpvcSrcBackoffStatus
pnniSpvcSrcBackoffStatus.description: The status of the backoff function for this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuit). If set to disabled(2), directed dtls configured for this SPVC will be continually retried on failure.

pnniSpvcSrcPriority.name: pnniSpvcSrcPriority
pnniSpvcSrcPriority.description: Priority of this SPVCC for connection

pnniSpvcSrcLastLocation.name: pnniSpvcSrcLastLocation
pnniSpvcSrcLastLocation.description: The last call setup failure location code for this SPVC. This indicates the switch that initiated the clearing for the call. This is formatted as a text string with the fields: FMT: Indicates diagnostic format RMT: Indicates whether a remote switch is the source of the failure or this switch inserted the location diag LINK:Link id that clear pertains to VPI: VPI that clear pertains to The remaining fields are format specific

pnniSpvcSrcOldRouteCost.name: pnniSpvcSrcOldRouteCost
pnniSpvcSrcOldRouteCost.description: This OID is specified only to be included the the pnniSpvcUp trap. It specifies the path cost of the call the previous time this call was up. If the call has not been up, this will report a value of -1.

pnniSpvcSrcDownReason.name: pnniSpvcSrcDownReason
pnniSpvcSrcDownReason.description: This OID is specified only to be included the the pnniSpvccDown and pnniSpvccFail traps. This specifies whether the SPVC call was cleared due to a better route being found, a network failure, or SPVC deletion.

pnniSpvcSrcActiveDtlNodeIndex.name: pnniSpvcSrcActiveDtlNodeIndex
pnniSpvcSrcActiveDtlNodeIndex.description: The Node index of the Active Designated Transit List for this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuit). The active DTL indexed by the node index and DTL index identifies the DTL that is currently used by the SVC portion of the SPVC. The value of this object is 65535 for FTPNNI nodes.

pnniSpvcSrcDtlTag.name: pnniSpvcSrcDtlTag
pnniSpvcSrcDtlTag.description: This value specifies an index into a table of DTLs, the DTL entries in this table will be used to setup the SPVC.

pnniSpvcSrcAutoDtlStatus.name: pnniSpvcSrcAutoDtlStatus
pnniSpvcSrcAutoDtlStatus.description: The status of the dynamic path selection function for this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuit). If set to disabled(2), auto path selection will not be used.

pnniSpvcSrcRGroupIndex.name: pnniSpvcSrcRGroupIndex
pnniSpvcSrcRGroupIndex.description: This specifies the entry in the Spvxc Redundancy Group table for information regarding the secondary port to be used as the redundant port

pnniSpvcSrcSecondaryVPI.name: pnniSpvcSrcSecondaryVPI
pnniSpvcSrcSecondaryVPI.description: The Secondary VPI to be used at the originating switch for the redundant permanent portion of this SPVC.

pnniSpvcSrcSecondaryVCI.name: pnniSpvcSrcSecondaryVCI
pnniSpvcSrcSecondaryVCI.description: The Secondary VCI to be used at the originating switch for the redundant permanent portion of this SPVC.

pnniSpvcDestNumberOfSPVCs.name: pnniSpvcDestNumberOfSPVCs
pnniSpvcDestNumberOfSPVCs.description: The number of connected SPVCs (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) that have their destination at this switch.

pnniSpvcDestTable.name: pnniSpvcDestTable
pnniSpvcDestTable.description: This table contains information about SPVCs (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) that have their destination at this switch.

pnniSpvcDestEntry.name: pnniSpvcDestEntry
pnniSpvcDestEntry.description: A table entry containing destination SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) information.

pnniSpvcDestIndex.name: pnniSpvcDestIndex
pnniSpvcDestIndex.description: The value of this object uniquely identify the SPVCs (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) that have this switch as their source.

pnniSpvcDestCallingAtmAddr.name: pnniSpvcDestCallingAtmAddr
pnniSpvcDestCallingAtmAddr.description: The ATM address of the local end NI (on this switch) for this SPVC.

pnniSpvcDestCallingPort.name: pnniSpvcDestCallingPort
pnniSpvcDestCallingPort.description: The value of this object identifies the port of this terminating SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) at the source end. It has a value of -1 if the port at the destination switch cannot be determined.

pnniSpvcDestCallingVPI.name: pnniSpvcDestCallingVPI
pnniSpvcDestCallingVPI.description: The VPI to be used at the Calling NI for this SPVC.

pnniSpvcDestCallingVCI.name: pnniSpvcDestCallingVCI
pnniSpvcDestCallingVCI.description: The VCI to be used at the Calling NI for this SPVC.

pnniSpvcDestCalledAtmAddr.name: pnniSpvcDestCalledAtmAddr
pnniSpvcDestCalledAtmAddr.description: The ATM address of the distant end NI (remote switch) for this SPVC.

pnniSpvcDestCalledPort.name: pnniSpvcDestCalledPort
pnniSpvcDestCalledPort.description: The value of this object identifies the port of this terminating SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) at the destination end. It has a value os -1 if the port at the destination switch cannot be determined.

pnniSpvcDestAssignedVPI.name: pnniSpvcDestAssignedVPI
pnniSpvcDestAssignedVPI.description: The VPI assigned at the Called NI for this SPVC. This value is only meaningful if the SPVC status is up.

pnniSpvcDestAssignedVCI.name: pnniSpvcDestAssignedVCI
pnniSpvcDestAssignedVCI.description: The VCI assigned at the Called NI for this SPVC. This value is only meaningful if the SPVC status is up.

pnniSpvcDestBearerClass.name: pnniSpvcDestBearerClass
pnniSpvcDestBearerClass.description: The broadband bearer class for this SPVC.

pnniSpvcDestTrafficType.name: pnniSpvcDestTrafficType
pnniSpvcDestTrafficType.description: The broadband bearer traffic type for this SPVC.

pnniSpvcDestTimingReq.name: pnniSpvcDestTimingReq
pnniSpvcDestTimingReq.description: The broadband bearer timing requirements for this SPVC.

pnniSpvcDestSusceptClip.name: pnniSpvcDestSusceptClip
pnniSpvcDestSusceptClip.description: The broadband bearer susceptability to clipping for this SPVC.

pnniSpvcDestUpTime.name: pnniSpvcDestUpTime
pnniSpvcDestUpTime.description: The time since this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) was created in hundredths of a second.

pnniSpvcDestFwdQoSClass.name: pnniSpvcDestFwdQoSClass
pnniSpvcDestFwdQoSClass.description: The requested quality of service for this SPVC in the forward (calling to called) direction.

pnniSpvcDestBckQoSClass.name: pnniSpvcDestBckQoSClass
pnniSpvcDestBckQoSClass.description: The requested quality of service for this SPVC in the backward (called to calling) direction.

pnniSpvcDestTransitNetSel.name: pnniSpvcDestTransitNetSel
pnniSpvcDestTransitNetSel.description: The optional transit network selection for this SPVC.

pnniSpvcDestStatus.name: pnniSpvcDestStatus
pnniSpvcDestStatus.description: The operational status of this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuit).

pnniSpvcDestRGroupIndex.name: pnniSpvcDestRGroupIndex
pnniSpvcDestRGroupIndex.description: This specifies the entry in the Spvxc Redundancy Group table for information regarding the secondary port to be used as the redundant port. This will used at the terminating PVC end.

pnniSpvcPaceInterval.name: pnniSpvcPaceInterval
pnniSpvcPaceInterval.description: The time interval between successive callbacks to the SPVC controller to open to the destinations of a batch of SPVCs

pnniSpvcPaceNumSpvcs.name: pnniSpvcPaceNumSpvcs
pnniSpvcPaceNumSpvcs.description: The max number of SPVCs that each batch of SPVCs that the SPVC controller tries to open to per pnniSpvcPaceInterval

pnniSpvcRerouteInterval.name: pnniSpvcRerouteInterval
pnniSpvcRerouteInterval.description: The time interval between successive callbacks to the SPVC controller to reroute existing SPVC connection if a better path is available to the destination

pnniSpvcRerouteNumSpvcs.name: pnniSpvcRerouteNumSpvcs
pnniSpvcRerouteNumSpvcs.description: The number of SPVCs that are attempted to be rerouted by the SPVC controller per pnniSpvcRerouteInterval

pnniSpvcRerouteThreshold.name: pnniSpvcRerouteThreshold
pnniSpvcRerouteThreshold.description: The percentage improvement in the cost that the new SPVC path must have over the current SPVC path before a reroute will be performed.

pnniSpvcLowestPriority.name: pnniSpvcLowestPriority
pnniSpvcLowestPriority.description: The value of lowest priority for SPVCCs

pnniSpvcDefaultUbrBandwidth.name: pnniSpvcDefaultUbrBandwidth
pnniSpvcDefaultUbrBandwidth.description: The default bandwidth in Kilo-CPS to be used for UBR SPVCs

pnniSpvcBackoffInterval.name: pnniSpvcBackoffInterval
pnniSpvcBackoffInterval.description: The time interval to backoff a DTL that failed call setup. The DTL will not be used again until this interval has elapsed. The interval will not be applicable if backoff is disabled on the SPVC.

pnniSpvcTrapMode.name: pnniSpvcTrapMode
pnniSpvcTrapMode.description: This configuration item specifies whether the switch should send the: spvcRerouteInitiated OR pnniSpvccUp and pnniSpvccFail OR pnniSpvccDown, pnniSpvccFail, and pnniSpvccUp traps.

pnniPmpSpvcPartyPaceNum.name: pnniPmpSpvcPartyPaceNum
pnniPmpSpvcPartyPaceNum.description: The maximum number parties within a PMP SPVC that are activated per SpvcPacingInterval.

pnniSpvpcPaceInterval.name: pnniSpvpcPaceInterval
pnniSpvpcPaceInterval.description: The time interval between successive callbacks to the SPVPC controller to open connections to the destinations of a batch of SPVPCs. This parameter along with pnniSpvpcPaceNumSpvpcs control the rate at which the SPVPCs that are down are established. Analogous SPVCC variable is pnniSpvcPaceInterval.

pnniSpvpcPaceNumSpvpcs.name: pnniSpvpcPaceNumSpvpcs
