pnniSpvpcPaceNumSpvpcs.description: The max number of SPVPCs that the SPVPC controller tries to activate per pnniSpvpcPaceInterval. This controls the rate at which SPVPCs that are down are established. The corresponding SPVCC variable is pnniSpvcPaceNumSpvcs.

pnniSpvpcRerouteInterval.name: pnniSpvpcRerouteInterval
pnniSpvpcRerouteInterval.description: The time interval between successive callbacks to the SPVPC controller to reroute existing SPVPC connections if a better path is available to the destination. This is one of the parameters that control the rate at which rerouting is attempted. The analogous SPVCC variable is pnniSpvcRerouteInterval.

pnniSpvpcRerouteNumSpvpcs.name: pnniSpvpcRerouteNumSpvpcs
pnniSpvpcRerouteNumSpvpcs.description: The number of SPVPCs that are attempted to be rerouted by the SPVPC controller per pnniSpvpcRerouteInterval. Thus it determines the rerouting rate. The analogous SPVCC variable is pnniSpvcRerouteNumSpvcs.

pnniSpvpcRerouteThreshold.name: pnniSpvpcRerouteThreshold
pnniSpvpcRerouteThreshold.description: The percentage improvement in the cost that the new SPVPC path must have over the current SPVPC path before a reroute will be performed. This is analogous to the pnniSpvcRerouteThreshold variable for SPVCCs.

pnniSpvpcLowestPriority.name: pnniSpvpcLowestPriority
pnniSpvpcLowestPriority.description: The value of lowest priority for SPVPCs

pnniSpvpcTrapMode.name: pnniSpvpcTrapMode
pnniSpvpcTrapMode.description: This configuration item specifies whether the switch should send the: spvcRerouteInitiated OR pnniSpvpcUp and pnniSpvpcFail OR pnniSpvpcDown, pnniSpvpcFail, and pnniSpvpcUp traps.

pnniSpvpcBackoffInterval.name: pnniSpvpcBackoffInterval
pnniSpvpcBackoffInterval.description: The time interval to backoff a DTL that failed call setup. The DTL will not be used again until this interval has elapsed. The interval will not be applicable if backoff is disabled on the SPVPC.

pnniSpvpcSrcTable.name: pnniSpvpcSrcTable
pnniSpvpcSrcTable.description: This table contains information about SPVPCs (Smart Permanent Virtual Path Connections) that have their source at this switch. This table serves the same function that the pnniSpvcSrcTable serves for SPVCCs.

pnniSpvpcSrcEntry.name: pnniSpvpcSrcEntry
pnniSpvpcSrcEntry.description: A table entry containing source SPVPC (Smart Permanent Virtual Path Connection) information.

pnniSpvpcSrcIndex.name: pnniSpvpcSrcIndex
pnniSpvpcSrcIndex.description: The value of this object uniquely identify the SPVPCs (Smart Permanent Virtual Path Connections) that have this switch as their source.

pnniSpvpcSrcCallingPort.name: pnniSpvpcSrcCallingPort
pnniSpvpcSrcCallingPort.description: The value of this object identifies the input port of this SPVPC (Smart Permanent Virtual Path Connection), and is the same as the chanrInputPort, chanPort, pathPort, and portNumber. The maximum value of this variable depends on the type of the switch. The upper bound given is the highest possible as of now. In some switches the range will be much narrower.

pnniSpvpcSrcCallingVPI.name: pnniSpvpcSrcCallingVPI
pnniSpvpcSrcCallingVPI.description: The VPI to be used at the originating switch for the permanent portion of this SPVPC (Smart Permanent Virtual Path Connection).

pnniSpvpcSrcCalledAtmAddr.name: pnniSpvpcSrcCalledAtmAddr
pnniSpvpcSrcCalledAtmAddr.description: The ATM address of the distant end NI (destination switch) for this SPVPC (Smart Permanent Virtual Path Connection). Distant end NI is the network interface at the destination switch at which the switched portion of this SPVPC terminates.

pnniSpvpcSrcCalledPort.name: pnniSpvpcSrcCalledPort
pnniSpvpcSrcCalledPort.description: The value of this object identifies the port where the permanent portion of this SPVPC (Smart Permanent Virtual Path Connection) resides at the destination switch. It has a value of -1 if this port at the destination switch cannot be determined.

pnniSpvpcSrcCalledVPVCSel.name: pnniSpvpcSrcCalledVPVCSel
pnniSpvpcSrcCalledVPVCSel.description: The originating switch for a SPVPC can specify the VPI to be used for the permanent portion of this SPVPC at the destination switch. The value of this object indicates whether the SPVPC was configured with a specific value for this VPI or not. require(2) indicates that the user configured a specific value for this VPI and noPref(1) indicates that the user did not specify any.

pnniSpvpcSrcCalledVPI.name: pnniSpvpcSrcCalledVPI
pnniSpvpcSrcCalledVPI.description: The VPI to be used at the destination switch for the permanent portion of this SPVPC (Smart Permanent Virtual Path Connection). The range given above is the maximum possible. The upperbound varies with the type of netmod.

pnniSpvpcSrcCalledAssignedVPI.name: pnniSpvpcSrcCalledAssignedVPI
pnniSpvpcSrcCalledAssignedVPI.description: The VPI that is assigned at the destination switch for the permanent portion of this SPVPC (Smart Permanent Virtual Path Connection). This value is only meaningful if the SPVPC status is up.

pnniSpvpcSrcFwdUpcKey.name: pnniSpvpcSrcFwdUpcKey
pnniSpvpcSrcFwdUpcKey.description: The forward UPC traffic contract key for this SPVPC. This traffic contract will be used for the data traffic flow from the originating switch to the destination switch. This key must be defined in the upcContractTable.

pnniSpvpcSrcBckUpcKey.name: pnniSpvpcSrcBckUpcKey
pnniSpvpcSrcBckUpcKey.description: The backward UPC traffic contract key for this SPVPC. This traffic contract will be used for the data flow in the direction from the destination switch to the originating switch. This key must be defined in the upcContractTable.

pnniSpvpcSrcSusceptClip.name: pnniSpvpcSrcSusceptClip
pnniSpvpcSrcSusceptClip.description: The requested broadband bearer susceptibility to clipping for this SPVPC. This object will be used to fill the broadband bearer capability information element in the call setup message for this SPVPC.

pnniSpvpcSrcFwdQoSClass.name: pnniSpvpcSrcFwdQoSClass
pnniSpvpcSrcFwdQoSClass.description: The requested quality of service class for this SPVPC in the forward (source to destination) direction. This determines the QoS objectives for the data path from the originating switch to the destination switch.

pnniSpvpcSrcBckQoSClass.name: pnniSpvpcSrcBckQoSClass
pnniSpvpcSrcBckQoSClass.description: The requested quality of service class for this SPVPC in the backward (destination to source) direction. This object determines the QoS objectives for the data flow in the reverse direction (from the destination switch to the originating switch).

pnniSpvpcSrcLastFailCause.name: pnniSpvpcSrcLastFailCause
pnniSpvpcSrcLastFailCause.description: The last call setup failure cause code for this SPVPC.

pnniSpvpcSrcRetryCount.name: pnniSpvpcSrcRetryCount
pnniSpvpcSrcRetryCount.description: The number of times the call setup has been attempted since the SPVPC creation or the last successful call setup for this SPVPC.

pnniSpvpcSrcLastChangeTime.name: pnniSpvpcSrcLastChangeTime
pnniSpvpcSrcLastChangeTime.description: The time since this SPVPC (Smart Permanent Virtual Path Connection) has been up/down in hundredths of a second.

pnniSpvpcSrcStatus.name: pnniSpvpcSrcStatus
pnniSpvpcSrcStatus.description: The operational status of this SPVPC (Smart Permanent Virtual Path Connection). The value of up(1) indicates that this SPVPC is operational and down(2) indicates that the SPVPC is not-operational.

pnniSpvpcSrcName.name: pnniSpvpcSrcName
pnniSpvpcSrcName.description: The value of this object identifies the name that has been assigned for this SPVPC.

pnniSpvpcSrcRowStatus.name: pnniSpvpcSrcRowStatus
pnniSpvpcSrcRowStatus.description: The status of this SPVPC (Smart Permanent Virtual Path Connection) entry.

pnniSpvpcSrcRouteCost.name: pnniSpvpcSrcRouteCost
pnniSpvpcSrcRouteCost.description: The cumulative route cost for the current route of this SPVPC (Smart Permanent Virtual Path Connection).

pnniSpvpcSrcRerouteStatus.name: pnniSpvpcSrcRerouteStatus
pnniSpvpcSrcRerouteStatus.description: The status of the reroute function for this SPVPC (Smart Permanent Virtual Path Connection). If set to disabled(2), no rerouting will be attempted for this SPVPC.

pnniSpvpcSrcCallingDomain.name: pnniSpvpcSrcCallingDomain
pnniSpvpcSrcCallingDomain.description: The Domain ID identifying the routing domain to be used at the Originating Switch for this SPVPC.

pnniSpvpcSrcQosIndex.name: pnniSpvpcSrcQosIndex
pnniSpvpcSrcQosIndex.description: The index for the QOS Class Expansion Table to be used for QoS class values into QoS parameter objectives for this SPVPC. The corresponding expansion table should be defined in the qosClassExpansionTable.

pnniSpvpcSrcPriority.name: pnniSpvpcSrcPriority
pnniSpvpcSrcPriority.description: Priority of this SPVPC for connection

pnniSpvpcSrcLastLocation.name: pnniSpvpcSrcLastLocation
pnniSpvpcSrcLastLocation.description: The last call setup failure location code for this SPVPC. This indicates the switch that initiated the clearing for the call. This is formatted as a text string with the fields: FMT: Indicates diagnostic format RMT: Indicates whether a remote switch is the source of the failure or this switch inserted the location diag LINK:Link id that clear pertains to VPI: VPI that clear pertains to The remaining fields are format specific

pnniSpvpcSrcOldRouteCost.name: pnniSpvpcSrcOldRouteCost
pnniSpvpcSrcOldRouteCost.description: This OID is specified only to be included the the pnniSpvcUp trap. It specifies the path cost of the call the previous time this call was up. If the call has not been up, this will report a value of -1.

pnniSpvpcSrcDownReason.name: pnniSpvpcSrcDownReason
pnniSpvpcSrcDownReason.description: This OID is specified only to be included the the pnniSpvccDown and pnniSpvccFail traps. This specifies whether the SPVC call was cleared due to a better route being found, a network failure, or SPVPC deletion.

pnniSpvpcSrcBackoffStatus.name: pnniSpvpcSrcBackoffStatus
pnniSpvpcSrcBackoffStatus.description: The status of the backoff function for this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Path Circuit). If set to disabled(2), directed dtls configured for this SPVPC will be continually retried on failure.

pnniSpvpcSrcActiveDtlIndex.name: pnniSpvpcSrcActiveDtlIndex
pnniSpvpcSrcActiveDtlIndex.description: The Active Designated Transit List (DTL) index for this SPVPC (Smart Permanent Virtual Path Circuit). This value along with pnniSpvcSrcActiveDtlNodeIndex uniquely identifies the DTL that is currently used by the SVC portion of the SPVPC.

pnniSpvpcSrcActiveDtlNodeIndex.name: pnniSpvpcSrcActiveDtlNodeIndex
pnniSpvpcSrcActiveDtlNodeIndex.description: The Node index of the Active Designated Transit List for this SPVPC (Smart Permanent Virtual Path Circuit). The active DTL indexed by the node index and DTL index identifies the DTL that is currently used by the SVC portion of the SPVPC. The value of this object is 65535 for FTPNNI nodes.

pnniSpvpcSrcDtlTag.name: pnniSpvpcSrcDtlTag
pnniSpvpcSrcDtlTag.description: This value specifies an index into a table of DTLs, the DTL entries in this table will be used to setup the SPVPC.

pnniSpvpcSrcAutoDtlStatus.name: pnniSpvpcSrcAutoDtlStatus
pnniSpvpcSrcAutoDtlStatus.description: The status of the dynamic path selection function for this SPVPC (Smart Permanent Virtual Path Circuit). If set to disabled(2), auto path selection will not be used.

pnniSpvpcSrcRGroupIndex.name: pnniSpvpcSrcRGroupIndex
pnniSpvpcSrcRGroupIndex.description: This specifies the entry in the Spvxc Redundancy Group table for information regarding the secondary port to be used as the redundant port

pnniSpvpcSrcSecondaryVPI.name: pnniSpvpcSrcSecondaryVPI
pnniSpvpcSrcSecondaryVPI.description: The Secondary VPI to be used at the originating switch for the redundant permanent portion of this SPVPC.

pnniSpvpcSrcNumberOfSPVPCs.name: pnniSpvpcSrcNumberOfSPVPCs
pnniSpvpcSrcNumberOfSPVPCs.description: The number of SPVPCs (Smart Permanent Virtual Path Connections) that have their source at this switch. This object is analogous to the pnniSpvcSrcNumberOfSPVCs object defined for SPVCCs.

pnniSpvpcDestNumberOfSPVPCs.name: pnniSpvpcDestNumberOfSPVPCs
pnniSpvpcDestNumberOfSPVPCs.description: The number of connected SPVPCs (Smart Permanent Virtual Path Connections) that have their destination at this switch. This object is analogous to the pnniSpvcDestNumberOfSPVCs object for SPVCCs.

pnniSpvpcDestTable.name: pnniSpvpcDestTable
pnniSpvpcDestTable.description: This table contains information about SPVPCs (Smart Permanent Virtual Path Connections) that have their destination at this switch. This table provides the same functions that the pnniSpvcDestTable provides for SPVCCs.

pnniSpvpcDestEntry.name: pnniSpvpcDestEntry
pnniSpvpcDestEntry.description: A table entry containing destination SPVPC (Smart Permanent Virtual Path Connection) information.

pnniSpvpcDestIndex.name: pnniSpvpcDestIndex
pnniSpvpcDestIndex.description: The value of this object uniquely identifies the SPVPCs (Smart Permanent Virtual Path Connections) that have this switch as their destination.

pnniSpvpcDestCallingAtmAddr.name: pnniSpvpcDestCallingAtmAddr
pnniSpvpcDestCallingAtmAddr.description: The ATM address of the calling end NI at the originating switch for this SPVPC (Smart Permanent Virtual Path Connection). Calling end NI is the network interface at the originating switch from which the switched portion of SPVPC originates.

pnniSpvpcDestCallingPort.name: pnniSpvpcDestCallingPort
pnniSpvpcDestCallingPort.description: The value of this object identifies the port of this terminating SPVPC (Smart Permanent Virtual Path Connection) at the source switch in which the permanent portion of the SPVPC resides. It has a value of -1 if the port at the source switch cannot be determined.

pnniSpvpcDestCallingVPI.name: pnniSpvpcDestCallingVPI
pnniSpvpcDestCallingVPI.description: The VPI to be used at the originating switch for the permanent portion of this SPVPC.

pnniSpvpcDestCalledAtmAddr.name: pnniSpvpcDestCalledAtmAddr
pnniSpvpcDestCalledAtmAddr.description: The ATM address of the local end NI (at this destination switch) for this SPVPC. Local end NI is network interface at this destination switch where the switched portion of this SPVPC terminates.

pnniSpvpcDestCalledPort.name: pnniSpvpcDestCalledPort
pnniSpvpcDestCalledPort.description: The value of this object identifies the port of this terminating SPVPC (Smart Permanent Virtual Path Connection) at this destination switch where the permanent portion of this SPVPC resides. It has a value of -1 if the port at the destination switch cannot be determined.

pnniSpvpcDestAssignedVPI.name: pnniSpvpcDestAssignedVPI
pnniSpvpcDestAssignedVPI.description: The VPI assigned at this destination switch for the permanent portion of this SPVPC. This value is only meaningful if the SPVPC status is up.

pnniSpvpcDestSusceptClip.name: pnniSpvpcDestSusceptClip
pnniSpvpcDestSusceptClip.description: The value of this object identifies if the SPVPC was setup with the broadband bearer susceptibility to clipping set or not.

pnniSpvpcDestUpTime.name: pnniSpvpcDestUpTime
pnniSpvpcDestUpTime.description: The time since this SPVPC (Smart Permanent Virtual Path Connection) was created in hundredths of a second.

pnniSpvpcDestFwdQoSClass.name: pnniSpvpcDestFwdQoSClass
pnniSpvpcDestFwdQoSClass.description: The requested quality of service class for this SPVPC in the direction from the source switch to the destination switch. This value determines the QoS parameter objectives for this SPVPC in that direction.

pnniSpvpcDestBckQoSClass.name: pnniSpvpcDestBckQoSClass
pnniSpvpcDestBckQoSClass.description: The requested quality of service class for this SPVPC in the direction from the destination switch to the source switch. This value determines the QoS objectives for the data flow in that direction.

pnniSpvpcDestStatus.name: pnniSpvpcDestStatus
pnniSpvpcDestStatus.description: The operational status of this SPVPC (Smart Permanent Virtual Path Connection). up(1) indicates that this SPVPC is operational while down(2) indicates that it is not.

pnniSpvpcDestRGroupIndex.name: pnniSpvpcDestRGroupIndex
pnniSpvpcDestRGroupIndex.description: This specifies the entry in the Spvxc Redundancy Group table for information regarding the secondary port to be used as the redundant port. This will used at the terminating PVC end.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcNextRootIndex.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcNextRootIndex
pnniPmpSpvccSrcNextRootIndex.description: The index of the next free root index in the pnniPmpSpvcSrcRootTable. Client is responsible for implementing a policy when a set on this variable fails. E.g. Keep testing this variable until a free index is found or choose a random number or a combination of the two.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcNumberOfSpvccs.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcNumberOfSpvccs
pnniPmpSpvccSrcNumberOfSpvccs.description: The number of PMP SPVCCs (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) that have their source at this switch.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootTable.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootTable
pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootTable.description: This table contains information about the root side of PMP SPVCCs (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) that have their source at this switch. It also contains the connection parameters that are common to all the parties

pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootEntry.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootEntry
pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootEntry.description: A table entry containing source PMP SPVCC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) information.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootIndex.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootIndex
pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootIndex.description: The value of this object uniquely identify the PMP SPVCCs (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) that have this switch as their source(root).

pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootPort.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootPort
pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootPort.description: The value of this object identifies the input port of this PMP SPVCC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits), and is the same as the chanrInputPort, chanPort, pathPort, and portNumber.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootVPI.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootVPI
pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootVPI.description: The VPI to be used at the Calling(root) NI for this PMP SPVCC.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootVCI.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootVCI
pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootVCI.description: The VCI to be used at the Calling(root) NI for this PMP SPVCC.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootFwdUpcKey.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootFwdUpcKey
pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootFwdUpcKey.description: The forward UPC traffic contract key for this PMP SPVCC. This key must be defined in the upcContractTable. Backward UPC traffic contract does not apply to PMP SPVCCs.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootBearerClass.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootBearerClass
pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootBearerClass.description: The requested broadband bearer class for this PMP SPVCC.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootSusceptClip.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootSusceptClip
pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootSusceptClip.description: The requested broadband bearer susceptability to for this PMP SPVCC.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootFwdQoSClass.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootFwdQoSClass
pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootFwdQoSClass.description: The requested quality of service for this PMP SPVCC in the forward (calling to called) direction. Backward direction does not apply to PMP SPVCCs.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootStatus.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootStatus
pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootStatus.description: The operational status of this PMP SPVCC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuit).

pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootName.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootName
pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootName.description: The value of this object identifies the name that has been assigned for this PMP SPVCC.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootPriority.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootPriority
pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootPriority.description: Priority of this PMP SPVCC for connection. This priority is shared with any point-to-point SPVCCs configured on this switch.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootNumberOfParties.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootNumberOfParties
pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootNumberOfParties.description: Number of parties currently configured with this PMP SPVCC

pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootNextPartyIndex.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootNextPartyIndex
pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootNextPartyIndex.description: This indicates the next allocatable party index

pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootCallingDomain.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootCallingDomain
pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootCallingDomain.description: The Domain ID to be used at the Calling NI for this PMP SPVCC.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootRowStatus.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootRowStatus
pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootRowStatus.description: The status of this SPVCC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) entry.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootRGroupIndex.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootRGroupIndex
pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootRGroupIndex.description: This specifies the entry in the Spvxc Redundancy Group table for information regarding the secondary port to be used as the redundant port

pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootSecondaryVPI.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootSecondaryVPI
pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootSecondaryVPI.description: The Secondary VPI to be used at the originating switch for the redundant permanent portion of this SPVC.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootSecondaryVCI.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootSecondaryVCI
pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootSecondaryVCI.description: The Secondary VCI to be used at the originating switch for the redundant permanent portion of this SPVC.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyTable.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyTable
pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyTable.description: This table contains information about the parties of PMP SPVCCs (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) that have their source at this switch.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyEntry.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyEntry
pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyEntry.description: A table entry containing information about parties in a PMP SPVCC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) at the source.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyIndex.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyIndex
pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyIndex.description: The value of this object uniquely identifies a party within a PMP SPVCC identified by pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootIndex. Root's parameters and commmon connection parameters for this party are availabe in pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootTable, indexed by pnniPmpSpvccSrcRootIndex.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyAtmAddr.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyAtmAddr
pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyAtmAddr.description: The ATM address of the distant end NI (remote switch) for this party.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyVPVCSel.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyVPVCSel
pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyVPVCSel.description: The Called VPI/VCI value selection qualifier.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyVPI.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyVPI
pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyVPI.description: The VPI to be used at the Called NI for this party.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyVCI.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyVCI
pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyVCI.description: The VCI to be used at the Called NI for this party.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyAssignedVPI.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyAssignedVPI
pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyAssignedVPI.description: The VPI assigned at the Called NI for this party. This value is only meaningful if the party status is up.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyAssignedVCI.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyAssignedVCI
pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyAssignedVCI.description: The VCI assigned at the Called NI for this party. This value is only meaningful if the party status is up.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyStatus.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyStatus
pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyStatus.description: Operational status of this party in the PMP SPVCC.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyName.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyName
pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyName.description: The value of this object identifies the name that has been assigned for this party.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyLastFailCause.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyLastFailCause
pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyLastFailCause.description: The last setup(addparty) failure cause code for this party.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyRetryCount.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyRetryCount
pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyRetryCount.description: The number of times the party setup/addparty has been attempted since the party creation or the last successful setup/addparty.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyLastChangeTime.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyLastChangeTime
pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyLastChangeTime.description: The time since this party has been up/down in hundredths of a second.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyFtDtlIndex.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyFtDtlIndex
pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyFtDtlIndex.description: The Designated Transit List (DTL) index for this party. This value must be defined in the ftPnniDTLTable. The DTL specifies a preferred call routing for the SVC portion of the party. If a DTL is specified, this party will not be rerouted when rerouting is requested administratively.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyRerouteStatus.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyRerouteStatus
pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyRerouteStatus.description: The status of the reroute function for this party. Rerouting can be administratively requested, for active parties, by setting this variable to reroute_requested(2). On successful completion of rerouting, it will be set to reroute_completed(3). When a DTL is specified for a party, rerouting will not be performed for that party and this variable will set to reroute_not_applicable.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyQosIndex.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyQosIndex
pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyQosIndex.description: The index for the QOS Class Expansion Table to be used for this PMP SPVCC.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyRowStatus.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyRowStatus
pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyRowStatus.description: The status of this party entry.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyLastLocation.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyLastLocation
pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyLastLocation.description: The last call setup failure location code for this SPVC. This indicates the switch that initiated the clearing for the call. This is formatted as a text string with the fields: FMT: Indicates diagnostic format RMT: Indicates whether a remote switch is the source of the failure or this switch inserted the location diag LINK:Link id that clear pertains to VPI: VPI that clear pertains to The remaining fields are format specific

pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyAutoDtlStatus.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyAutoDtlStatus
pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyAutoDtlStatus.description: The status of the dynamic path selection function for this SPVC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuit). If set to disabled(2), auto path selection will not be used.

pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyDownReason.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyDownReason
pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyDownReason.description: The reason for the spvc down is set accordingly

pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyRouteCost.name: pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyRouteCost
pnniPmpSpvccSrcPartyRouteCost.description: The link cost associated for the party isset here

pnniPmpSpvccDestNumberOfSpvccs.name: pnniPmpSpvccDestNumberOfSpvccs
pnniPmpSpvccDestNumberOfSpvccs.description: The number of connected PMP SPVCCs (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) that have their parties terminating at this switch.

pnniPmpSpvccDestRootTable.name: pnniPmpSpvccDestRootTable
pnniPmpSpvccDestRootTable.description: This table contains information about the root of PMP SPVCCs (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) that have their parties terminating at this switch.

pnniPmpSpvccDestRootEntry.name: pnniPmpSpvccDestRootEntry
pnniPmpSpvccDestRootEntry.description: A table entry containing destination SPVCC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) information.

pnniPmpSpvccDestRootIndex.name: pnniPmpSpvccDestRootIndex
pnniPmpSpvccDestRootIndex.description: The value of this object uniquely identifies the PMP SPVCCs (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) that has one or more parties terminating at this switch.

pnniPmpSpvccDestRootAtmAddr.name: pnniPmpSpvccDestRootAtmAddr
pnniPmpSpvccDestRootAtmAddr.description: The ATM address of the root of the PMP SPVCC that has one or more parties terminating at this switch.

pnniPmpSpvccDestRootPort.name: pnniPmpSpvccDestRootPort
pnniPmpSpvccDestRootPort.description: The value of this object identifies the port of this terminating PMP SPVCC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) at the source end. It has a value of -1 if the port at the destination switch cannot be determined.

pnniPmpSpvccDestRootVPI.name: pnniPmpSpvccDestRootVPI
pnniPmpSpvccDestRootVPI.description: The VPI used for the PVCC portion of the connection at the root of the PMP SPVCC. The root switch is identified by pnniPmpSpvccDestCallingAtmAddr.

pnniPmpSpvccDestRootVCI.name: pnniPmpSpvccDestRootVCI
pnniPmpSpvccDestRootVCI.description: The VCI used for the PVCC portion of the connection at the root of the PMP SPVCC. The root switch is identified by pnniPmpSpvccDestCallingAtmAddr.

pnniPmpSpvccDestRootBearerClass.name: pnniPmpSpvccDestRootBearerClass
pnniPmpSpvccDestRootBearerClass.description: The broadband bearer class signalled for the first party of this PMP SPVCC. All subsequent parties should have the same value.

pnniPmpSpvccDestRootSusceptClip.name: pnniPmpSpvccDestRootSusceptClip
pnniPmpSpvccDestRootSusceptClip.description: The broadband bearer susceptability to clipping signalled for the first party of this PMP SPVCC. All subsequent parties should have the same value.

pnniPmpSpvccDestRootFwdQoSClass.name: pnniPmpSpvccDestRootFwdQoSClass
pnniPmpSpvccDestRootFwdQoSClass.description: The requested quality of service for this PMP SPVCC in the forward (from root to leaves) direction. Backward QoS requirements do not apply to PMP SPVCCs.

pnniPmpSpvccDestRootNumberOfParties.name: pnniPmpSpvccDestRootNumberOfParties
pnniPmpSpvccDestRootNumberOfParties.description: Number of parties currently terminating at this switch within this PMP SPVCC

pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyTable.name: pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyTable
pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyTable.description: This table contains information about the parties of PMP SPVCCs (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) that terminate at this switch.

pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyEntry.name: pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyEntry
pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyEntry.description: A table entry containing destination information about parties in a PMP SPVCC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits).

pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyIndex.name: pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyIndex
pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyIndex.description: The value of this object uniquely identifies a party of PMP SPVCCs (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) that have one or more parties terminating at this switch. This value is unique within a PMP SPVCC represented by pnniPmpSpvccDestRootIndex

pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyAtmAddr.name: pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyAtmAddr
pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyAtmAddr.description: The ATM address of the switch where this party of a PMP SPVCC terminates.

pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyPort.name: pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyPort
pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyPort.description: The value of this object identifies the port where this party of a PMP SPVCC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) terminates.It has a value os -1 if the port at the destination switch cannot be determined.

pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyAssignedVPI.name: pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyAssignedVPI
pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyAssignedVPI.description: The value of this object identifies the VPI assigned for this party of a PMP SPVCC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) at the terminating switch. This value is only meaningful if the party status, identified by pnniPmpSpvccDestStatus, is up.

pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyAssignedVCI.name: pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyAssignedVCI
pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyAssignedVCI.description: The value of this object identifies the VCI assigned for this party of a PMP SPVCC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) at the terminating switch. This value is only meaningful if the party status, identified by pnniPmpSpvccDestStatus, is up.

pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyUpTime.name: pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyUpTime
pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyUpTime.description: The time since this party of PMP SPVCC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuits) was created in hundredths of a second.

pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyTransitNetSel.name: pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyTransitNetSel
pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyTransitNetSel.description: The optional transit network selection for this party of PMP SPVCC.

pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyStatus.name: pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyStatus
pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyStatus.description: The operational status of this party of PMP SPVCC (Smart Permanent Virtual Circuit).

pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyRGroupIndex.name: pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyRGroupIndex
pnniPmpSpvccDestPartyRGroupIndex.description: This specifies the entry in the Spvxc Redundancy Group table for information regarding the secondary port to be used as the redundant port. This will used at the terminating PVC end.

pnniSpvxcRGroupTable.name: pnniSpvxcRGroupTable
pnniSpvxcRGroupTable.description: A table of Primary to Secondary Port mappings that will be used for redundancy in permanent portion of SPVxCs.

pnniSpvxcRGroupEntry.name: pnniSpvxcRGroupEntry
pnniSpvxcRGroupEntry.description: A table entry containing the primary to secondary port mappings.

pnniSpvxcRGroupIndex.name: pnniSpvxcRGroupIndex
pnniSpvxcRGroupIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the Group Index associated with this entry.

pnniSpvxcRGroupPrimaryPort.name: pnniSpvxcRGroupPrimaryPort
pnniSpvxcRGroupPrimaryPort.description: The value of this object identifies the primary port of this entry. This will used as the primary PVC port for the SPVC created with this group index.

pnniSpvxcRGroupSecondaryPort.name: pnniSpvxcRGroupSecondaryPort
pnniSpvxcRGroupSecondaryPort.description: The value of this object identifies the secondary port of this group. This will used as the redundant PVC port for the SPVC created with this group index. During a switch command, the PVCs will be switched from primary port to this port.

pnniSpvxcRGroupNsapAddr.name: pnniSpvxcRGroupNsapAddr
pnniSpvxcRGroupNsapAddr.description: This shows the default nsap address associated with this group using the default domain's prefix. This is a read-only variable available to view the default nsap address associated with this group.

pnniSpvxcRGroupSwitchoverCmd.name: pnniSpvxcRGroupSwitchoverCmd
pnniSpvxcRGroupSwitchoverCmd.description: The value of this MIB defines the switchover command. The value of 1 is used to switch over the permanent PVC portion to the primary port. The value of 2 is used to switch over the permanent PVC portion to the secondary port. If the permanent portions are already on the specified port, no action is taken

pnniSpvxcRGroupActivePort.name: pnniSpvxcRGroupActivePort
pnniSpvxcRGroupActivePort.description: This specifies the port that is active. This can take any one of the primary or secondary port values. This is a read only variable useful to check the currently active port.

pnniSpvxcRGroupPacingNumber.name: pnniSpvxcRGroupPacingNumber
pnniSpvxcRGroupPacingNumber.description: This specifies the pacing number for this group. During a pacing interval, pacing number of SPVCs will be attempted for PVC switch over.

pnniSpvxcRGroupPacingInterval.name: pnniSpvxcRGroupPacingInterval
pnniSpvxcRGroupPacingInterval.description: This specifies the pacing interval in units of milliseconds for this group. Every time a switchover command is issued, pacing number of SPVCs will be attempted for PVC switch over every Pacing Interval.

pnniSpvxcRGroupAutoPVCSwitchover.name: pnniSpvxcRGroupAutoPVCSwitchover
pnniSpvxcRGroupAutoPVCSwitchover.description: The value of this MIB defines if automatic switchover of the PVC portion is enable dor disabled. The default value is disabled(2).

pnniSpvxcRGroupName.name: pnniSpvxcRGroupName
pnniSpvxcRGroupName.description: The value of this object identifies the name that has been assigned for this Rgroup.

pnniSpvxcRGroupState.name: pnniSpvxcRGroupState
pnniSpvxcRGroupState.description: This specifies the state of the Redundancy Group. State operational(1) indicates that this group is in the normal state and switchover is not going on. State switchover_in_progress(2) indicates that switchover is presently going on for this group. In this state no new SPVCs can be added to this group.

pnniSpvxcRGroupRowStatus.name: pnniSpvxcRGroupRowStatus
pnniSpvxcRGroupRowStatus.description: The status of this pnniSpvxcRGroup entry.

q2931AdminTable.name: q2931AdminTable
q2931AdminTable.description: A table of general information about the Q2931 signaling path.

q2931AdminEntry.name: q2931AdminEntry
q2931AdminEntry.description: A table entry containing Q2931Admin signaling administration information, indexed by port and path.

q2931AdminPort.name: q2931AdminPort
q2931AdminPort.description: The value of this object identifies the port of this signalling path, and is the same as the portNumber.

q2931AdminVPI.name: q2931AdminVPI
q2931AdminVPI.description: The VPI (Virtual Path Identifier) of this signaling path.

q2931AdminVCI.name: q2931AdminVCI
q2931AdminVCI.description: The VCI (Virtual Channel Identifier) of the signaling channel within the signaling path.

q2931AdminStatus.name: q2931AdminStatus
q2931AdminStatus.description: The desired state of this signaling channel. The up(1) state dictates that Q2931 messages are used for signalling. The down(2) state dictates that Q2931 protocol is not used for signalling.

q2931OperStatus.name: q2931OperStatus
q2931OperStatus.description: The current operational state of this signaling channel, as determined either by administrative action, when the value of q2931AdminStatus is down(2), or by a link monitoring protocol, when the value of q2931AdminStatus is up(1).

q2931SSCOPOperStatus.name: q2931SSCOPOperStatus
q2931SSCOPOperStatus.description: The current operational state of the underlying SSCOP (Service Specific Connection Orientedd Protocol) on this channel. SSCOP's function is to provide a reliable data link layer for the exchange of Q.2931 signalling messages. The value up(1) reflects the value dataTransReady(4) for the SSCOPOperStatus object in the SSCOP Administration table (sscopAdminTable). All other values of that object are reflected as the value down(2) for this object.

q2931ILMIAdminStatus.name: q2931ILMIAdminStatus
q2931ILMIAdminStatus.description: The desired state of the underlying ILMI (Interim Local Manageemnt Interface) status and configuration channel. The up(1) state dictates that ILMI messages are used for status and configuration information. The down(2) state dictates that ILMI protocol is not used.

q2931ILMIOperStatus.name: q2931ILMIOperStatus
q2931ILMIOperStatus.description: The current operational state of the underlying ILMI (Interim Local Manageemnt Interface) status and configuration channel, as determined either by administrative action, when the value of q2931ILMIAdminStatus is down(2), or by a link monitoring protocol, when the value of q2931ILMIAdminStatus is up(1).

q2931AdminAALType.name: q2931AdminAALType
q2931AdminAALType.description: The AAL (ATM Adaptation Layer) type that is used by this Q2931 signaling path.

q2931AdminUNISide.name: q2931AdminUNISide
q2931AdminUNISide.description: This object detemines the role this port takes in the UNI (User Network Interface). If this port is connected to a host via the private UNI, this port is on the network(2) side of the UNI, whilst if this port is connected to the Public UNI the port may be required to be the user(1) side of the connection.

q2931AdminConfigType.name: q2931AdminConfigType
q2931AdminConfigType.description: The configuration of the UNI (User Network Interface) at initialization. Configuring the UNI to publicUNI(1) means that this link will be used between the switch and a public switch. Configuring the UNI to automode(2) means that the operational type will be determined dynamically. Configuring the UNI to iisp(3) (Interim Inter-Switch Signalling Protocol) indicates that this link is used for static routing NNI (Network to Network Interface). Configuring the type to privateNNI allows the interface to come up as PNNI type and running the PNNI routing protocol. Configuring the type as privateUNI indicates that the interface should comeup as a user-network interface UNI.

q2931AdminOperType.name: q2931AdminOperType
q2931AdminOperType.description: The operational configuration of the UNI (User Network Interface). publicUNI(1) is used between the switch and a public switch. privateUNI(2) is used between the switch and a host. IISP, iisp(3), stands for Interim Inter-Switch Signalling Protocol, is used between two switches using static routing. And spansNNI(4) is used between two switches using SPANS mapping messages for dynamic routing. If the q2931AdminConfigType is set to auto(2), the value of this object may be either privateUNI(2), or spansNNI(4).

q2931AdminEntryStatus.name: q2931AdminEntryStatus
q2931AdminEntryStatus.description: The status of this signaling path entry. Setting this object to invalid(4) causes the q2931 path to be destroyed.

q2931AdminRemoteIpAddress.name: q2931AdminRemoteIpAddress
q2931AdminRemoteIpAddress.description: The IP address of the entity connected to this q2931 signalling path. The remote IP address is derived using ILMI on this interface.

q2931SigReservedBW.name: q2931SigReservedBW
q2931SigReservedBW.description: Bandwidth reserved for the UNI Signaling VC, in cells/sec.

q2931ILMIReservedBW.name: q2931ILMIReservedBW
q2931ILMIReservedBW.description: Bandwidth reserved for the UNI ILMI VC, in cells/sec.

q2931ILMIAdminVCI.name: q2931ILMIAdminVCI
q2931ILMIAdminVCI.description: The VCI (Virtual Channel Identifier) of the ILMI signalling channel.

q2931AdminMinVCI.name: q2931AdminMinVCI
q2931AdminMinVCI.description: The minimum configured VCI (Virtual Channel Identifier) used for SVCs (Signalling Virtual Circuits).

q2931AdminMaxVCI.name: q2931AdminMaxVCI
q2931AdminMaxVCI.description: The maximum configured VCI (Virtual Channel Identifier) used for SVCs (Signalling Virtual Circuits).

q2931MinVCI.name: q2931MinVCI
q2931MinVCI.description: The minimum actual VCI (Virtual Channel Identifier) used for SVCs (Signalling Virtual Circuits).

q2931MaxVCI.name: q2931MaxVCI
q2931MaxVCI.description: The maximum actual VCI (Virtual Channel Identifier) used for SVCs (Signalling Virtual Circuits).

q2931UNIConfigVersion.name: q2931UNIConfigVersion
q2931UNIConfigVersion.description: The configuration version of the UNI protocol to use at initialization. Configuring the UNI to auto(1), means that the UNI will attempt to automatically determine which version of the UNI protocol to use by reading the value of ILMI variable atmfAtmLayerUniVersion. Configuring the UNI to uni30(2) means that this link will use version 30 of the UNI protocol, likewise for uni31(3). If the nni interface has to be brought up as pnni then pnni10 version isspecified. To bring the interface as uni40 version then sepcify uni40.

q2931UNIOperVersion.name: q2931UNIOperVersion
q2931UNIOperVersion.description: The version of the UNI that is currently being used on this link, i.e. the operational version of the UNI.

q2931ILMIRegistration.name: q2931ILMIRegistration
q2931ILMIRegistration.description: Whether to do ILMI Address and Prefix Registration across this UNI. If disabled, no prefix registration messages are sent by the network-side, and no address registration messages are generated by the user-side. If set to ignore, then the network-side performs as it normally would, except that addresses registered are not published into the routing database. This setting is not recommended except in Public Network situations where CPE equipment requires ILMI Address registration in order to function correctly. The default value of this variable is different depending on the type of UNI being created. If creating a public UNI, this variable defaults to disable, while it defaults to enable for all other types.

q2931CallingPDefaultAddress.name: q2931CallingPDefaultAddress
q2931CallingPDefaultAddress.description: The calling party address to be inserted in Connection Setup messages which do not contain Calling Party Addresses.

q2931AdminUseNativeE164.name: q2931AdminUseNativeE164
q2931AdminUseNativeE164.description: Whether to use Native Form of E164 Addresses across this link. Used by Public UNI.

q2931AdminNativeE164Address.name: q2931AdminNativeE164Address
q2931AdminNativeE164Address.description: Native E164 Address for this uni.

q2931AdminE164AddressResolution.name: q2931AdminE164AddressResolution
q2931AdminE164AddressResolution.description: Whether to resolve Private NSAPs into Native E164 addresses (using the Q2931E164AddrResTable). If disabled, but if q2931AdminUseNativeE164 is enabled, then the only address conversion performed at this UNI will be of Private NSAPs in E.164 format.

q2931AdminFtPnniOrigCost.name: q2931AdminFtPnniOrigCost
q2931AdminFtPnniOrigCost.description: The cost of each pnni orig loglink. It is configured at originating end of sigpath

q2931AdminFtPnniTermCost.name: q2931AdminFtPnniTermCost
q2931AdminFtPnniTermCost.description: The cost of each pnni term loglink. The originating side of a link informs the terminating side of the configured q2931AdminFtPnniOrigCost in a hello message. The terminating side then uses the cost value in the hello message as the q2931AdminFtPnniTermCost for topology advertisement.

q2931AdminAVPresentation.name: q2931AdminAVPresentation
q2931AdminAVPresentation.description: The set of Address Validation interface options as follows: (The bits in this integer have the following meanings:) Bit Significance Default ======== ============= ======== 0x0001 Address Validation Enabled disabled 0x0002 insertCallingPDefaultAddress disabled 0x0004 CallingP_delivery enabled 0x0008 CallingPSubAddr_trxf enabled 0x0010 CalledPSubAddr_trxf enabled 0x0020 BHLI_TRXF enabled 0x0040 BLLI_TRXF enabled 0x0080 BLLI_selection_TRXF enabled 0x0100 AAL_INFO_TRXF enabled --- Not used presently. ----

q2931AdminSigMode.name: q2931AdminSigMode
q2931AdminSigMode.description: The configured mode for signalling: VP-associated, Non-Associated or auto mode. vpAssoc(1) stands for VP-associated signalling, if set to this value, the uni encodes the connection identifier with the VP-associated signalling bits. nonAssoc(2) is for Non-associated signalling, if set to this value the connection identifier is encoded with non-associated signalling bits. auto(3) stands for auto-configured signalling mode, if set to this value, the operating mode will be determined dynamically and will either be VP-associated or Non-associated depending on the operating type of the signalling link

q2931AdminSigAlloc.name: q2931AdminSigAlloc
q2931AdminSigAlloc.description: The current configured allocation policy for a network side uni. If set to allocVP(1), the signalling entity will allocate connections within the containing VP only. If set to allocLink(2), the signalling entity will allocate connections in its containing VP and may allocate connections in other VPS that are available to it. If set to allocVpBundle, the uni will allocate connections in its containing VP and a bundle of other VPs which are pre-created. If set to auto(3), the operating allocation policy will be determined based on the operating type of the signalling entity and the VPI value of the VP in which the signalling channel is present. Based on these, it might be allocLink or allocVP or allocVpBundle

q2931PeerPort.name: q2931PeerPort
q2931PeerPort.description: The value of this object identifies the port of the peer's signalling path. The value starts at zero.

q2931InputSigContract.name: q2931InputSigContract
q2931InputSigContract.description: Traffic Contract to be applied to the input signalling channel.

q2931OutputSigService.name: q2931OutputSigService
q2931OutputSigService.description: Service Queue where the output signalling vc should be inserted into.

q2931SSCOPNoRespTimer.name: q2931SSCOPNoRespTimer
q2931SSCOPNoRespTimer.description: The Value to be set for the duration of the SSCOP No response timer. This is the time in seconds that we will wait before bringing the SSCOP link down. If no value is specified by the user, a default value of 10 seconds is used if the oper version is uni30 and a default value of 7 secs is used if the oper version is uni31.

q2931AdminIncomingNSAPFilterIndex.name: q2931AdminIncomingNSAPFilterIndex
q2931AdminIncomingNSAPFilterIndex.description: The Filter Index of the NSAP Address Filter used to filter incoming calls. If this variable is set to zero, all incoming calls on this UNI will be accepted.

q2931AdminOutgoingNSAPFilterIndex.name: q2931AdminOutgoingNSAPFilterIndex
q2931AdminOutgoingNSAPFilterIndex.description: The Filter Index of the NSAP Address Filter used to filter outgoing calls. If this variable is set to zero, all incoming calls on this UNI will be accepted.

q2931AdminIEFilter.name: q2931AdminIEFilter
q2931AdminIEFilter.description: The set of Information Element Filtering interface options as follows: (The bits in this integer have the following meanings:) Bit Significance Default ======== ============= ======== 0x0001 IE Filtering enabled disabled 0x0002 InsertCallingPDefaultAddress disabled 0x0004 CallingP_delivery enabled 0x0008 CallingPSubAddr_trxf enabled 0x0010 CalledPSubAddr_trxf enabled 0x0020 BHLI_trxf enabled 0x0040 BLLI_trxf enabled 0x0080 BLLI_selection_trxf enabled 0x0100 AAL_Info_trxf enabled --- not used presently ---- The valid combinations of bits 0x40 (BLLI_TRXF) and 0x80 (BLLI_selection_TRXF) are: 0xc0 (1 1) transfer all BLLIs default 0x80 (1 0) **invalid** 0x40 (0 1) transfer only the first BLLI 0x00 (0 0) remove all BLLIs

q2931SendCallProc.name: q2931SendCallProc
q2931SendCallProc.description: A flag which allows the user to specify at creation time if CALL PROCEEDING should be sent on this particular interface. If set to on(1), a CALL PROCEEDING message is sent out that interface for every SETUP received on that interface that is successfully forwarded. If set to off(2), no CALL PROCEEDING messages are sent on this interface.

q2931VCIRangeStatus.name: q2931VCIRangeStatus
q2931VCIRangeStatus.description: A flag which indicates the status of Min/MaxVCI range with respect to whether or not the range values are assigned after negotiating with the peer through ILMI process. This variable is set to valid if ILMI is up and range negotiation with the peer is completed, except if a UNI (link) is configured as IISP or ILMI-down, then the value of this MIB value is always set to valid.

q2931ClearOnCarrierLoss.name: q2931ClearOnCarrierLoss
q2931ClearOnCarrierLoss.description: This object indicates whether to clear calls when carrier is lost on the link associated with this signalling channel. The default value is noClear(1). This follows the ATM Forum specification which requires the specific signalling timers to expire before clearing the connections. Setting this value to clearCalls(2) will result in the connections being torn down as soon as carrier loss is detected (not compliant with ATM Forum signalling specifications).

q2931QosClassExpansionKey.name: q2931QosClassExpansionKey
q2931QosClassExpansionKey.description: The key for the QOS Class Expansion Table to be used for this UNI.

q2931AtmrConfDomainID.name: q2931AtmrConfDomainID
q2931AtmrConfDomainID.description: This is the ID of the routing domain to which this interface belongs if this uni is operating as a private UNI, public UNI or IISP

q2931AtmrPnniNodeIndex.name: q2931AtmrPnniNodeIndex
q2931AtmrPnniNodeIndex.description: This is the index of the node to which this interface attaches for FT-PNNI and PNNI interfaces. The value is always 0xffff for FT-PNNI interfaces.

q2931AdminOperSigMode.name: q2931AdminOperSigMode
q2931AdminOperSigMode.description: The operating mode for signalling: VP-associated or Non-associated. vpAssoc(1) stands for VP-associated signalling, if set to this value, the uni encodes the conn_id with the VP-associated signalling bits. nonAssoc(2) stands for Non-associated signalling, if set to this value, the uni encodes the conn_id with Non-associated signalling bits.

q2931AdminOperSigAlloc.name: q2931AdminOperSigAlloc
q2931AdminOperSigAlloc.description: The operating allocation policy for a network side uni. If set to allocVP, the network side uni will allocate connections in its containing VP only. If set to allocLink, the uni will allocate connections in its containing VP and may allocate connections in other VPS that are available to it. If set to allocVpBundle, the uni will allocate connections in its containing VP and a bundle of other VPs which are pre-created.

q2931OutputSigUpc.name: q2931OutputSigUpc
q2931OutputSigUpc.description: Traffic contract to be applied to the output side of the signalling channel. If this is not specified, signalling will be put in the vbr queue with no bandwidth reservation and no policing.

q2931AdminPlanType.name: q2931AdminPlanType
q2931AdminPlanType.description: This is the plan type to be used in calling party number and called party number IEs in the signalling messages. The value of this variable is dependent on whether q2931AdminUseNativeE164 is set to enable or disable. Further, q2931AdminPlanType can be set in conjunction with q2931AdminUseNativeE164. When q2931AdminUseNativeE164 is set to disable, q2931AdminPlanType takes a default value of 1(unknown). All other values are invalid. When q2931AdminUseNativeE164 is set to enable, q2931AdminPlanType takes a default value of 2(international). Other valid values are 3(national) and 4(subscriber).

q2931AdminMaxVPI.name: q2931AdminMaxVPI
q2931AdminMaxVPI.description: The maximum configured VPI (Virtual Path Identifier) that is used for SVPs (Signalling Virtual Paths) when this interface sets up SVP Connections and also the Max VPI that is used to create dynamic paths for SVCs (Signalling Virtual Circuit) connections.

q2931MaxSvccVPI.name: q2931MaxSvccVPI
q2931MaxSvccVPI.description: The maximum actual VPI (Virtual Path Identifier) that will be used for SVCs (Signalling Virtual Circuit) dynamic paths. This variable denotes the operating value for the maximum VPI value that can be used for setting up dynamic path SVPS. The operating value can differ from the configured value (q2931AdminMaxVPI) as the operating value depends on the outcome of possible ILMI based VPI range negotiation procedure.

q2931LastChangeTime.name: q2931LastChangeTime
q2931LastChangeTime.description: The time the Signalling entity was created in hundredths of a second.

q2931MaxSvpcVPI.name: q2931MaxSvpcVPI
q2931MaxSvpcVPI.description: The maximum actual VPI (Virtual Path Identifier) that will be used for SVPs (Signalling Virtual Paths). This variable denotes the operating value for the maximum VPI value that can be used for setting up dynamic path SVPS. The operating value can differ from the configured value (q2931AdminMaxVPI) as the operating value depends on the outcome of possible ILMI based VPI range negotiation procedure.

q2931VpCapability.name: q2931VpCapability
q2931VpCapability.description: This mib variable is used to determine if this interface is capable of supporting Switched VPs. For UNI3.x and VP Scope Signalling Interfaces, SVPs (Switch Virtual Paths) cannot be created and hence undefined(1). For UNI40 & PNNI Link Scope interfaces, if there is a non-zero VPI range intersection with the peer, the interface is vpCapable(2), else notVpCapable(3)

q2931NNIProto.name: q2931NNIProto
q2931NNIProto.description: The NNI protocol being run on this link

q2931AcceleratedClear.name: q2931AcceleratedClear
q2931AcceleratedClear.description: This object indicates whether to clear calls when carrier is lost on the link associated with this signalling channel or the Virtual Path goes down. The default value is noClear(1). This follows the ATM Forum specification which requires the specific signalling timers to expire before clearing the connections. Setting this value to clearCalls(2) will result in the connections being torn down as soon as carrier loss/VP failure is detected (not compliant with ATM Forum signalling specifications).

q2931VpciGroupIndex.name: q2931VpciGroupIndex
q2931VpciGroupIndex.description: The index into the VPCI Mapping Group Table to use for this signalling interface.

q2931ProxyDirGroupIndex.name: q2931ProxyDirGroupIndex
q2931ProxyDirGroupIndex.description: The index into the proxy address group table to use for this signalling interface.

q2931SupplementaryServicesStatus.name: q2931SupplementaryServicesStatus
q2931SupplementaryServicesStatus.description: This MIB variable is used to enable or disable all the supplementary services features for this interface. This acts as a global switch for this interface to disable or enable all of the supplementary services. The MIB variables defined for all supplementary services will be used only when this is enabled. The supplementary services is disabled by default. The value of undefined(3) is a read-only value used for interfaces where supplementary services are not applicable.

q2931CallingPAddressPresentation.name: q2931CallingPAddressPresentation
q2931CallingPAddressPresentation.description: The Calling party address presentation can be set to one of the two values as described above. The CLIP MIB variable is used when this interface is acting as a called party for a call setup message. When set to enable(1), while a call setup message is forwarded through this interface, the calling party number is provided. When set to disable(2), the calling party number is not provided in the call setup message. The value of undefined(3) is a read-only value used for interfaces where supplementary services are not applicable.

q2931CallingPAddressRestriction.name: q2931CallingPAddressRestriction
q2931CallingPAddressRestriction.description: The Calling party address restriction can be set to one of the two values as described above. The CLIR MIB variable is used when this interface is acting as a calling party for a call setup message. When set to enable(1), while a call setup mes-sage is received from this interface and forwarded out, the calling party number is not provided to called user. When set to disable(2), the calling party number is provided to the called user. The value of undefined(3) is a read-only value used for interfaces where supplementary services are not applicable.

q2931ConnectedPAddressPresentation.name: q2931ConnectedPAddressPresentation
q2931ConnectedPAddressPresentation.description: The Connected party address presentation can be set to one of the two values as described above. The COLP MIB variable is used when the interface is acting as a calling party to a call setup message. When set to enable(1), while a call establish-ment response message is forwarded through this interface, the connected party number is provided to the calling user. When set to disable(2), while a call establishment response message is forwarded through this interface, the connected party number is not provided to the calling user. The value of undefined(3) is a read-only value used for interfaces where supplementary services are not applicable.

q2931ConnectedPAddressRestriction.name: q2931ConnectedPAddressRestriction
q2931ConnectedPAddressRestriction.description: The Connected party address restriction can be set to one of the two values as described above. The COLR MIB variable is used when the interface is acting as a called party to a call setup message. When set to enable(1), while a call establishment response message is forwarded from this interface, the connected party number is not provided to the calling user. When set to disable(2),while a call establishment response message is forwarded from this interface, the connected party number is provided to the calling user. The value of undefined(3) is a read-only value used for interfaces where supplementary services are not applicable.

q2931ConnectedPDefaultAddress.name: q2931ConnectedPDefaultAddress
q2931ConnectedPDefaultAddress.description: The connected party address to be used in Connection Acceptance (connect, add party ack etc.) messages that do not contain Connected Party Addresses.

q2931SubaddressingAdminStatus.name: q2931SubaddressingAdminStatus
q2931SubaddressingAdminStatus.description: This is used to enable or disable the sub-addressing capability. If this is set to enable(1), the called party sub-address IE is passed along. Ifthis is set to disbale(2), this IE is removed while forwarding the messages. The value of undefined(3) is a read-only value used for interfaces where supplementary services are not applicable.

q2931UserUserSignallingAdminStatus.name: q2931UserUserSignallingAdminStatus
q2931UserUserSignallingAdminStatus.description: This is used to enable or disable the User to User Signalling capability. If this is set to enable(1), the UUS IE is passed along. If this is set to disbale(2), this IE is removed while forwarding the messages. The value of undefined(3) is a read-only value used for interfaces where supplementary services are not applicable.

q2931OutputIlmiUpc.name: q2931OutputIlmiUpc
q2931OutputIlmiUpc.description: The index into the UPC table for the ILMI channel

q2931OutputRccUpc.name: q2931OutputRccUpc
q2931OutputRccUpc.description: The index into the UPC table for the RCC channel

q2931PnniRccVci.name: q2931PnniRccVci
q2931PnniRccVci.description: This is used to specify the PVC RCC VCI used by PNNI. Normally this will always be 18, but if a user creates a VPT with a VCI range that does not contain 18, then this field is used to specify the PNNI PVC RCC VCI.

q2931AdminubrCalls.name: q2931AdminubrCalls
q2931AdminubrCalls.description: This flag is used to disable processing of UBR calls.

q2931AdmincbrCalls.name: q2931AdmincbrCalls
q2931AdmincbrCalls.description: This flag is used to disable processing of CBR calls.

q2931AdminabrCalls.name: q2931AdminabrCalls
q2931AdminabrCalls.description: This flag is used to disable processing of ABR calls.

q2931AdminrtvbrCalls.name: q2931AdminrtvbrCalls
q2931AdminrtvbrCalls.description: This flag is used to disable processing of RT-VBR calls.

q2931AdminnrtvbrCalls.name: q2931AdminnrtvbrCalls
q2931AdminnrtvbrCalls.description: This flag is used to disable processing of NRT-VBR calls.

q2931StatsTable.name: q2931StatsTable
q2931StatsTable.description: A table of statistics about the Q2931 signaling path.

q2931StatsEntry.name: q2931StatsEntry
q2931StatsEntry.description: A table entry containing signaling path statistics, indexed by port and path.

q2931StatsPort.name: q2931StatsPort
q2931StatsPort.description: The value of this object identifies the port of this signalling path, and is the same as q2931Port.

q2931StatsVPI.name: q2931StatsVPI
q2931StatsVPI.description: The value of this object identifies the VPI (Virtual Path Identifier) of this signaling path statistics entry, and is the same as q2931VPI.

q2931VCCs.name: q2931VCCs
q2931VCCs.description: The number of Virtual Channel Connections (VCCs) on this signaling path.

q2931Restarts.name: q2931Restarts
q2931Restarts.description: The number of times the switch has lost and regained contact with the remote signaling entity on this path.

q2931CallsCompletions.name: q2931CallsCompletions
q2931CallsCompletions.description: The number of successfully completed calls on this signaling path.

q2931CallsFailures.name: q2931CallsFailures
q2931CallsFailures.description: The number of call failures on this signaling path.

q2931CallsRejections.name: q2931CallsRejections
q2931CallsRejections.description: The number of connections on this signaling path that were rejected by the far end.

q2931TransmittedMessages.name: q2931TransmittedMessages
q2931TransmittedMessages.description: The total number of Q2931 messages that have been transmitted over this signalling path.

q2931ReceivedMessages.name: q2931ReceivedMessages
q2931ReceivedMessages.description: The total number of Q2931 messages that have been received on this signalling path.

q2931E164AddrResTable.name: q2931E164AddrResTable
q2931E164AddrResTable.description: A table of E164 Address Resolution entries.

q2931E164AddrResEntry.name: q2931E164AddrResEntry
q2931E164AddrResEntry.description: A table entry containing E164 Address Resolution information, indexed by Nsap.

q2931NPCallTable.name: q2931NPCallTable
q2931NPCallTable.description: A table of NSAP addressed and call parameters to be used in testing the reachability of destination addresses.

q2931NPCallEntry.name: q2931NPCallEntry
q2931NPCallEntry.description: A table entry containing NSAP address, call parameter information.

q2931NPCallIndex.name: q2931NPCallIndex
q2931NPCallIndex.description: The value of this object identifies an entry in the q2931NPCallTable.

q2931NPCallDstNsap.name: q2931NPCallDstNsap
q2931NPCallDstNsap.description: The Destination NSAP address used by this table entry.

q2931NPCallState.name: q2931NPCallState
q2931NPCallState.description: This field keeps the state of the nsap call. This field is set to inprogress by default. 'up' means call was successful, 'down' means call was rejected by the destination, 'err' means call was not attempted primarily because no route to destination was available, 'locpref', 'lochost' mean that the address is local

q2931NPCallClientType.name: q2931NPCallClientType
q2931NPCallClientType.description: Holds the type of the client expected to answer the call at destination. Set to noIndication by default.

q2931NPCallFwdUpcKey.name: q2931NPCallFwdUpcKey
q2931NPCallFwdUpcKey.description: UPC table entry to be used in the forward direction of the call is stored here. Set to ZERO by default.

q2931NPCallBckUpcKey.name: q2931NPCallBckUpcKey
q2931NPCallBckUpcKey.description: UPC table entry to be used in the backward direction of the call is stored here. Set to ZERO by default.

q2931NPCallCallingDomain.name: q2931NPCallCallingDomain
q2931NPCallCallingDomain.description: The domain at the originating switch on which the call has to be routed. By default this is set to the default domain, control port domain.

q2931NPCallQosIndex.name: q2931NPCallQosIndex
q2931NPCallQosIndex.description: QOS Index entry to be used in the forward direction of the call is stored here. Set to ZERO by default.

q2931NPCallQosClassFwd.name: q2931NPCallQosClassFwd
q2931NPCallQosClassFwd.description: QOS Class for forward direction of the call. Set to ZERO by default.

q2931NPCallQosClassBwd.name: q2931NPCallQosClassBwd
q2931NPCallQosClassBwd.description: QOS Class for backward direction of the call. Set to ZERO by default.

q2931NPCallBearerClass.name: q2931NPCallBearerClass
q2931NPCallBearerClass.description: Bearer Class to be used for the NSAP Ping call. Set to classX by default.

q2931NPCallVerbose.name: q2931NPCallVerbose
q2931NPCallVerbose.description: Holds the info, whether the call setup messages have to be displayed on user console or not. By default set to off.

q2931NPCallStatus.name: q2931NPCallStatus
q2931NPCallStatus.description: The status of this table entry. This entry may not be destroyed if there are any filter entries that refer to it.

q2931NPPingState.name: q2931NPPingState
q2931NPPingState.description: This field tracks the state of the ping process. Invalid is the initial state, when the connection is made the state changes to 'inprogress' and when the ping is complete the state changes to 'complete'.

q2931NPCallCauseCode.name: q2931NPCallCauseCode
q2931NPCallCauseCode.description: The UNI call setup failure cause code. This value is valid only if the call state is 'down'

q2931NPPingPktCount.name: q2931NPPingPktCount
q2931NPPingPktCount.description: The number of ping packets used in the ping process

q2931NPPingStatsPktsSent.name: q2931NPPingStatsPktsSent
q2931NPPingStatsPktsSent.description: The number of ping packets actually sent

q2931NPPingStatsPktsReceived.name: q2931NPPingStatsPktsReceived
q2931NPPingStatsPktsReceived.description: The number of ping packets replied to by the destination

q2931NPPingStatsAverageDelay.name: q2931NPPingStatsAverageDelay
q2931NPPingStatsAverageDelay.description: The average round trip delay expressed in milli seconds.

q2931NPMeasureRoundTripDelay.name: q2931NPMeasureRoundTripDelay
q2931NPMeasureRoundTripDelay.description: Holds the info, whether the ping process has to be done after the connection is made, By default set to off

q2931NPPingStatsMaximumDelay.name: q2931NPPingStatsMaximumDelay
q2931NPPingStatsMaximumDelay.description: The maximum round trip delay expressed in milli seconds.

q2931NPPingStatsMinimumDelay.name: q2931NPPingStatsMinimumDelay
q2931NPPingStatsMinimumDelay.description: The minimum round trip delay expressed in milli seconds.

q2931NPCallNextIndex.name: q2931NPCallNextIndex
q2931NPCallNextIndex.description: The index of the next free row in the q2931NPCallTable.

q2931AFTemplateTable.name: q2931AFTemplateTable
q2931AFTemplateTable.description: A table of allowable (or rejectable) NSAP source and destination addresses.

q2931AFTemplateEntry.name: q2931AFTemplateEntry
q2931AFTemplateEntry.description: A table entry containing NSAP address filtering information.

q2931AFTemplateIndex.name: q2931AFTemplateIndex
q2931AFTemplateIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the NSAP Address Filter Template to which this entry belongs.

q2931AFTemplateSrcPort.name: q2931AFTemplateSrcPort
q2931AFTemplateSrcPort.description: The source UNI port matched by this entry. A value of -1 matches all ports.

q2931AFTemplateSrcVPI.name: q2931AFTemplateSrcVPI
q2931AFTemplateSrcVPI.description: The source UNI VPI matched by this entry. A value of -1 matches all VPIs.

q2931AFTemplateSrcNsap.name: q2931AFTemplateSrcNsap
q2931AFTemplateSrcNsap.description: The Source NSAP address filtered by this table entry.

q2931AFTemplateSrcNsapMask.name: q2931AFTemplateSrcNsapMask
q2931AFTemplateSrcNsapMask.description: The mask applied to the source address in order to compare against the above q2931AFTemplateEntrySrcNsap. A mask of 0 bits matches all source addresses.

q2931AFTemplateDstPort.name: q2931AFTemplateDstPort
q2931AFTemplateDstPort.description: The destination UNI port matched by this entry. A value of -1 matches all ports.

q2931AFTemplateDstVPI.name: q2931AFTemplateDstVPI
q2931AFTemplateDstVPI.description: The destination UNI VPI matched by this entry. A value of -1 matches all VPIs.

q2931AFTemplateDstNsap.name: q2931AFTemplateDstNsap
q2931AFTemplateDstNsap.description: The Destination NSAP address filtered by this table entry.

q2931AFTemplateDstNsapMask.name: q2931AFTemplateDstNsapMask
q2931AFTemplateDstNsapMask.description: The mask applied to the destination address in order to compare against the above q2931AFTemplateDstNsap. A mask of 0 bits matches all destination addresses.

q2931AFTemplateAction.name: q2931AFTemplateAction
q2931AFTemplateAction.description: What to do with addresses that match this entry.

q2931AFTemplateName.name: q2931AFTemplateName
q2931AFTemplateName.description: An optional text name for the template.

q2931AFTemplateStatus.name: q2931AFTemplateStatus
q2931AFTemplateStatus.description: The status of this table entry. This entry may not be destroyed if there are any filter entries that refer to it.

q2931AFTemplateNextIndex.name: q2931AFTemplateNextIndex
q2931AFTemplateNextIndex.description: The index of the next free row in the q2931AFTemplateTable.

q2931AFFilterTable.name: q2931AFFilterTable
q2931AFFilterTable.description: A table of filters, each composed of an ordered list of address filtering templates.

q2931AFFilterEntry.name: q2931AFFilterEntry
q2931AFFilterEntry.description: A table entry for one filter.

q2931AFFilterIndex.name: q2931AFFilterIndex
q2931AFFilterIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the NSAP Address Filter to which this entry belongs.

q2931AFFilterName.name: q2931AFFilterName
q2931AFFilterName.description: An optional text name for the filter.

q2931AFFilterStatus.name: q2931AFFilterStatus
q2931AFFilterStatus.description: The status of this table entry. Setting this variable to destroy removes this row from the q2931AFFilterTable, and removes the corresponding entries from the q2931AFFilterTListTable.

q2931AFFilterNextIndex.name: q2931AFFilterNextIndex
q2931AFFilterNextIndex.description: The index of the next free row in the q2931AFFilterTable.

q2931AFFilterTListTable.name: q2931AFFilterTListTable
q2931AFFilterTListTable.description: A table of template lists for filters. A template list is composed of an ordered list of address filtering templates. All objects with the same value for q2931AFFilterIndex are conceptually part of the corresponding q2931AFFilterEntry.

q2931AFFilterTListEntry.name: q2931AFFilterTListEntry
q2931AFFilterTListEntry.description: A table entry holding one template in a filter's template list.

q2931AFFilterTListIndex.name: q2931AFFilterTListIndex
q2931AFFilterTListIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the order in this NSAP Address Filter in which this template is applied.

q2931AFFilterTListTemplateIndex.name: q2931AFFilterTListTemplateIndex
q2931AFFilterTListTemplateIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the NSAP Address Filter Template for this entry.

q2931AFFilterTListStatus.name: q2931AFFilterTListStatus
q2931AFFilterTListStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

q2931AFStatsTable.name: q2931AFStatsTable
q2931AFStatsTable.description: A table of address filtering statistics.

q2931AFStatsEntry.name: q2931AFStatsEntry
q2931AFStatsEntry.description: An entry in the table of address filtering statistics. There are two entries for each UNI: one for incoming call setup attempts, and one for outgoing call setup attempts.

q2931AFDirection.name: q2931AFDirection
q2931AFDirection.description: The value of this object identifies whether this row of the statistics table applies to incoming or outgoing call attempts.

q2931AFAccepts.name: q2931AFAccepts
q2931AFAccepts.description: The total number of Q2931 messages that have been accepted by Address Filtering on this UNI.

q2931AFRejectKnowns.name: q2931AFRejectKnowns
q2931AFRejectKnowns.description: The total number of Q2931 messages that have been rejected because the supplied address matched a template in the address filtering table where the action was to reject the call.

q2931AFRejectUnknowns.name: q2931AFRejectUnknowns
q2931AFRejectUnknowns.description: The total number of Q2931 messages that have been rejected because the supplied address matched no template in the address filtering table.

q2931AFLookupTable.name: q2931AFLookupTable
q2931AFLookupTable.description: The Lookup facility for NSAP address filtering.

q2931AFLookupEntry.name: q2931AFLookupEntry
q2931AFLookupEntry.description: The result of an inquiry to the Lookup facility.

q2931AFLookupIndex.name: q2931AFLookupIndex
q2931AFLookupIndex.description: The value of this object identifies this entry in the Filter Lookup table.

q2931AFLookupNSAPFilterIndex.name: q2931AFLookupNSAPFilterIndex
q2931AFLookupNSAPFilterIndex.description: The index of the NSAP address filter for this lookup.

q2931AFLookupSrcPort.name: q2931AFLookupSrcPort
q2931AFLookupSrcPort.description: The simulated incoming Port for this filter lookup.

q2931AFLookupSrcVPI.name: q2931AFLookupSrcVPI
q2931AFLookupSrcVPI.description: The simulated incoming VPI for this filter lookup.

q2931AFLookupSrcNsap.name: q2931AFLookupSrcNsap
q2931AFLookupSrcNsap.description: The Source NSAP address for this filter lookup.

q2931AFLookupDstPort.name: q2931AFLookupDstPort
q2931AFLookupDstPort.description: The simulated outgoing Port for this filter lookup.

q2931AFLookupDstVPI.name: q2931AFLookupDstVPI
q2931AFLookupDstVPI.description: The simulated outgoing VPI for this filter lookup.

q2931AFLookupDstNsap.name: q2931AFLookupDstNsap
q2931AFLookupDstNsap.description: The Destination NSAP address for this filter lookup.

q2931AFLookupResult.name: q2931AFLookupResult
q2931AFLookupResult.description: The result of a filter Lookup on the selected values: 1 Accepted 2 Rejected

q2931AFLookupTemplate.name: q2931AFLookupTemplate
q2931AFLookupTemplate.description: The index of the template in the address filter that either accepted or rejected the call. It is zero if the address was unknown.

q2931AFLookupStatus.name: q2931AFLookupStatus
q2931AFLookupStatus.description: The status of this table entry.

q2931AFLastFailureSrcPort.name: q2931AFLastFailureSrcPort
q2931AFLastFailureSrcPort.description: The incoming port for this failed call attempt.

q2931AFLastFailureSrcVPI.name: q2931AFLastFailureSrcVPI
q2931AFLastFailureSrcVPI.description: The incoming VPI for this failed call attempt.

q2931AFLastFailureSrcNsap.name: q2931AFLastFailureSrcNsap
q2931AFLastFailureSrcNsap.description: The source address of this failed call attempt.

q2931AFLastFailureDstPort.name: q2931AFLastFailureDstPort
q2931AFLastFailureDstPort.description: The outgoing port for this failed call attempt.

q2931AFLastFailureDstVPI.name: q2931AFLastFailureDstVPI
q2931AFLastFailureDstVPI.description: The outgoing VPI for this failed call attempt.

q2931AFLastFailureDstNsap.name: q2931AFLastFailureDstNsap
q2931AFLastFailureDstNsap.description: The destination address of this failed call attempt.

q2931AFLastFailureTemplateIndex.name: q2931AFLastFailureTemplateIndex
q2931AFLastFailureTemplateIndex.description: The index of the template which rejected this call attempt. If this call was rejected because its addresses were not known, this field is set to zero.

q2931AFLastFailureDirection.name: q2931AFLastFailureDirection
q2931AFLastFailureDirection.description: The value of this object identifies whether the incoming (source) or outgoing (destination) filter rejected the call. Its value is irrelevant for accepted calls.

proxyDirMapEntryTable.name: proxyDirMapEntryTable
proxyDirMapEntryTable.description: A table of ATM End system address, Proxy address directory and VPCI mappings.

proxyDirMapEntry.name: proxyDirMapEntry
proxyDirMapEntry.description: A table entry containing ATM End System Address, proxy directory group index and VPCI.

proxyDirMapIndex.name: proxyDirMapIndex
proxyDirMapIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the mapping associated with this entry.

proxyDirMapAESA.name: proxyDirMapAESA
proxyDirMapAESA.description: The ATM End System Address associated with this entry

proxyDirMapGroup.name: proxyDirMapGroup
proxyDirMapGroup.description: The proxy directory address group identifier associated with this mapping

proxyDirMapVPCI.name: proxyDirMapVPCI
proxyDirMapVPCI.description: The VPCI value associated with this entry

proxyDirMapStatus.name: proxyDirMapStatus
proxyDirMapStatus.description: The status of this mapping entry.

proxyDirMapVp.name: proxyDirMapVp
proxyDirMapVp.description: The VP value associated with this entry

proxyDirMapPort.name: proxyDirMapPort
proxyDirMapPort.description: The port associated with this entry

proxyDirGroupTable.name: proxyDirGroupTable
proxyDirGroupTable.description: A group of ATM End system address and VPCI mappings

proxyDirGroupEntry.name: proxyDirGroupEntry
proxyDirGroupEntry.description: A group of ATM End system address and VPCI mappings

proxyDirGroupIndex.name: proxyDirGroupIndex
proxyDirGroupIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the mapping associated with this entry.

proxyDirGroupPrefix.name: proxyDirGroupPrefix
proxyDirGroupPrefix.description: The prefix of the ATM End System Address that is used in mapping to a VPCI

proxyDirGroupVPCIGroup.name: proxyDirGroupVPCIGroup
proxyDirGroupVPCIGroup.description: The VPCI group index associated with this entry

proxyDirGroupStatus.name: proxyDirGroupStatus
proxyDirGroupStatus.description: The status of this mapping entry.

vmtVpciMapTable.name: vmtVpciMapTable
vmtVpciMapTable.description: A table of VPCI, VPI and Port mappings.

vmtVpciMapEntry.name: vmtVpciMapEntry
vmtVpciMapEntry.description: A table entry containing a VPCI, VPI and Port mappings.

vmtVpciMapIndex.name: vmtVpciMapIndex
vmtVpciMapIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the VPCI mapping associated with this entry.

vmtVpciMapVPCI.name: vmtVpciMapVPCI
vmtVpciMapVPCI.description: The VPCI associated with this VPCI mapping entry.

vmtVpciMapVPI.name: vmtVpciMapVPI
vmtVpciMapVPI.description: The VPI associated with this VPCI mapping entry. A value of -1 indicates that the VPI is the same as the VPI associated with the signalling interface using this VPCI mapping entry.
