vmtVpciMapPort.name: vmtVpciMapPort
vmtVpciMapPort.description: The Port associated with this VPCI mapping entry. A value of -1 indicates that the Port is the same as the Port associated with the signalling interface using this VPCI mapping entry.

vmtVpciMapStatus.name: vmtVpciMapStatus
vmtVpciMapStatus.description: The status of this VPCI mapping entry. The status cannot be set to destroy if there are any vmtVpciMapGroupTable entries that refer to it.

vmtVpciMapGroupTable.name: vmtVpciMapGroupTable
vmtVpciMapGroupTable.description: A table of VPCI mapping groups. Each VPCI mapping group consists of a list if VPCI mapping entries.

vmtVpciMapGroupEntry.name: vmtVpciMapGroupEntry
vmtVpciMapGroupEntry.description: A table entry for one VPCI mapping group.

vmtVpciMapGroupIndex.name: vmtVpciMapGroupIndex
vmtVpciMapGroupIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the VPCI mapping group associated with this entry.

vmtVpciMapGroupStatus.name: vmtVpciMapGroupStatus
vmtVpciMapGroupStatus.description: The status of the VPCI mapping group entry. This object cannot be transitioned from the Active state to any other state if there are any signalling interfaces using this VPCI mapping group. Setting this variable to destroy will remove this row from the vmtVpciMapGroupTable and also remove the corresponding entries from the vmtVpciMapListTable.

vmtVpciMapListTable.name: vmtVpciMapListTable
vmtVpciMapListTable.description: A table of VPCI mapping entries for VPCI mapping groups. A VPCI mapping list is composed of a list of VPCI mapping entries. All objects with the same value for vmtVpciMapGroupIndex are conceptually part of the same vmtVpciMapGroupEntry. Entries in this table may be added, deleted or modified only if the corresponding vpcigroup index is not being used by any signalling interface.

vmtVpciMapListEntry.name: vmtVpciMapListEntry
vmtVpciMapListEntry.description: A table entry holding one VPCI mapping entry in a VPCI mapping group.

vmtVpciMapListIndex.name: vmtVpciMapListIndex
vmtVpciMapListIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the order of a VPCI mapping entry in the VPCI mapping group in which it is used.

vmtVpciMapListMEIndex.name: vmtVpciMapListMEIndex
vmtVpciMapListMEIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the VPCI mapping entry in the vmtVpciMapTable for this entry.

vmtVpciMapListStatus.name: vmtVpciMapListStatus
vmtVpciMapListStatus.description: The status of this entry. This object can be set to destroy only if the corresponding vmtVpciMapGroupStatus is not Active.

perCallDbgFilterTable.name: perCallDbgFilterTable
perCallDbgFilterTable.description: A table of Per Call Debugging Filter entries.

perCallDbgFilterEntry.name: perCallDbgFilterEntry
perCallDbgFilterEntry.description: A table entry containing a Per Call Debugging filter.

perCallDbgFilterIndex.name: perCallDbgFilterIndex
perCallDbgFilterIndex.description: The value of the object indicates the index of this entry in the PCD table. A limit will be set as a constant to limit the number of filter that can exist at once.

perCallDbgFilterTemplateId.name: perCallDbgFilterTemplateId
perCallDbgFilterTemplateId.description: The value of this object reflects the index of the template to be used for this filter

perCallDbgFilterName.name: perCallDbgFilterName
perCallDbgFilterName.description: The value of this object reflects a name that will be printed out with the debug messages generated by this feature.

perCallDbgFilterFlavor.name: perCallDbgFilterFlavor
perCallDbgFilterFlavor.description: The value of this object reflects the type of debugging that has been enabled.

perCallDbgFilterMatches.name: perCallDbgFilterMatches
perCallDbgFilterMatches.description: The value of this object reflects the number of SVC setup messages matches that have been found for this filter.

perCallDbgFilterRowStatus.name: perCallDbgFilterRowStatus
perCallDbgFilterRowStatus.description: The status of this PCD filter entry.

perCallDbgTransFlag.name: perCallDbgTransFlag
perCallDbgTransFlag.description: Enables a switch to generate and print PCD debugging information when a switch receives a PCD GIT IE. The default value will be enabled.

nsapNetworkPrefixTable.name: nsapNetworkPrefixTable
nsapNetworkPrefixTable.description: A table of Network Prefix addresses

nsapNetworkPrefixEntry.name: nsapNetworkPrefixEntry
nsapNetworkPrefixEntry.description: An entry in the Network Prefix table.

nsapNetworkPrefixPort.name: nsapNetworkPrefixPort
nsapNetworkPrefixPort.description: The value of this object identifies the port of this signalling path, and is the same as nsapPort.

nsapNetworkPrefixVPI.name: nsapNetworkPrefixVPI
nsapNetworkPrefixVPI.description: The value of this object identifies the VPI (Virtual Path Identifier) of this signaling path statistics entry, and is the same as nsapVPI.

nsapNetworkPrefixValue.name: nsapNetworkPrefixValue
nsapNetworkPrefixValue.description: The network prefix for ATM addresses which is in effect on the user-side of the ATM UNI port.

nsapNetworkPrefixStatus.name: nsapNetworkPrefixStatus
nsapNetworkPrefixStatus.description: The status of this Network Prefix entry. Setting this object to invalid(4) causes this Network to disappear.

nsapTopologyTable.name: nsapTopologyTable
nsapTopologyTable.description: A table for NSAP (Network Service Access Point) topology, based on NSAP routing.

nsapTopologyEntry.name: nsapTopologyEntry
nsapTopologyEntry.description: An entry in the NSAP (Network Service Access Point) topology table.

nsapTopoBoard.name: nsapTopoBoard
nsapTopoBoard.description: The index of the switch board within the ATM switch cluster. This object is the same as the swBoardIndex.

nsapTopoLinkSrc.name: nsapTopoLinkSrc
nsapTopoLinkSrc.description: The value of this object identifies the source NSAP (Network Service Access Point) address of this link.

nsapTopoLinkSrcMask.name: nsapTopoLinkSrcMask
nsapTopoLinkSrcMask.description: The value of this object identifies the mask that is used for the link source NSAP (Network Service Access Point) address. The mask identifies the number of bits in the NSAP address that are valid. The value of the mask object is in the range 0-160 (160 bits is the size of an NSAP address).

nsapTopoLinkSrcPort.name: nsapTopoLinkSrcPort
nsapTopoLinkSrcPort.description: This object identifies the physical port of the link source.

nsapTopoLinkSrcVpi.name: nsapTopoLinkSrcVpi
nsapTopoLinkSrcVpi.description: This object identifies the virtual path identifier of the link source.

nsapTopoLinkDest.name: nsapTopoLinkDest
nsapTopoLinkDest.description: The value of this object identifies the destination NSAP (Network Service Access Point) address of this link.

nsapTopoLinkDestMask.name: nsapTopoLinkDestMask
nsapTopoLinkDestMask.description: The value of this object identifies the mask that is used for the link destination NSAP (Network Service Access Point) address. The mask identifies the number of bits in the NSAP address that are valid. The value of the mask object is in the range 0-160 (160 bits is the size of an NSAP address).

nsapTopoLinkDestPort.name: nsapTopoLinkDestPort
nsapTopoLinkDestPort.description: This object identifies the physical port of the link destination.

nsapTopoLinkDestVpi.name: nsapTopoLinkDestVpi
nsapTopoLinkDestVpi.description: This object identifies the virtual path identifier of the link destination.

nsapTopoLinkCost.name: nsapTopoLinkCost
nsapTopoLinkCost.description: The routing metric for this link.

nsapTopoLinkCbrCapacity.name: nsapTopoLinkCbrCapacity
nsapTopoLinkCbrCapacity.description: The available capacity for additional CBR (Constant Bit Rate) connections. The available capacity is measured in Kbps.

nsapTopoLinkCbrFifo.name: nsapTopoLinkCbrFifo
nsapTopoLinkCbrFifo.description: The size of the FIFO queue that is used for transmitting CBR (Constant Bit Rate) traffic. The size of the fifo is measured in number of cells.

nsapTopoLinkVbrCapacity.name: nsapTopoLinkVbrCapacity
nsapTopoLinkVbrCapacity.description: The available capacity for additional VBR (Variable Bit Rate) connections. The available capacity is measured in Kbps.

nsapTopoLinkVbrFifo.name: nsapTopoLinkVbrFifo
nsapTopoLinkVbrFifo.description: The size of the FIFO queue that is used for transmitting VBR (Variable Bit Rate) traffic. The size of the fifo is measured in number of cells.

nsapTopoLinkOrig.name: nsapTopoLinkOrig
nsapTopoLinkOrig.description: The source of this route information.

nsapTopoLinkCapabilitySet.name: nsapTopoLinkCapabilitySet
nsapTopoLinkCapabilitySet.description: A bitmap indicate the capabilities of this link. For example, whether the link support ABR (Available Bit Rate) traffic.

nsapTopoLinkFreshness.name: nsapTopoLinkFreshness
nsapTopoLinkFreshness.description: This object indicates the freshness (or staleness) of this NSAP (Network Service Access Point) link. As the number increases, the link becomes stale.

nsapTopoLinkUbrEstimatedBandwidth.name: nsapTopoLinkUbrEstimatedBandwidth
nsapTopoLinkUbrEstimatedBandwidth.description: The estimated UBR bandwidth on this link.

nsapStaticRouteTable.name: nsapStaticRouteTable
nsapStaticRouteTable.description: A table for static NSAP (Network Service Access Point) route administration.

nsapStaticRouteEntry.name: nsapStaticRouteEntry
nsapStaticRouteEntry.description: An entry in the NSAP (Network Service Access Point) static route administration table.

nsapStaticRouteAddress.name: nsapStaticRouteAddress
nsapStaticRouteAddress.description: The value of this object identifies the destination NSAP address

nsapStaticRouteMask.name: nsapStaticRouteMask
nsapStaticRouteMask.description: The value of this object identifies the mask that is used for this NSAP (Network Service Access Point) address.

nsapStaticRoutePort.name: nsapStaticRoutePort
nsapStaticRoutePort.description: The value of this object identifies the port through which this NSAP (Network Service Access Point) address can be reached.

nsapStaticRouteVPI.name: nsapStaticRouteVPI
nsapStaticRouteVPI.description: The value of this object identifies the path through which this NSAP (Network Service Access Point) address can be reached.

nsapStaticRouteCost.name: nsapStaticRouteCost
nsapStaticRouteCost.description: The value of this object identifies the cost associated with this Static Route. This cost is to be used as a metric while routing

nsapStaticRouteMaxCbrCap.name: nsapStaticRouteMaxCbrCap
nsapStaticRouteMaxCbrCap.description: The value of this object identifies the maximum capacity available on this route for CBR connections

nsapStaticRouteMaxVbrCap.name: nsapStaticRouteMaxVbrCap
nsapStaticRouteMaxVbrCap.description: The value of this object identifies the maximum capacity available on this route for VBR connections

nsapStaticRouteAbrSupport.name: nsapStaticRouteAbrSupport
nsapStaticRouteAbrSupport.description: The value identifies the capability to support ABR traffic on this route

nsapStaticRouteEpdSupport.name: nsapStaticRouteEpdSupport
nsapStaticRouteEpdSupport.description: The value identifies the capability to support Early Packet Discard (EPD) on this route

nsapStaticRouteStatus.name: nsapStaticRouteStatus
nsapStaticRouteStatus.description: The status of this NSAP (Network Service Access Point) address. Setting this object to invalid(4) causes this NSAP address to disappear.

ftPnniDTLTable.name: ftPnniDTLTable
ftPnniDTLTable.description: A table of Designated Transit List entries. The DTLs represent statically configured FT-PNNI routes

ftPnniDTLEntry.name: ftPnniDTLEntry
ftPnniDTLEntry.description: An entry in the FT-PNNI DTLble. A DTL is formed by concatenating rows of the table for which the ftPnniDTLIndex is the same

ftPnniDTLIndex.name: ftPnniDTLIndex
ftPnniDTLIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the index of a (FT-PNNI) DTL in the table. A DTL (Designated Transit List) is a source route of entries comprising a FT-PNNI node and the corresponding logical output port at that node. The FT-PNNI node is given by the node's NSAP Prefix and mask. The logical port is given by the linkid and the VPI.

ftPnniDTLEntryIndex.name: ftPnniDTLEntryIndex
ftPnniDTLEntryIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the Index of an entry within a given DTL. A DTL is a source route and each entry in the DTL represents a single hop in the source route. Each hop is represented by a FT-PNNI node and the logical output port at that node. An entry in the DTL is given an index equal to its position in the source route. Thus the entry corresponding to the first hop is given an index of 1, the second hop an index of 2 and so on.

ftPnniDTLNodePrefix.name: ftPnniDTLNodePrefix
ftPnniDTLNodePrefix.description: This the Prefix part of the Node ID of this DTL entry. In FT-PNNI, The Node IDs are represented as prefixes, that represents both the ID of the node and a summary of reachable addresses

ftPnniDTLNodeMask.name: ftPnniDTLNodeMask
ftPnniDTLNodeMask.description: This the Mask corresponding to the ftPnniDTLNodePrefix. This gives the length of the above prefix in number of bits. This can vary from 0 to 104 (13 bytes).

ftPnniDTLPort.name: ftPnniDTLPort
ftPnniDTLPort.description: This is the output port at the Node given by the above Node ID. This is also the port to which the next node in the DTL (if there is one) is connected.

ftPnniDTLVPI.name: ftPnniDTLVPI
ftPnniDTLVPI.description: This is the output path in the output port above that is the signalling path to the peer given by the next node in the DTL.

ftPnniDTLStatus.name: ftPnniDTLStatus
ftPnniDTLStatus.description: The entry status of this entry in the table.

ftPnniSummaryTable.name: ftPnniSummaryTable
ftPnniSummaryTable.description: A table of Prefixes that are used for either summarizing or suppressing internal and exterior reachability information by the FT-PNNI routing protocol

ftPnniSummaryEntry.name: ftPnniSummaryEntry
ftPnniSummaryEntry.description: An entry in the FT-PNNI Summary table.

ftPnniSummaryAddress.name: ftPnniSummaryAddress
ftPnniSummaryAddress.description: The address prefix that is to be either summarized or suppressed by the FT-PNNI routing protocol

ftPnniSummaryPrefixLength.name: ftPnniSummaryPrefixLength
ftPnniSummaryPrefixLength.description: This value is the mask for the address. This gives length of the address prefix in number of bits

ftPnniSummaryType.name: ftPnniSummaryType
ftPnniSummaryType.description: This value identifies the type of the summary being described

ftPnniSummarySuppress.name: ftPnniSummarySuppress
ftPnniSummarySuppress.description: The Suppress flag determinces what is to be done with this address. The default value (no) will indicate that the summary should be propagated. If the value is yes, this summary and any reachable address it summarizes are suppressed for being propagated

ftPnniSummaryState.name: ftPnniSummaryState
ftPnniSummaryState.description: This value indicates whether the summary is currently being advertised by the FT-PNNI routing protocol

ftPnniSummaryStatus.name: ftPnniSummaryStatus
ftPnniSummaryStatus.description: The entry status of this entry in the table.

upcContractTable.name: upcContractTable
upcContractTable.description: A table of user defined UPC traffic contracts.

upcContractEntry.name: upcContractEntry
upcContractEntry.description: A table entry containing a user defined UPC traffic contract.

upcContractKey.name: upcContractKey
upcContractKey.description: The key of this UPC configuration.

upcContractEntryStatus.name: upcContractEntryStatus
upcContractEntryStatus.description: The SNMP status of this upcContract entry.

upcContractPCR01.name: upcContractPCR01
upcContractPCR01.description: The peak cell rate (cells/sec) for cell loss priority 0+1

upcContractSCR01.name: upcContractSCR01
upcContractSCR01.description: The sustained cell rate (cells/sec) for cell loss priority 0+1

upcContractMBS01.name: upcContractMBS01
upcContractMBS01.description: The maximum burst size (cells) for cell loss priority 0+1

upcContractPCR0.name: upcContractPCR0
upcContractPCR0.description: The peak cell rate (cells/sec) for cell loss priority 0

upcContractSCR0.name: upcContractSCR0
upcContractSCR0.description: The sustained cell rate (cells/sec) for cell loss priority 0

upcContractMBS0.name: upcContractMBS0
upcContractMBS0.description: The maximum burst size (cells) for cell loss priority 0.

upcContractCDVT.name: upcContractCDVT
upcContractCDVT.description: The Cell Delay Variation Tolerance associated with PCR's. The Default CDVT values (in microseconds) for the various physical media are: DS1_DEFAULT_LINK_CDVT - 5000 DS3_DEFAULT_LINK_CDVT - 2500 E1_DEFAULT_LINK_CDVT - 5000 E3_DEFAULT_LINK_CDVT - 2500 J2_DEFAULT_LINK_CDVT - 5000 SONET_OC3_LINK_DEFAULT_CDVT - 250 SONET_OC12_LINK_DEFAULT_CDVT - 250 SONET_OC48_LINK_DEFAULT_CDVT - 250 TAXI_DEFAULT_LINK_CDVT - 1000 TP25_DEFAULT_LINK_CDVT - 5000 CTRLPORT_DEFAULT_LINK_CDVT - 5000 BACKPLANE_DEFAULT_LINK_CDVT - 100

upcContractTagReq.name: upcContractTagReq
upcContractTagReq.description: Should we tag (instead of drop) non-compliant CLP=0 cells?.

upcContractAal5Epd.name: upcContractAal5Epd
upcContractAal5Epd.description: Should we do AAL5 EPD on this connection?. This variable has been subsumed by the two new variables upcContractIsAAL5 and upcContractdoPacketDiscard. These new variables allow us to decouple the AAL5'ness of a connection from whether we are going to do packet discard on it if it is AAL5.

upcContractName.name: upcContractName
upcContractName.description: The name associated with this UPC traffic contract.

upcContractDoGCRAPolicing.name: upcContractDoGCRAPolicing
upcContractDoGCRAPolicing.description: Should we suppress GCRA policing on connections using this UPC Contract ?

upcContractIsAAL5.name: upcContractIsAAL5
upcContractIsAAL5.description: Is this UPC contract using AAL5?

upcContractDoPacketDiscard.name: upcContractDoPacketDiscard
upcContractDoPacketDiscard.description: Should we perform AAL5 Packet Discard (EPD/PPD) on this UPC contract. This variable only has meaning if the connection is also AAL5

upcContractDoPPPolicing.name: upcContractDoPPPolicing
upcContractDoPPPolicing.description: Should we perform AAL5 Partial Packet Policing on this UPC contract. This variable only has meaning if the connections is also AAL5.

upcContractDoUBRTagging.name: upcContractDoUBRTagging
upcContractDoUBRTagging.description: Should we perform tagging (set CLP=1) of all cells of connections that use this UBR traffic contract?

upcContractSchedMode.name: upcContractSchedMode
upcContractSchedMode.description: This variable indicates the scheduling mode that is requested for connections that use this UPC contract.

upcContractUseAltCLPThreshold.name: upcContractUseAltCLPThreshold
upcContractUseAltCLPThreshold.description: This flag determines whether the Series-DW per-VC Alternate CLP Threshold should be used for all non-ABR VC's created with this UPC contract.

upcContractMCR.name: upcContractMCR
upcContractMCR.description: The minimum cell rate (cells/sec) for ABR connections.

upcContractEstimatedUbrBandwidth.name: upcContractEstimatedUbrBandwidth
upcContractEstimatedUbrBandwidth.description: The estimated UBR bandwidth in Kilo-CPS associated with this UPC contract

upcContractAAL5CountingMode.name: upcContractAAL5CountingMode
upcContractAAL5CountingMode.description: The Counter mode for an AAL5 connection

upcContractServiceCategory.name: upcContractServiceCategory
upcContractServiceCategory.description: Index of this service category within serviceCategoryTable

upcContractPoliceScheme.name: upcContractPoliceScheme
upcContractPoliceScheme.description: It identifies the policing associated with the UPC contract as defined in the ATM Forum TM 4.0 specifications. However, the policing schemes cbr0 and cbr0tag are specific to FORE switches

upcContractSCR.name: upcContractSCR
upcContractSCR.description: The sustained cell rate (cells/sec). It also holds the PCR0 value for cbr0 & cbr0tag contracts

upcContractServiceSubCategory.name: upcContractServiceSubCategory
upcContractServiceSubCategory.description: The Service subcategory for this connection.Default value is 1.

upcContractCongestionBasedPeakBw.name: upcContractCongestionBasedPeakBw
upcContractCongestionBasedPeakBw.description: The expected peak bandwidth for this congestion based UPC contract

upcContractBehaviorClassSelector.name: upcContractBehaviorClassSelector
upcContractBehaviorClassSelector.description: The behavior class selector (BCS) for this UPC contract

qosClassExpansionTable.name: qosClassExpansionTable
qosClassExpansionTable.description: A table of user defined QOS Class Expansions.

qosClassExpansionEntry.name: qosClassExpansionEntry
qosClassExpansionEntry.description: A table entry containing a user defined QOS Class Expansion.

qosClassExpansionKey.name: qosClassExpansionKey
qosClassExpansionKey.description: The unique key for the set of entries in this table that make up a QOS Class Mapping table. Only one entry for each Class is allowed per key.

qosClassValue.name: qosClassValue
qosClassValue.description: QOS Class which needs to be expanded. If a class does not exist for a specific Expansion Key, all qos parameters will be interpreted as any acceptable qos parameter value.

qosClassExpansionEntryStatus.name: qosClassExpansionEntryStatus
qosClassExpansionEntryStatus.description: The SNMP status of this Expansion entry.

qosClassFwdCtd.name: qosClassFwdCtd
qosClassFwdCtd.description: The maximum acceptable forward Cell Transfer Delay in microseconds to be used for this expansion. A value of 16777215 will signify any acceptable forward CTD value.

qosClassFwdCdv.name: qosClassFwdCdv
qosClassFwdCdv.description: The maximum acceptable peak to peak forward Cell Delay Variation in micro-seconds to be used for this expansion. A value of 16777215 will signify any acceptable forward CDV value.

qosClassBackCdv.name: qosClassBackCdv
qosClassBackCdv.description: The maximum acceptable peak to peak backward Cell Delay Variation in micro-seconds to be used for this expansion. A value of 16777215 will signify any acceptable backward CDV value.

qosClassFwdClr.name: qosClassFwdClr
qosClassFwdClr.description: 10 raised to the power of this value signifies the maximum acceptable forward Cell Loss Ratio value to be used for this expansion. The valid values are from 1 to 15 (both inclusive) and 255. A value of 255 will signify any acceptable forward CLR value.

qosClassBackClr.name: qosClassBackClr
qosClassBackClr.description: 10 raised to the power of this value signifies the maximum acceptable backward Cell Loss Ratio value to be used for this expansion. The valid values are from 1 to 15 (both inclusive) and 255. A value of 255 will signify any acceptable backward CLR value.

qosClassName.name: qosClassName
qosClassName.description: A name associated with this entry in the qos class table

pathExtQosMetricTable.name: pathExtQosMetricTable
pathExtQosMetricTable.description: Qos metric table for path extension

pathExtQosMetricMaxClr.name: pathExtQosMetricMaxClr
pathExtQosMetricMaxClr.description: cell loss ratio. 10**(-n) where n is the returned value

pathExtEntry.name: pathExtEntry
pathExtEntry.description: A table entry containing path Qos Metric information.

pathExtCbrMetric.name: pathExtCbrMetric
pathExtCbrMetric.description: index to the path ext qos metric table

pathExtRtVbrMetric.name: pathExtRtVbrMetric
pathExtRtVbrMetric.description: index to the path ext qos metric table

pathExtNrtVbrMetric.name: pathExtNrtVbrMetric
pathExtNrtVbrMetric.description: index to the path ext qos metric table

pathExtAbrMetric.name: pathExtAbrMetric
pathExtAbrMetric.description: index to the path ext qos metric table

pathExtUbrMetric.name: pathExtUbrMetric
pathExtUbrMetric.description: index to the path ext qos metric table

opathExtCbrMetric.name: opathExtCbrMetric
opathExtCbrMetric.description: index to the path ext qos metric table

opathExtRtVbrMetric.name: opathExtRtVbrMetric
opathExtRtVbrMetric.description: index to the path ext qos metric table

opathExtNrtVbrMetric.name: opathExtNrtVbrMetric
opathExtNrtVbrMetric.description: index to the path ext qos metric table

opathExtAbrMetric.name: opathExtAbrMetric
opathExtAbrMetric.description: index to the path ext qos metric table

opathExtUbrMetric.name: opathExtUbrMetric
opathExtUbrMetric.description: index to the path ext qos metric table

vpGroupIndex.name: vpGroupIndex
vpGroupIndex.description: Zero mean not belong to any vpgroup group

poolConfPPCalls.name: poolConfPPCalls
poolConfPPCalls.description: Specifies the number of point to point calls that the switch should handle through pools. The switch comes up with enough resources in the pools to handle so many point to point calls. The new value will take effect at the next reboot.

poolConfPMPCalls.name: poolConfPMPCalls
poolConfPMPCalls.description: Specifies the number of point to multipoint calls that the switch should handle through pools. The switch comes up with enough resources in the pools to handle so many point to multipoint calls. The new value will take effect at the next reboot.

poolConfMaxPercentage.name: poolConfMaxPercentage
poolConfMaxPercentage.description: Limits the max percentage of the main heap that can be taken for pool configuration purposes.

swBoardTable.name: swBoardTable
swBoardTable.description: A table of ATM switch cluster configuration information.

swBoardEntry.name: swBoardEntry
swBoardEntry.description: A table entry containing ATM switch cluster information, index by the switch board.

swBoardIndex.name: swBoardIndex
swBoardIndex.description: The index of this switch board within the ATM switch cluster.

swBoardMaxPaths.name: swBoardMaxPaths
swBoardMaxPaths.description: The maximum number of input VPIs (Virtual Path Identifier) on this switch board.

swBoardMaxChannels.name: swBoardMaxChannels
swBoardMaxChannels.description: The maximum number of input VCIs (Virtual Channel Identifiers) on this switch board.

swBoardAtmAddress.name: swBoardAtmAddress
swBoardAtmAddress.description: The address of this ATM switch board.

swBoardUptime.name: swBoardUptime
swBoardUptime.description: The length of time this ATM switch board has been up, in hundredths of a second.

swBoardCDV.name: swBoardCDV
swBoardCDV.description: The switch board Cell Delay Variation (CDV) specified in microseconds, indicates the time window in which a cell may be received on a connection and be accepted. A cell that is received on a connection outside the CDV window will be tagged or dropped as indicated by the swBoardPolicingAction object. The boardCDV is the default CDV for all the connection on this switch board. Individual connections can be set to explicitly override this value.

swBoardPolicingAction.name: swBoardPolicingAction
swBoardPolicingAction.description: This object indicates the action the switch board will take in case of bandwidth violation. The swBoardPolicingAction is the default policing action for all the connections on this switch board. Individual connections can be set to explicitly override this default action.

swBoardNsapPrefix.name: swBoardNsapPrefix
swBoardNsapPrefix.description: The default NSAP (Network Service Access Point) prefix for this ATM switch board. The NSAP prefix will be used in the ILMI address registration message as well as the 'hello-indication' SPANS-NNI message.

swBoardClockScalingFactor.name: swBoardClockScalingFactor
swBoardClockScalingFactor.description: This specifies the value written into the switch boards Time Scaling Factor register. See Sec. 3.2.1 for more info. The Time Scaling Factor is an 8-bit register that determines the number of 25ns clock cycles that occur between increments of the Time and Interrupt Timer Reigsters. Increasing the Time Scale Factor increases the burst tolerance that can be represented by the policer (in multiples of .838 seconds) while reducing the precision of the policer by a similar factor. The possible values for this variable are 1 through 255.

swBoardDebugMode.name: swBoardDebugMode
swBoardDebugMode.description: This object indicates whether or not debugging services are available for this switch.

swBoardMulticastMode.name: swBoardMulticastMode
swBoardMulticastMode.description: This object identifies the mode in which this ATM switch board is operating. Extended-mode provides greater flexibility when selecting VCI for point to multipoint connections. Non-extended (mixed) mode is more restrictive. If any series A or B netmods are present, the switch board should operate in non-extended mode.

swBoardFingerMode.name: swBoardFingerMode
swBoardFingerMode.description: This object indicates whether or not finger services are available for this switch.

swBoardATMLayerOAM.name: swBoardATMLayerOAM
swBoardATMLayerOAM.description: This object specifies whether the processing of ATM layer OAM cells by this switch board is enabled or disabled.

swBoardTopoTable.name: swBoardTopoTable
swBoardTopoTable.description: A table of switch board topology general information.

swBoardTopoEntry.name: swBoardTopoEntry
swBoardTopoEntry.description: A table entry containing switch board topology information.

swBoardTopoIndex.name: swBoardTopoIndex
swBoardTopoIndex.description: The index of this switch board within the ATM switch cluster. This object should be the same as the swBoardIndex.

swBoardTopoNumberOfLinks.name: swBoardTopoNumberOfLinks
swBoardTopoNumberOfLinks.description: Current number of inter-switch links known by this switch board.

swBoardLinkTable.name: swBoardLinkTable
swBoardLinkTable.description: A table of ATM links that are known to a given switch board in the switch cluster. If all boards in the switch cluster are interconnected, all swBoardLinkEntries will be identical.

swBoardLinkEntry.name: swBoardLinkEntry
swBoardLinkEntry.description: A table entry containing link information known to a given switch board.

swBoardLinkIndex.name: swBoardLinkIndex
swBoardLinkIndex.description: The index of this switch board within the ATM switch cluster. This object should be the same as the swBoardIndex.

swBoardLinkSrc.name: swBoardLinkSrc
swBoardLinkSrc.description: The ATM address of the source switch of this link.

swBoardLinkDest.name: swBoardLinkDest
swBoardLinkDest.description: The ATM address of the destination switch of this link.

swBoardLinkCapacity.name: swBoardLinkCapacity
swBoardLinkCapacity.description: The free capacity of this link in kilobits per second.

swBoardLinkAge.name: swBoardLinkAge
swBoardLinkAge.description: The freshness of the information about this link. The actual value has no units associated with it. It should be used for comparison.

oamGeneratingChannelTable.name: oamGeneratingChannelTable
oamGeneratingChannelTable.description: When an AIS cell is generated on a particular channel it gets added to this table. If a channel is deleted the corresponding entry is removed from this table.

oamGeneratingChannelEntry.name: oamGeneratingChannelEntry
oamGeneratingChannelEntry.description: A table entry containing a channel which has generated AIS cells.

oamGeneratingChannelCells.name: oamGeneratingChannelCells
oamGeneratingChannelCells.description: The number of AIS OAM cells generated on this channel.

oamGeneratingOpathTable.name: oamGeneratingOpathTable
oamGeneratingOpathTable.description: When an RDI cell is generated on a particular outgoing path it gets added to this table. If an outgoing path is deleted the corresponding entry is removed from this table.

oamGeneratingOpathEntry.name: oamGeneratingOpathEntry
oamGeneratingOpathEntry.description: A table entry containing an outgoing path which has generated RDI cells.

oamGeneratingOpathCells.name: oamGeneratingOpathCells
oamGeneratingOpathCells.description: The number of RDI OAM cells generated on this path.

oamGeneratingPathrTable.name: oamGeneratingPathrTable
oamGeneratingPathrTable.description: When an AIS cell is generated on a particular through path it gets added to this table. If a through path is deleted the corresponding entry is removed from this table.

oamGeneratingPathrEntry.name: oamGeneratingPathrEntry
oamGeneratingPathrEntry.description: A table entry containing a through path which has generated AIS cells.

oamGeneratingPathrCells.name: oamGeneratingPathrCells
oamGeneratingPathrCells.description: The number of AIS OAM cells generated on this path.

oamReceivedPathTable.name: oamReceivedPathTable
oamReceivedPathTable.description: When an OAM cell is received on a particular terminating path it gets added to this table. If a terminating path is deleted the corresponding entry is removed from this table.

oamReceivedPathEntry.name: oamReceivedPathEntry
oamReceivedPathEntry.description: A table entry containing a terminating path which has received OAM cells.

oamReceivedPathAISCells.name: oamReceivedPathAISCells
oamReceivedPathAISCells.description: The number of AIS OAM cells received on this path.

oamReceivedPathRDICells.name: oamReceivedPathRDICells
oamReceivedPathRDICells.description: The number of RDI OAM cells received on this path.

guardTable.name: guardTable
guardTable.description: The OAM guards for each board in a switch.

guardEntry.name: guardEntry
guardEntry.description: A table entry containing the guards for a board.

oamGuard.name: oamGuard
oamGuard.description: The value of sysUpTime the last time an OAM cell was generated/received on this board.

trapNumberOfDest.name: trapNumberOfDest
trapNumberOfDest.description: The current number of configured trap destinations. All traps are sent to all destinations.

trapDestTable.name: trapDestTable
trapDestTable.description: A table of destinations to which the agent sends traps.

trapDestEntry.name: trapDestEntry
trapDestEntry.description: A table entry containing address of a management station, to which the agent sends traps.

trapDest.name: trapDest
trapDest.description: Address to which the agent sends traps. Usually a network management station sets this address to itself.

trapDestStatus.name: trapDestStatus
trapDestStatus.description: The status of this trap destination entry.

snmpReconfigure.name: snmpReconfigure
snmpReconfigure.description: The SNMP agent will reset itself and reconfigure its database from the default database when this variable is set to enable(2). After reconfiguring is done, the value of this object is disable(1). Note that enabling snmpReconfigure will end up with a loss of the entire ATM configuration.

snmpReadCommunity.name: snmpReadCommunity
snmpReadCommunity.description: The community string used for SNMP (v1) read operations, i.e. get and getnext requests. This has been deprecated, since it's now possible to have more than one read community string. Setting this variable will result in all current read community strings being deleted, and this one added. Note this object is write-only and reading it will result in implementation-specific results.

snmpWriteCommunity.name: snmpWriteCommunity
snmpWriteCommunity.description: The community string used for SNMP (v1) write operations, i.e. set requests. This has been deprecated, since it's now possible to have more than one write community string. Setting this variable will result in all current write community strings being deleted, and this one added. Note this object is write-only and reading it will result in implementation-specific results.

snmpWarmStart.name: snmpWarmStart
snmpWarmStart.description: The SNMP agent will reset the switch, and restart the switch control software using the existing configuration database when this variable is set to enable(2). After the warm start, the value of this object is disable(1). A warmStart trap is sent after the switch control software restarts.

snmpColdStart.name: snmpColdStart
snmpColdStart.description: The SNMP agent will reset the configuration database for all ATM related configuration objects, and reboot the switch, when this variable is set to enableResetAtmConf(2). When the value of this variable is set to enableResetAllConf(3), all configuration objects, including ATM and IP objects will be removed, and the switch will be rebooted. A coldStart trap is sent just before the trap destination table is removed. After the cold start, the value of this object is disable(1).

snmpRemoteSetsStatus.name: snmpRemoteSetsStatus
snmpRemoteSetsStatus.description: The value of this object controls SNMP set operations from remote management stations. The default value is enabled(1). If it is set to disabled(2), set requests from remote management stations will not be processed and an authorization error is returned. This value can be set only by the manager running on this device.

snmpThisAgentBoardNumber.name: snmpThisAgentBoardNumber
snmpThisAgentBoardNumber.description: The instance of this agent type within the enclosure; typically a board number.

snmpAgentTable.name: snmpAgentTable
snmpAgentTable.description: A table of SNMP agent IP addresses. Each entry in this table represents an IP address which may be used to reach the associated SNMP agent, assuming appropriate network connectivity.

snmpAgentEntry.name: snmpAgentEntry
snmpAgentEntry.description: A table entry containing the identity and address of an SNMP agent.

snmpAgentBoardNumber.name: snmpAgentBoardNumber
snmpAgentBoardNumber.description: The number of the SNMP agent within this enclosure. This generally corresponds to a board number.

snmpAgentInterface.name: snmpAgentInterface
snmpAgentInterface.description: An interface number associated with the agent IP address. This number is for tabulation purposes only, and has no other significance.

snmpAgentAddress.name: snmpAgentAddress
snmpAgentAddress.description: The IP address of the identified SNMP agent.

asxSwLinkDown.name: asxSwLinkDown
asxSwLinkDown.description: An asxSwLinkDown trap signifies that the sending protocol entity recognizes a failure in one of the ATM Switch links that is connected to another switch.

asxSwLinkUp.name: asxSwLinkUp
asxSwLinkUp.description: An asxSwLinkUp trap signifies that the sending protocol entity recognizes that one of the ATM Switch links that is connected to another switch has come up.

asxHostLinkDown.name: asxHostLinkDown
asxHostLinkDown.description: An asxHostLinkDown trap signifies that the sending protocol entity recognizes a failure in one of the ATM Switch links that is connected to a host.

asxHostLinkUp.name: asxHostLinkUp
asxHostLinkUp.description: An asxHostLinkUp trap signifies that the sending protocol entity recognizes that one of the ATM Switch links that is connected to a host has come up.

asxNetModuleDown.name: asxNetModuleDown
asxNetModuleDown.description: An asxNetModuleDown trap signifies that the sending protocol entity recognizes a failure in one of the ATM Switch network modules, that is identified by the board and the module numbers. This is probably caused by a hot-swap of a network module.

asxNetModuleUp.name: asxNetModuleUp
asxNetModuleUp.description: An asxNetModuleUp trap signifies that the sending protocol entity recognizes a new operational ATM Switch network module, that is identified by the board and the module numbers. This is probably caused by a hot-swap of a network module.

asxPsInputDown.name: asxPsInputDown
asxPsInputDown.description: This trap alerts that one ATM switch power supply failed due to failure in the input voltage. The power supply that failed is identified by the power supply index. Note that an input voltage may be out of spec and may not cause a power supply failure if high loads are not applied.

asxPsInputUp.name: asxPsInputUp
asxPsInputUp.description: This trap alerts that one ATM switch power supply that had an input failure is up. The power supply that is back up is identified by the power supply index.

asxPsOutputDown.name: asxPsOutputDown
asxPsOutputDown.description: This trap alerts that one ATM switch power supply output failed, or the power supply was physically removed. The power supply that failed is identified by the power supply index.

asxPsOutputUp.name: asxPsOutputUp
asxPsOutputUp.description: This trap alerts that one ATM switch power supply that had an output failure or was removed is now up. The power supply that is back up is identified by the power supply index.

asxFanBankDown.name: asxFanBankDown
asxFanBankDown.description: This trap alerts that one ATM switch fan bank failed. The fan bank that failed is identified by the fan bank index.

asxFanBankUp.name: asxFanBankUp
asxFanBankUp.description: This trap alerts that one ATM switch fan bank is up. The fan bank that is back up is identified by the fan bank index.

asxLinkDown.name: asxLinkDown
asxLinkDown.description: This trap alerts that the link that is identified by portName was configured up, but its underlying physical layer has lost its carrier (or the framing bit) and is currently down.

asxLinkUp.name: asxLinkUp
asxLinkUp.description: This trap alerts that the link that is identified by portName is back up.

asxSpansDown.name: asxSpansDown
asxSpansDown.description: This trap alerts that the SPANS signalling on the link that is identified by the sigPathPort and sigPathVPI failed.

asxSpansUp.name: asxSpansUp
asxSpansUp.description: This trap alerts that the SPANS signalling on the link that is identified by the sigPathPort and sigPathVPI is up.

asxTempSensorOverTemp.name: asxTempSensorOverTemp
asxTempSensorOverTemp.description: This trap alerts that one of the temperature sensors indicates over temperature. The temperature sensor is identified by the temperature sensor index.

asxTempSensorRegularTemp.name: asxTempSensorRegularTemp
asxTempSensorRegularTemp.description: This trap alerts that one of the temperature sensors indicates regular temperature. The temperature sensor is identified by the temperature sensor index.

asxFabricTemperatureOverTemp.name: asxFabricTemperatureOverTemp
asxFabricTemperatureOverTemp.description: This trap alerts that one of the temperature sensors indicates over temperature. The temperature sensor is identified by the temperature sensor index.

asxFabricTemperatureRegularTemp.name: asxFabricTemperatureRegularTemp
asxFabricTemperatureRegularTemp.description: This trap alerts that one of the temperature sensors indicates regular temperature. The temperature sensor is identified by the temperature sensor index.

asxSonetLOSDetected.name: asxSonetLOSDetected
asxSonetLOSDetected.description: This trap indicates that the specified SONET port is experiencing Loss Of Signal. Bellcore Document TA-NWT-000253 Section 6.3.1.1.1 states that... A SONET NE shall declare a LOS failure when the LOS defect persists for 2.5 (+- .5) seconds, or when a LOS defect is present and the criteria for LOF failure declaration have been met.

asxSonetLOSCleared.name: asxSonetLOSCleared
asxSonetLOSCleared.description: This trap indicates that the LOS condition identified by trap asxSonetLOSDetected has been cleared.

asxSonetPathLabelDetected.name: asxSonetPathLabelDetected
asxSonetPathLabelDetected.description: This trap indicates that the specified SONET port is receiving and errored C2 Path Label byte. Reference Bellcore Document TA-NWT-000253 Section 3.3.2.3 and 6.3.1.1.8 the Path Label (C2) byte should have the value 0x13 or 0x01.

asxSonetPathLabelCleared.name: asxSonetPathLabelCleared
asxSonetPathLabelCleared.description: This trap indicates that the Errored Path Label (C2) byte error condition signaled by the asxSonetPathLabelDetected trap has been cleared.

asxSonetLineAISDetected.name: asxSonetLineAISDetected
asxSonetLineAISDetected.description: This trap indicates that the specified SONET port is receiving a Line level Alarm Indication Signal from the far-end equipment.

asxSonetLineAISCleared.name: asxSonetLineAISCleared
asxSonetLineAISCleared.description: This trap indicates that the Line AIS error condition signaled by the asxSonetLineAISDetected trap has been cleared.

asxDS3PLCPYellowDetected.name: asxDS3PLCPYellowDetected
asxDS3PLCPYellowDetected.description: This trap indicates that the specified DS3 port has detected incoming PLCP Yellow Alarm.

asxDS3PLCPYellowCleared.name: asxDS3PLCPYellowCleared
asxDS3PLCPYellowCleared.description: This trap indicates that the specified DS3 port has detected clearance of incoming PLCP Yellow Alarm.

asxDS3PLCPLOFDetected.name: asxDS3PLCPLOFDetected
asxDS3PLCPLOFDetected.description: This trap indicates that the specified DS3 port has detected incoming PLCP LOF Alarm.

asxDS3PLCPLOFCleared.name: asxDS3PLCPLOFCleared
asxDS3PLCPLOFCleared.description: This trap indicates that the specified DS3 port has detected clearance of incoming PLCP LOF Alarm.

asxDS3LOFDetected.name: asxDS3LOFDetected
asxDS3LOFDetected.description: This trap indicates that Loss Of Frame(LOF) is detected on the incoming signal.

asxDS3LOFCleared.name: asxDS3LOFCleared
asxDS3LOFCleared.description: This trap indicates that Loss Of Frame is cleared on the incoming signal.

asxDS3AISDetected.name: asxDS3AISDetected
asxDS3AISDetected.description: This trap indicates that AIS Alarm is detected on the incoming signal.

asxDS3AISCleared.name: asxDS3AISCleared
asxDS3AISCleared.description: This trap indicates that AIS Alarm is cleared on the incoming signal.

asxDS1PLCPYellowDetected.description: This trap indicates that the specified DS1 port has detected incoming PLCP Yellow Alarm.

asxDS1PLCPYellowCleared.name: asxDS1PLCPYellowCleared
asxDS1PLCPYellowCleared.description: This trap indicates that the specified DS1 port has detected clearance of incoming PLCP Yellow Alarm.

asxDS1PLCPLOFDetected.name: asxDS1PLCPLOFDetected
asxDS1PLCPLOFDetected.description: This trap indicates that the specified DS1 port has detected incoming PLCP LOF Alarm.

asxDS1PLCPLOFCleared.name: asxDS1PLCPLOFCleared
asxDS1PLCPLOFCleared.description: This trap indicates that the specified DS1 port has detected clearance of incoming PLCP LOF Alarm.

asxDS1YellowDetected.description: This trap indicates that Yellow Alarm is detected on the incoming signal.

asxDS1YellowCleared.name: asxDS1YellowCleared
asxDS1YellowCleared.description: This trap indicates that Yellow Alarm is cleared on the incoming signal.

asxDS1AISDetected.description: This trap indicates that AIS Alarm is detected on the incoming signal.

asxDS1AISCleared.name: asxDS1AISCleared
asxDS1AISCleared.description: This trap indicates that AIS Alarm is cleared on the incoming signal.

asxDS1LOSDetected.description: This trap indicates that LOS Alarm is detected on the incoming signal.

asxDS1LOSCleared.name: asxDS1LOSCleared
asxDS1LOSCleared.description: This trap indicates that LOS Alarm is cleared on the incoming signal.

asxDS1LOFDetected.description: This trap indicates that LOF Alarm is detected on the incoming signal.

asxDS1LOFCleared.name: asxDS1LOFCleared
asxDS1LOFCleared.description: This trap indicates that LOF Alarm is cleared on the incoming signal.

asxDS3FERFDetected.name: asxDS3FERFDetected
asxDS3FERFDetected.description: This trap indicates that FERF Alarm or DS3 Yellow Alarm is detected on the incoming signal.

asxDS3FERFCleared.name: asxDS3FERFCleared
asxDS3FERFCleared.description: This trap indicates that FERF Alarm or DS3 Yellow Alarm is cleared on the incoming signal.

asxE3YellowDetected.name: asxE3YellowDetected
asxE3YellowDetected.description: This trap indicates that the Yellow Alarm is being detected on the incoming signal.

asxE3YellowCleared.name: asxE3YellowCleared
asxE3YellowCleared.description: This trap indicates that Yellow alarm has cleared on the incoming signal.

asxE3OOFDetected.name: asxE3OOFDetected

asxE3OOFCleared.name: asxE3OOFCleared
asxE3OOFCleared.description: This trap indicates that Loss Of Frame is cleared on the incoming signal.

asxE3AtmLCDDetected.name: asxE3AtmLCDDetected
asxE3AtmLCDDetected.description: This trap indicates that the specified E3 port is experiencing Loss of Cell Deliniation (LCD). A LCD failure is declared when the LCD defect persists for a period of 2.5 +/- 0.5 seconds.

asxE3AtmLCDCleared.name: asxE3AtmLCDCleared
asxE3AtmLCDCleared.description: This trap indicates that the LCD failure identified by trap asxE3AtmLCDDetected has been cleared. A LCD failure is cleared when the LCD defect is absent for 10 +/- 0.5 seconds.

asxE3PLCPYellowDetected.description: This trap indicates that the specified E3 port has detected incoming PLCP Yellow Alarm.

asxE1LOFCleared.name: asxE1LOFCleared

asxE1LOSDetected.name: asxE1LOSDetected
asxE1LOSDetected.description: This trap indicates that the specified E1 port has detected incoming LOS Alarm.

asxE1LOSCleared.name: asxE1LOSCleared
asxE1LOSCleared.description: This trap indicates that incoming LOS alarm has been cleared on the specified E1 port.

asxE1AISDetected.name: asxE1AISDetected
asxE1AISDetected.description: This trap indicates that the specified E1 port has detected incoming AIS Alarm.

asxE1AISCleared.name: asxE1AISCleared
asxE1AISCleared.description: This trap indicates that incoming AIS alarm has been cleared on the specified E1 port.

asxE3AISDetected.name: asxE3AISDetected
asxE3AISDetected.description: This trap indicates that the specified E3 port has detected incoming AIS Alarm.

asxE3AISCleared.description: This trap indicates that incoming AIS alarm has been cleared on the specified E3 port.

asxE3LOSDetected.name: asxE3LOSDetected
asxE3LOSDetected.description: This trap indicates that the specified E3 port has detected incoming LOS Alarm.

asxE3LOSCleared.name: asxE3LOSCleared
asxE3LOSCleared.description: This trap indicates that incoming LOS alarm has been cleared on the specified E3 port.

asxE3PLCPLOFDetected.name: asxE3PLCPLOFDetected

asxE3PLCPLOFCleared.name: asxE3PLCPLOFCleared
asxE3PLCPLOFCleared.description: This trap indicates that incoming PLCP LOF alarm has been cleared on the specified E3 port.

asxJ2YellowDetected.name: asxJ2YellowDetected
asxJ2YellowDetected.description: This trap indicates that Yellow Alarm is detected on the incoming signal.

asxJ2YellowCleared.name: asxJ2YellowCleared
asxJ2YellowCleared.description: This trap indicates that Yellow Alarm is cleared on the incoming signal.

asxJ2AISDetected.name: asxJ2AISDetected
asxJ2AISDetected.description: This trap indicates that AIS Alarm is detected on the incoming signal.

asxJ2AISCleared.name: asxJ2AISCleared
asxJ2AISCleared.description: This trap indicates that AIS Alarm is cleared on the incoming signal.

asxJ2LOSDetected.name: asxJ2LOSDetected
asxJ2LOSDetected.description: This trap indicates that LOS Alarm is detected on the incoming signal.

asxJ2LOSCleared.name: asxJ2LOSCleared
asxJ2LOSCleared.description: This trap indicates that LOS Alarm is cleared on the incoming signal.

asxJ2LOFDetected.name: asxJ2LOFDetected
asxJ2LOFDetected.description: This trap indicates that LOF Alarm is detected on the incoming signal.

asxJ2LOFCleared.name: asxJ2LOFCleared
asxJ2LOFCleared.description: This trap indicates that LOF Alarm is cleared on the incoming signal.

asxDS3LOSDetected.name: asxDS3LOSDetected
asxDS3LOSDetected.description: This trap indicates that the specified DS3 port has detected incoming LOS Alarm.

asxDS3LOSCleared.name: asxDS3LOSCleared
asxDS3LOSCleared.description: This trap indicates that the incoming LOS Alarm has been cleared on the specified DS3 port.

asxSonetLOFDetected.name: asxSonetLOFDetected
asxSonetLOFDetected.description: This trap indicates that the specified SONET port is experiencing Loss Of Frame (LOF) failure. An LOF failure is declared when the LOF defect persists fore a period of 2.5 +/- 0.5 seconds, except when an LOS defect or failure is present.

asxSonetLOFCleared.name: asxSonetLOFCleared
asxSonetLOFCleared.description: This trap indicates that the LOF failure identified by trap asxSonetLOFDetected has been cleared. The LOF failure is cleared when the LOS failure is declared, or when the LOF defect is absent for 10 +/- 0.5 seconds.

asxSonetLineRDIDetected.name: asxSonetLineRDIDetected
asxSonetLineRDIDetected.description: This trap indicates that the specified SONET port is experiencing Line Remote Defect Indication (LRDI). A Line RDI failure is declared when the incoming Line RDI defects lasts for 2.5 +/- 0.5 seconds.

asxSonetLineRDICleared.name: asxSonetLineRDICleared
asxSonetLineRDICleared.description: This trap indicates that the Line RDI failure identified by trap asxSonetLineRDIDetected has been cleared. The Line RDI failure is cleared when no Line RDI defects are detected for 10 +/- 0.5 seconds.

asxSonetPathAISDetected.name: asxSonetPathAISDetected
asxSonetPathAISDetected.description: This trap indicates that the specified SONET port is experiencing Path Alarm Inidication Signal (PAIS). A Path AIS failure is declared when the Path AIS defect persists for 2.5 +/- 0.5 seconds.

asxSonetPathAISCleared.name: asxSonetPathAISCleared
asxSonetPathAISCleared.description: This trap indicates that the PathAIS failure identified by trap asxSonetPathAISDetected has been cleared. A PAIS failure is cleared when the PAIS defect is absent for 10 +/- 0.5 seconds.

asxSonetPathLOPDetected.name: asxSonetPathLOPDetected
asxSonetPathLOPDetected.description: This trap indicates that the specified SONET port is experiencing Loss Of Pointer (LOP). A LOP failure is declared when the LOP defect persists for a period of 2.5 +/- 0.5 seconds.

asxSonetPathLOPCleared.name: asxSonetPathLOPCleared
asxSonetPathLOPCleared.description: This trap indicates that the LOP failure identified by trap asxSonetLOPDetected has been cleared. A LOP failure is cleared when the LOP defect is absent for 10 +/- 0.5 seconds.

asxSonetPathUNEQDetected.name: asxSonetPathUNEQDetected
asxSonetPathUNEQDetected.description: This trap indicates that the specified SONET port is experiencing unequiped (UNEQ). A UNEQ failure is declared when the UNEQ defect persists for a period of 2.5 +/- 0.5 seconds.

asxSonetPathUNEQCleared.name: asxSonetPathUNEQCleared
asxSonetPathUNEQCleared.description: This trap indicates that the UNEQ failure identified by trap asxSonetUNEQDetected has been cleared. A UNEQ failure is cleared when the UNEQ defect is absent for 10 +/- 0.5 seconds.

asxSonetPathRDIDetected.name: asxSonetPathRDIDetected
asxSonetPathRDIDetected.description: This trap indicates that the specified SONET port is experiencing Path Remote Defect Indication (PRDI). A Path RDI failure is declared when the incoming Path RDI defects lasts for 2.5 +/- 0.5 seconds.

asxSonetPathRDICleared.name: asxSonetPathRDICleared
asxSonetPathRDICleared.description: This trap indicates that the Path RDI failure identified by trap asxSonetPathRDIDetected has been cleared. The Path RDI failure is cleared when no Path RDI defects are detected for 10 +/- 0.5 seconds.

asxSonetAtmLCDDetected.name: asxSonetAtmLCDDetected
asxSonetAtmLCDDetected.description: This trap indicates that the specified SONET port is experiencing Loss of Cell Deliniation (LCD). A LCD failure is declared when the LCD defect persists for a period of 2.5 +/- 0.5 seconds.

asxSonetAtmLCDCleared.name: asxSonetAtmLCDCleared
asxSonetAtmLCDCleared.description: This trap indicates that the LCD failure identified by trap asxSonetAtmLCDDetected has been cleared. A LCD failure is cleared when the LCD defect is absent for 10 +/- 0.5 seconds.

asxSonetAtmLineBIPDetected.name: asxSonetAtmLineBIPDetected
asxSonetAtmLineBIPDetected.description: This trap indicates that the specified SONET port is experiencing Bit Interleaved Parity (BIP) errors. A Line BIP failure is declared when the Line BIP defect persists for a period of 2.5 +/- 0.5 seconds.

asxSonetAtmLineBIPCleared.name: asxSonetAtmLineBIPCleared
asxSonetAtmLineBIPCleared.description: This trap indicates that the Line BIP failure identified by trap asxSonetAtmLineBIPDetected has been cleared. A Line BIP failure is cleared when the Line BIP defect is absent for 10 +/- 0.5 seconds.

asxDS3IdleDetected.name: asxDS3IdleDetected
asxDS3IdleDetected.description: This trap indicates that an Idle Maintenance Signal (IDLE) is detected on the incoming signal.

asxDS3IdleCleared.name: asxDS3IdleCleared
asxDS3IdleCleared.description: This trap indicates that an Idle Maintenance Signal (IDLE) is cleared on the incoming signal.

asxDS3AtmLCDDetected.name: asxDS3AtmLCDDetected
asxDS3AtmLCDDetected.description: This trap indicates that the specified DS3 port is experiencing Loss of Cell Deliniation (LCD). A LCD failure is declared when the LCD defect persists for a period of 2.5 +/- 0.5 seconds.

asxDS3AtmLCDCleared.name: asxDS3AtmLCDCleared
asxDS3AtmLCDCleared.description: This trap indicates that the LCD failure identified by trap asxDS3AtmLCDDetected has been cleared. A LCD failure is cleared when the LCD defect is absent for 10 +/- 0.5 seconds.

asxDS3PbitPerrDetected.name: asxDS3PbitPerrDetected
asxDS3PbitPerrDetected.description: This trap indicates that the specified DS3 port is experiencing P-bit Parity errors. A P-bit Parity Error failure is declared when the P-bit Parity Error persists for a period of 2.5 +/- 0.5 seconds.

asxDS3PbitPerrCleared.name: asxDS3PbitPerrCleared
asxDS3PbitPerrCleared.description: This trap indicates that the P-bit Parity Error failure identified by trap asxDS3PbitPerrDetected has been cleared. A P-bit Parity Error failure is cleared when the P-bit Parity Error defect is absent for 10 +/- 0.5 seconds.

asxDS1PRBSDetected.name: asxDS1PRBSDetected
asxDS1PRBSDetected.description: This trap indicates that PRBS pattern is detected on the incoming signal.

asxDS1PRBSCleared.name: asxDS1PRBSCleared
asxDS1PRBSCleared.description: This trap indicates that PRBS pattern is cleared on the incoming signal.

asxDS1AtmLCDDetected.name: asxDS1AtmLCDDetected
asxDS1AtmLCDDetected.description: This trap indicates that the specified DS1 port is experiencing Loss of Cell Deliniation (LCD). A LCD failure is declared when the LCD defect persists for a period of 2.5 +/- 0.5 seconds.

asxDS1AtmLCDCleared.name: asxDS1AtmLCDCleared
asxDS1AtmLCDCleared.description: This trap indicates that the LCD failure identified by trap asxDS1AtmLCDDetected has been cleared. A LCD failure is cleared when the LCD defect is absent for 10 +/- 0.5 seconds.

asxDS1CRCErrDetected.name: asxDS1CRCErrDetected
asxDS1CRCErrDetected.description: This trap indicates that the specified DS1 port is experiencing excessive CRC-6 errors. A CRC-6 Error failure is declared when the CRC-6 Error persists for a period of 2.5 +/- 0.5 seconds.

asxDS1CRCErrCleared.name: asxDS1CRCErrCleared
asxDS1CRCErrCleared.description: This trap indicates that the excessive CRC-6 Error failure identified by trap asxDS1CRCErrDetected has been cleared. A CRC-6 Parity Error failure is cleared when the CRC-6 Error defect is absent for 10 +/- 0.5 seconds.

asxE3TrailChangeDetected.name: asxE3TrailChangeDetected
asxE3TrailChangeDetected.description: This trap indicates that a change in the trail trace message was detected on the incoming signal.

asxE1AtmLCDDetected.name: asxE1AtmLCDDetected
asxE1AtmLCDDetected.description: This trap indicates that the specified E1 port is experiencing Loss of Cell Deliniation (LCD). A LCD failure is declared when the LCD defect persists for a period of 2.5 +/- 0.5 seconds.

asxE1AtmLCDCleared.name: asxE1AtmLCDCleared
asxE1AtmLCDCleared.description: This trap indicates that the LCD failure identified by trap asxE1AtmLCDDetected has been cleared. A LCD failure is cleared when the LCD defect is absent for 10 +/- 0.5 seconds.

asxJ2RLOCDetected.name: asxJ2RLOCDetected
asxJ2RLOCDetected.description: This trap indicates that Receive Loss of Clock (RLOC) is detected on the incoming signal.

asxJ2RLOCCleared.name: asxJ2RLOCCleared
asxJ2RLOCCleared.description: This trap indicates that Receive Loss of Clock (RLOC) is cleared on the incoming signal.

asxJ2HBERDetected.name: asxJ2HBERDetected
asxJ2HBERDetected.description: This trap indicates that High Bit Error Rate (HBER) is detected on the incoming signal.

asxJ2HBERCleared.name: asxJ2HBERCleared
asxJ2HBERCleared.description: This trap indicates that High Bit Error Rate (HBER) is cleared on the incoming signal.

asxJ2PAISDetected.name: asxJ2PAISDetected
asxJ2PAISDetected.description: This trap indicates that Payload Alarm Indication Signal (PAIS) is detected on the incoming signal.

asxJ2PAISCleared.name: asxJ2PAISCleared
asxJ2PAISCleared.description: This trap indicates that Payload Alarm Indication SIgnal (PAIS) is cleared on the incoming signal.

asxJ2AtmLCDDetected.name: asxJ2AtmLCDDetected
asxJ2AtmLCDDetected.description: This trap indicates that the specified J2 port is experiencing Loss of Cell Deliniation (LCD). A LCD failure is declared when the LCD defect persists for a period of 2.5 +/- 0.5 seconds.

asxJ2AtmLCDCleared.name: asxJ2AtmLCDCleared
asxJ2AtmLCDCleared.description: This trap indicates that the LCD failure identified by trap asxJ2AtmLCDDetected has been cleared. A LCD failure is cleared when the LCD defect is absent for 10 +/- 0.5 seconds.

asxJ2TLOCDetected.name: asxJ2TLOCDetected
asxJ2TLOCDetected.description: This trap indicates that Transmit Loss of Clock (TLOC) is detected.

asxJ2TLOCCleared.name: asxJ2TLOCCleared
asxJ2TLOCCleared.description: This trap indicates that Transmit Loss of Clock (TLOC) is cleared.

asxTP25LOSDetected.name: asxTP25LOSDetected
asxTP25LOSDetected.description: This trap indicates that LOS Alarm is detected on the incoming signal.

asxTP25LOSCleared.name: asxTP25LOSCleared
asxTP25LOSCleared.description: This trap indicates that LOS Alarm is cleared on the incoming signal.

asxOutputQueueCongested.name: asxOutputQueueCongested
asxOutputQueueCongested.description: This trap indicates that the output queue for the given priority has exceeded its dedicated length, and has begun overflowing into the shared buffer space on the netmod.

asxOutputQueueCellLoss.name: asxOutputQueueCellLoss
asxOutputQueueCellLoss.description: This trap indicates that the output queue for the given priority has overflowed and cells have been dropped.

asxExtendedModeViolation.name: asxExtendedModeViolation
asxExtendedModeViolation.description: This trap indicates that a series A or B network module was inserted into a switch board running in extended mode. Multicast will not work on the series B module without removing all series D modules and rebooting the rebooted.

asxNonextendedModeWarning.name: asxNonextendedModeWarning
asxNonextendedModeWarning.description: This trap indicates that a series C or greater network module was inserted into a switch board running in non-extended mode.

crConfMemoryOflow.name: crConfMemoryOflow
crConfMemoryOflow.description: This trap is generated when the allocated callrecord memory(as indicated by crMemoryAllocated) is exceeded.

crXfrPrimaryXfrFailed.name: crXfrPrimaryXfrFailed
crXfrPrimaryXfrFailed.description: This trap is generated when the call record transfer to the primary host(as indicated by crXfrPrimaryUrl) fails.

crXfrSecondaryXfrFailed.name: crXfrSecondaryXfrFailed
crXfrSecondaryXfrFailed.description: This trap is generated when the call record transfer to the secondary host(as indicated by crXfrSecondaryUrl) fails.

crConfMemAllocFail.name: crConfMemAllocFail
crConfMemAllocFail.description: This trap is generated when Callrecord functionality is unable to allocate memory as specified by crMemoryAllocated. This can happen when the crConfAdminStatus changes state from `off' or when the switch reboots when Callrecords is configured `on'.

crGeneralFailure.name: crGeneralFailure
crGeneralFailure.description: This trap is generated when any of the callrecord related functionality fails for any reason. One example would be when the Callrecord Module fails to schedule an interval timer.

asxDualScpSyncFailure.name: asxDualScpSyncFailure
asxDualScpSyncFailure.description: This trap indicates that automatic CDB synchronization is disabled due to failures.

asxDualScpSwitchOver.name: asxDualScpSwitchOver
asxDualScpSwitchOver.description: This trap indicates that the backup SCP has taken control of the switch.

asxDualScpHotSwap.name: asxDualScpHotSwap
asxDualScpHotSwap.description: This trap indicates that an SCP hotswap insertion or removal has occurred.

asxVPAISDetected.name: asxVPAISDetected
asxVPAISDetected.description: This trap indicates that the Alarm Indication Signal (AIS) is detected on the incoming (terminating) virtual path. This trap is generated once when the virtual path is declared to be in the active AIS state.

asxVPAISCleared.name: asxVPAISCleared
asxVPAISCleared.description: This trap indicates that the Alarm Indication Signal (AIS) has been removed from the incoming (terminating) virtual path. This trap is generated once when the virtual path is declared to be in the inactive AIS state.

asxVPRDIDetected.name: asxVPRDIDetected
asxVPRDIDetected.description: This trap indicates that the Remote Defect Indication (RDI) is detected on the incoming (terminating) virtual path. This trap is generated once when the virtual path is declared to be in the active RDI state.

asxVPRDICleared.name: asxVPRDICleared
asxVPRDICleared.description: This trap indicates that the Remote Defect Indication (RDI) has been removed from the incoming (terminating) virtual path. This trap is generated once when the virtual path is declared to be in the inactive RDI state.

asxNonextendedModeViolation.name: asxNonextendedModeViolation
asxNonextendedModeViolation.description: This trap indicates that a series D network module was inserted into a switch board running in non-extended mode. Multicast will not work on the series D module without removing all series B modules and rebooting the switch.

asxUnsupportedNetworkModule.name: asxUnsupportedNetworkModule
asxUnsupportedNetworkModule.description: This trap indicates that a unsupported network module was inserted into a switch.

asxDualScpRedundancy.name: asxDualScpRedundancy
asxDualScpRedundancy.description: This trap indicates that there is a change in the state of dual SCP Redundancy.

asxIpFilterViolation.name: asxIpFilterViolation
asxIpFilterViolation.description: An asxIpFilterViolation trap occurs when an incoming IP packet is unauthorized to enter the switch control port and has been dropped.

q2931AFRejectKnown.name: q2931AFRejectKnown
q2931AFRejectKnown.description: This trap is generated whenever any q2931 UNI with Address Filtering enabled rejects a Setup request because the request matched a template with the action 'reject'. The variables sent in the trap identify the source and destination UNI for the call.

q2931AFRejectUnknown.name: q2931AFRejectUnknown
q2931AFRejectUnknown.description: This trap is generated whenever any q2931 UNI with Address Filtering enabled rejects a Setup request because the address matched no template. The variables sent in the trap identify the source and destination UNI for the call.

q2931CreationFailure.name: q2931CreationFailure
q2931CreationFailure.description: This trap is generated whenever a switch fails to create a UNI. This is most likely due to a resource limitation on the switch.

asxPsCurrentDown.name: asxPsCurrentDown
asxPsCurrentDown.description: This trap alerts that one ATM switch power supply had a curent failure. The power supply that failed is identified by the power supply index.

asxPsCurrentUp.name: asxPsCurrentUp
asxPsCurrentUp.description: This trap alerts that one ATM switch power supply that had a curent failure is now up. The power supply that is back up is identified by the power supply index.

asxPs5VoltDown.name: asxPs5VoltDown
asxPs5VoltDown.description: This trap alerts that one ATM switch power supply had a +5V failure. The power supply that failed is identified by the power supply index.

asxPs5VoltUp.name: asxPs5VoltUp
asxPs5VoltUp.description: This trap alerts that one ATM switch power supply that had a +5V failure is now up. The power supply that is back up is identified by the power supply index.

asxSwitchLoginDetected.name: asxSwitchLoginDetected
asxSwitchLoginDetected.description: An asxSwitchLoginDetected trap signifies that a user logged in on the switch.

asxSwitchLoginFailed.name: asxSwitchLoginFailed
asxSwitchLoginFailed.description: An asxSwitchLoginFailed trap signifies that a user's attempt to log in on the switch failed.

pnniTdbGuardbandResrvFail.name: pnniTdbGuardbandResrvFail
pnniTdbGuardbandResrvFail.description: This trap is generated when guardband memory reserve for any of the PNNI TDB(Topology Database) related functionalites like creation,modification and deletion on objects like node, ptse,flags,interal prefixes,external prefixes and etc fails. The switch is low on memory.

pnniTdbInconsistentState.name: pnniTdbInconsistentState
pnniTdbInconsistentState.description: This trap is generated when PNNI TDB(Topology Database) is in an unrecoverable error condition due to MALLOC and other TDB related faliures. When this happenes the associated logical node is shutdown and this trap is sent.The switch has to be rebooted to bring this PNNI logical node up again.

asxShmem2OutputQueueCongested.name: asxShmem2OutputQueueCongested
asxShmem2OutputQueueCongested.description: This trap indicates that the output queue for the given priority has exceeded its dedicated length, and has begun overflowing into the shared buffer space on the netmod.

asxShmem2OutputQueueCellLoss.name: asxShmem2OutputQueueCellLoss
asxShmem2OutputQueueCellLoss.description: This trap indicates that the output queue for the given priority has overflowed and cells have been dropped.

fabricLvl3Lookup.name: fabricLvl3Lookup
fabricLvl3Lookup.description: This trap is generated when a fabric detects excessive level 3 lookup errors. The level 3 lookup count is read every second. If the lookup count is non-null for 5 consecutive seconds, then this trap is generated. If the errors continue, this trap will be generated continuously every 5 seconds. This trap can be caused by: a misconfigured PVC; bad hardware.

fabricCorrectedLookup.name: fabricCorrectedLookup
fabricCorrectedLookup.description: This trap is generated when the SCP detects inconsistant information in the HDCOMP lookup. The switch has corrected the bad information in the HDCOMP lookup ASIC's data structures.

spvcRerouteInitiated.name: spvcRerouteInitiated
spvcRerouteInitiated.description: This trap is sent when a SPVC is being re-routed due to a better path being found.

asxQ2931Down.name: asxQ2931Down
asxQ2931Down.description: This trap is generated whenever UNI signalling goes down.

asxQ2931Up.name: asxQ2931Up
asxQ2931Up.description: This trap is generated whenever UNI signalling goes up.

asxFabricDown.name: asxFabricDown
asxFabricDown.description: An asxFabricDown trap signifies that the sending protocol entity recognizes a failure in one of the ATM Switch fabric, that is identified by the board number. This is probably caused by a hot-swap of a fabric module.

asxFabricUp.name: asxFabricUp
asxFabricUp.description: An asxFabricUp trap signifies that the sending protocol entity recognizes a new operational ATM Switch fabric, that is identified by the board number. This is probably caused by a hot-swap of a fabric module.

asxQ2931CallClearing.name: asxQ2931CallClearing
asxQ2931CallClearing.description: This trap is generated whenever calls are cleared in a signalling interface for the following reasons. * Carrier loss * SONET alarms in case of SONE * VP failure

pnniSpvccDown.name: pnniSpvccDown
pnniSpvccDown.description: This trap is sent when a SPVC call is cleared or deleted. The pnniSpvcSrcDownReason indicates if the call was cleared due to a better route being found or a network failure. It also may indicate SPVC deletion. This trap is only sent if pnniSpvcTrapMode is all.

pnniSpvccUp.name: pnniSpvccUp
pnniSpvccUp.description: This trap is send when a SPVC call is established. It identifies the SPVC and the old and new cost. If the call has not been up before, the pnniSpvcSrcOldRouteCost will be -1. This trap is only sent if pnniSpvcTrapMode is failure or all.

pnniSpvccFail.name: pnniSpvccFail
pnniSpvccFail.description: This trap is sent when a SPVC call that is down fails to get connected on 16 consecutive attempts. This trap is only sent if pnniSpvcTrapMode is failure or all.

pnniSpvpcDown.name: pnniSpvpcDown
pnniSpvpcDown.description: This trap is sent when a SPVP call is cleared. The pnniSpvcSrcDownReason indicates if the call was cleared due to a better route being found or a network failure. It also may indicate SPVPC deletion. This trap is only sent if pnniSpvpcTrapMode is all.

pnniSpvpcUp.name: pnniSpvpcUp
pnniSpvpcUp.description: This trap is send when a SPVP call is established. It identifies the SPVP and the old and new cost. If the call has not been up before, the pnniSpvcSrcOldRouteCost will be -1. This trap is only sent if pnniSpvpcTrapMode is all or failure.

pnniSpvpcFail.name: pnniSpvpcFail
pnniSpvpcFail.description: This trap is sent when a SPVP call that is down fails to get connected on 16 consecutive attempts. This trap is only sent if pnniSpvpcTrapMode is all or failure.

asxPortCardDown.name: asxPortCardDown
asxPortCardDown.description: An asxPortCardDown trap signifies that the sending protocol entity recognizes a failure in one of the ATM Switch portcards, that is identified by the portcard name. This is probably caused by a hot-swap of the port card.

asxPortCardUp.name: asxPortCardUp
asxPortCardUp.description: An asxPortCardUp trap signifies that the sending protocol entity recognizes a new operational ATM Switch port card, that is identified by the portcard name. This is probably caused by a hot-swap of the port card.

asxServiceCategoryOutputQueueCongested.name: asxServiceCategoryOutputQueueCongested
asxServiceCategoryOutputQueueCongested.description: This trap indicates that the output queue for the service category has exceeded its dedicated length, and has begun overflowing into the shared buffer space on the netmod.

asxServiceCategoryOutputQueueCellLoss.name: asxServiceCategoryOutputQueueCellLoss
asxServiceCategoryOutputQueueCellLoss.description: This trap indicates that the output queue for the given service category has overflowed and cells have been dropped.

pnniNormalToOverloadTransition.name: pnniNormalToOverloadTransition
pnniNormalToOverloadTransition.description: This trap is generated on transition from the normal state to the overload state.

pnniOverloadToNormalTransition.name: pnniOverloadToNormalTransition
pnniOverloadToNormalTransition.description: This trap is generated on transition from the overload to the normal state.

syslogFacility.name: syslogFacility
syslogFacility.description: The syslog facility string, possible values are daemon, local[0-7].

syslogConsoleState.name: syslogConsoleState
syslogConsoleState.description: The syslog console state, ON means syslog messages are sent to console.

syslogDestinationTable.name: syslogDestinationTable
syslogDestinationTable.description: This table lists all the syslog destinations

syslogDestinationEntry.name: syslogDestinationEntry
syslogDestinationEntry.description: A structure containing the parameters for a syslog destination

syslogDestinationHost.name: syslogDestinationHost
syslogDestinationHost.description: The host IP address of the syslog destination

pnniPmpRerouteInitiated.name: pnniPmpRerouteInitiated
pnniPmpRerouteInitiated.description: This trap is sent when a party is being re-routed due to a better path being found or if a reroute is requested using a AMI command.

pnniPmpSpvcUp.name: pnniPmpSpvcUp
pnniPmpSpvcUp.description: This trap is send when a pmp SPVC call is established. This trap is only sent if pnniSpvcTrapMode is failure or all.

pnniPmpSpvcDown.name: pnniPmpSpvcDown
pnniPmpSpvcDown.description: This trap is sent when a pmp SPVC call is cleared. The pnniSpvcSrcDownReason indicates if the call was cleared due to a better route being found or a network failure. This trap is only sent if pnniSpvpcTrapMode is all.

pnniPmpSpvcFail.name: pnniPmpSpvcFail
pnniPmpSpvcFail.description: This trap is sent when a SPVC call that is down fails to get connected on 16 consecutive attempts. This trap is only sent if pnniSpvcTrapMode is failure or all.

pnniSpvxRGroupSwover.name: pnniSpvxRGroupSwover
pnniSpvxRGroupSwover.description: This trap is sent when a automatic switch over occurs in a SPVC Redundancy group that has automatic PVC switch over enabled.

asxSVXCPStateTransferFailed.name: asxSVXCPStateTransferFailed
asxSVXCPStateTransferFailed.description: This trap is sent when the SVx/SPVx Preservation module is unable to transfer call and interface state information to the Standby SCP, due either to temporary unavailablility of system resources or to a permanent system error requiring a system reboot.

asxSVXCPStateTransferRestarted.name: asxSVXCPStateTransferRestarted
asxSVXCPStateTransferRestarted.description: This trap is sent when the SVx/SPVx Preservation module has restarted its transfer of call and interface state information to the Standby SCP, which transfer was halted due to unavailablility of system resources.

asxSVXCPStateDroppedCall.name: asxSVXCPStateDroppedCall
asxSVXCPStateDroppedCall.description: This trap is sent when the SVx/SPVx Preservation module has insufficient memory to store one or more calls during its transfer of call and interface state information to the Standby SCP. Such calls therefore will be lost (not preserved on switchover). This trap is sent only once, no matter how many calls suffer this fate. Recovering any lost calls is possible only by disabling and then re-enabling SVx/SPVx Preservation, in order to provoke a complete retrial of the transfer process.
